title: good vegetable casserole
directions: Mix all of the ingredients together.
Put in greased casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: seven layer casserole(layer in order)
directions: Heat oven to 350 degrees and bake covered for 1 hour. Uncover and bake an additional 30 minutes or until bacon is crisp.

title: dot's sweet potato pie
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Boil sweet potatoes in water until tender when pierced with fork.
Cool slightly.
Peel potatoes and put in large mixing bowl.
Beat with mixer until smooth.
Stir in butter and sugar; beat in eggs one at a time.
Add spices, salt and milk.
Pour into unbaked pie crusts.
Bake in center of oven 70 minutes or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.

title: fudge
directions: Stir until dissolved over very low heat.
Cook over very low heat.
Run spoon over bottom of pan occasionally to be sure it doesn't stick.
Cook until firm ball stage, about 1 hour.
Set off stove for 30 to 40 minutes.
Beat with electric beater until it won't turn.
Beat more with wooden spoon.
Add pecans.

Can be put in a Pyrex dish and cut in squares or rolled into a fudge roll. Also can reduce heating time slightly and made into truffles dipped in flavored sugars, crushed almonds, flavored cocoa, etc.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Dilute cream of chicken soup with sour cream.
Pour melted butter over stuffing mix.
Layer in following order: zucchini, carrots, onion, cream of chicken soup and sour cream mixture, stuffing with butter on top.
Put in greased 2-quart casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: apple nut dessert
directions: Beat eggs in small bowl.
Gradually beat in sugar and vanilla. Fold in flour mixed with baking powder.
Fold in apples and nuts.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream shortening,
sugars,
eggs
and vanilla.	Combine salt, soda and flour.
Add
dry
mixture	to creamed mixture a little at a time.
Blend in oatmeal, nuts and raisins.
Divide dough into thirds and	form
into
long
rolls.
Wrap rolls in waxed paper and chill or freeze.

title: finger lickin' good fudge
directions: Grease 9 x 13-inch pan with margarine.
In large heavy pot, add sugar and evaporated milk; mix with wooden spoon.
Do not heat until sugar and milk have been thoroughly mixed.
Turn stove to medium-high, stirring constantly while heating until it comes to a boil.
Turn heat down, but keep boiling.
Time for 7 minutes; stir frequently.
After 7 minutes, remove pot from heat.
To hot mixture, add remaining ingredients except nuts.
Mix until it looks like fudge, about 5 minutes.
Add dash of salt and nuts. Pour in pan and when lukewarm, refrigerate.

title: cream cheese fruit dip
directions: Blend all ingredients thoroughly.
Excellent for dipping fresh fruit.

title: pickled beets or eggs
directions: Add enough water to beet liquid to measure 2 cups.
Heat liquid mixture, sugar and vinegar.
Pour over beets/eggs.
Cover and refrigerate 12 hours.

title: easy microwave chicken
directions: Place chicken
in
casserole dish.
Cover with mushroom soup. Place sliced
mushrooms
on top of soup.
Sprinkle with grated cheese.
Cover
casserole
dish and microwave for 20 to 25 minutes on Full power.

title: microwave chicken a la king
directions: In a 2-quart casserole, combine butter and green pepper. Microwave on High for 3 to 4 minutes or until green pepper is tender.
Blend in flour, salt and pepper. Gradually stir in broth and milk.
Microwave on Medium-high (170°) for 6 to 7 minutes or until sauce thickens, stirring 2 or 3 times.
Stir in chicken, peas, pimiento and sherry.
Microwave on Medium-high for 6 to 7 minutes or until heated through, stirring 2 times.
Serve over toast, hot cooked noodles or rice.

title: chili
directions: Saute onion, green pepper and garlic powder in small amount of cooking oil.
Combine all ingredients, except tomato sauce, in heavy skillet.
Cook until meat loses its pink color and onions become transparent.
Add tomato sauce and simmer 30 minutes to 1 hour.
Can add more chili powder.

title: sweet pickle relish
directions: Combine cucumbers, onions and peppers in large bowl; sprinkle with salt and cover with cold water.
Let stand 2 hours.
Prepare home canning jars and lids according to manufacturer's instructions.
Drain vegetables thoroughly; press out liquid. Combine sugar, vinegar, celery seed and mustard seed in a large saucepot; bring to boil.
Add drained vegetables; simmer for 10 minutes.
Carefully pack hot relish into hot jars, leaving 1/4-inch headspace.
Adjust caps.
Process 10 minutes in boiling water bath canner.
Yields approximately 8 half pint jars.

title: moist chocolate cake
directions: Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: sweet and sour baked beans
directions: Place onions in skillet.
Add sugar, mustard, garlic salt, salt and vinegar.
Cook for 20 minutes, covered.
Add onion mixture to beans.
Add crumbled bacon.
Pour into a 3-quart casserole.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Makes 12 servings.

title: southern spoon bread
directions: In medium saucepan, gradually stir in cornmeal and salt into boiling water.
Cook over medium flame, stirring constantly until thick.
Add butter and milk; beat until smooth.
Let cool to room temperature.
Beat egg whites until stiff peaks form; set aside. Using same beaters, beat egg yolks until thick and lemon colored. Stir egg yolks and baking powder into cornmeal mixture, mixing well.
Gently fold in egg whites until well combined.
Pour into a greased 2-quart casserole.
Bake in a preheated 375° gas oven for 40 to 50 minutes until golden brown and puffy.
To serve, spoon from casserole and serve hot with butter.
Yield:
8 servings.

title: potato cakes
directions: Mix together well.
Shape into
patties,
like hamburgers. Fry in buttered skillet until
golden brown.
Serve with pancake syrup, gravy, etc.

title: cauliflower and broccoli salad
directions: Mix together all ingredients.

title: veggie squares
directions: Lightly grease 10 x 15-inch aluminum pan.
Separate the 2 sections of crescent rolls from each can and lay flat in the pan for crust, pressing a little bit up the sides.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Let cool.
Mix together cream cheese, mayonnaise and dry salad dressing.
Spread over crust.
Cut vegetables into very small pieces or use food processor.
Mix all vegetables together and spread over cheese mixture.
Sprinkle Parmesan cheese on top and cut into squares.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Place broccoli, rice, onion and cream of mushroom soup in 2-quart casserole dish.
Stir to mix.
Make cheese sauce by adding milk to Cheez Whiz and heat until cheese is melted.
Add to broccoli mixture and mix well.
Top with cracker crumbs.
Drizzle melted oleo over crumbs.
Bake at 350° until lightly brown.

title: swedish cookies
directions: Mix and chill.
Roll into small balls and put on cookie sheet half thickness of a ball apart.
Bake about 12 minutes at 350°. When done, roll in powdered sugar and pack in airtight jar.
These cookies improve with age.

title: sour cream coconut cake
directions: At least 3 days before needed to serve; mix sour cream, sugar and coconut.
Place in covered container and refrigerate overnight.
The
next
day
bake
cake
according
to
package directions.
Cool.
Slice
each
layer in 2 (making 4).
Place each layer cut-side up.
"Ice" with coconut mixture.
Place in tightly
covered
container.
Refrigerate
for at least 1 day. This keeps for a long time.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Clean mushrooms, cutting off stems.
Saute onions and stems in butter.
Cook sausage and drain.
In saucepan, cook spinach, then drain.
Mix all ingredients.
Stuff mushrooms.
Place in shallow greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: aunt mae pearl's buttermilk pound cake
directions: Cream 2 cups sugar with margarine or shortening.
Add egg yolks, one at a time.
Sift dry ingredients and add to creamed mixture with milk.
Beat egg whites with remaining 1 cup sugar. Add extract.
Fold into batter.
Bake at 300° for 90 minutes.

title: orange creamsicle jello
directions: Combine graham crackers, 1/4 cup sugar and margarine.
Cover bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan with crust.
Bake at 375 ° for 8 minutes.
Cool.

title: hawaiian wedding cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a large bowl and bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan (greased and floured) for 40 to 45 minutes at 350°. Frost with Cream Cheese Frosting.
Best served cold.

title: corned beef spread
directions: Mash corned beef.
Add horseradish, mustard and pickle relish. Add mayonnaise to make spreading consistency.
Serve with assorted crackers.
Yield: About 2 cups.

title: sour cream apple cake
directions: Fresh hard pears are good also and a mixture of apples and pears are good.

title: hot apple 'n cabbage slaw
directions: Cook cabbage and onion in margarine for about 10 minutes.
Add the rest of the ingredients.
Cover and cook for about 5 to 10 minutes; serve hot.
Serves 6. Contains 160 calories.

title: pepperoni bites
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients.
Stir in cheese and pepperoni.
Put in 13 x 9 x 2-inch greased pan.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes or until browned.
Cool and cut into 1-inch cubes.

title: crazy pea salad
directions: Layer the first 6 ingredients in casserole dish.
Combine mayonnaise and sugar and spread evenly over top of salad, sealing to edge of dish.
Sprinkle bacon bits and cheese over mayonnaise. Refrigerate, covered, for 6 to 8 hours or overnight.
Garnish with tomatoes when serving.

title: german red-cabbage
directions: Shred cabbage.
Mix remaining ingredients (except bacon). Pour over cabbage.
Add bacon.
Bring mixture to a boil.
Simmer, covered, for 45 minutes or until tender.

title: chicken in vermouth
directions: Cut up chicken; wash and dry.
Rub with garlic, salt, pepper and paprika.
Put salad oil in roasting pan or casserole.
Add chicken and dot with butter; add vermouth.
Baste frequently in 325° oven.
Bake 2 to 2 1/2 hours or until tender.

title: baked chicken and rice casserole
directions: Combine cream of chicken soup, celery soup, milk and instant rice in a 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Arrange pieces of chicken on top and then sprinkle on onion soup mix.
Cover tightly with foil and bake at 325° for about 2 1/2 hours.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Crush 1 cup berries thoroughly.
Add 1 cup water; bring to a boil.
Mix sugar and cornstarch with a little water; stir into the boiling berries.
Cook for 3 minutes, until clear.
Cool.
Place remaining berries in pie shell.
Pour lukewarm mixture over berries; place in refrigerator until cornstarch mixture sets. Before serving, cover with whipped cream.

title: cheese ball
directions: Gradually stir ingredients into cream cheese; chill well. Form into ball.
Roll in 1 cup chopped pecans.
Chill until served.
Garnish with parsley, cherries or pineapple slices.

title: refrigerator rolls
directions: Beat well with mixer the first 3 ingredients.
Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Mix all ingredients together, kneading real good.

title: california blend casserole
directions: Boil vegetables on top of stove for 5 minutes.
Drain. Combine cheese, soup and milk.
Add to vegetables.
Place in casserole and bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Remove and serve.

title: cheesy potatoes
directions: Melt butter, then add vegetable packet.
Cube potatoes.
Mix potatoes and broccoli in a 9 x 11-inch microwave dish.
Put in microwave oven for 10 minutes on High.
After 10 minutes, take out.
Stir.
Put back in for 8 minutes, then take out.
Sprinkle cheese on top.
Put back for 2 minutes.

title: buttercups (tarts)
directions: Quarter cherries.
Add butter, light corn syrup, sugar, salt and beaten eggs to top of double boiler.
Add enough cornstarch to thicken mixture.
Add cherries and almond extract.

title: soup (for chapah)
directions: Fry onion in oil until golden brown.
Add meat, cook until almost done and add peeled potatoes.
Cook until almost ready and then add tomatoes.
After tomatoes are ready, add water and bring to a boil, then simmer for 1/2 hour or until cooked or soup looks thick.

title: betty sautter's buffalo chips
directions: Line 2 cookie sheets with graham crackers.
Combine margarine and sugar and boil for 3 minutes.
Pour over crackers.
Top with pecan pieces.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: easy chocolate truffle
directions: Beat cream cheese until smooth.
Gradually add sugar, beating until well blended.
Add melted chocolate and vanilla; mix well. Refrigerate about 1 hour.
Shape into 1 inch balls.
Roll in walnuts, cocoa or coconut.
Store in refrigerator.
Makes about 5 dozen candies.

title: champ(traditional irish potato dish)
directions: Cook the chopped scallions, greens as well, in milk.
Drain, but save the milk.
Add to the mashed potatoes.
Beat well together and add enough hot milk to make the dish creamy and smooth.

title: wiltfong's german pancakes
directions: Put 1/3 cube butter stick in a glass 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Let it melt until it sizzles in oven. (Can do this while oven is preheating to 375°.) After butter is melted, pour in other mixed ingredients. Bake 20 minutes. Dust with powdered sugar and serve with syrup.

title: layered dessert
directions: Combine graham cracker crumbs, 1/4 cup sugar and melted butter. Press into bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Beat cream cheese with sugar and 2 tablespoons milk until smooth.
Fold in half the whipped topping; spread over crust.
Using 3 1/2 cups cold milk, prepare pudding as directed on package.
Pour over cream cheese layer. Chill several hours or overnight.
Spread remaining whipped topping over pudding.
Garnish with grated chocolate or chopped nuts, if desired.
(You may also substitute pistachio, lemon or butterscotch flavors of pudding.)

title: stuffed shells
directions: Cook shells as directed.
Brown ground beef and onion.
In bowl, mix bread (cubed in small pieces), milk and egg.
Add to bowl of bread mixture the meat, 1/2 of the cheese and a small amount of spaghetti sauce.
Spray with Pam a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Spread 1/2 cup of spaghetti sauce evenly over the bottom. Fill each shell with meat mixture and place in dish.
Pour spaghetti sauce over filled shells.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 350° until bubbly; sprinkle rest of cheese over top and bake until cheese melts (about 15 minutes).

title: orange chili barbecue sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients in small saucepan; mix well.
Heat the sauce until it comes to a boil, stirring constantly.
Simmer for 1 minute.
Use the sauce immediately as a marinade and baste for grilled chicken, ribs, beef or pork, or cool and store in the refrigerator for future use.

title: cherry topped cheese cake
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Reserve 1 cup dry cake mix.
In large bowl combine remaining mix, 1 egg and oil (mixture will be crumbly).
Press mix evenly into bottom and 3/4 up sides of a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
In same bowl, blend cream cheese and sugar.
Add 3 eggs and reserved cake mix.
Beat 1 minute.
Slowly add milk and flavorings.
Mix until smooth.
Pour into crust, bake for 45 to 55 minutes at 300°.
Chill and store in refrigerator. When cool, top with pie filling.

title: easy cobbler
directions: Pour batter in butter coated pan.
Add fruit and bake at 350° until crust comes to the top and is golden brown.

title: prune cake
directions: Sift together the first 7 ingredients and set aside.
Put into a large bowl and blend the next 3 ingredients.
Add prunes.
Add alternately the buttermilk and the above flour mixture.
Bake in 2 (9-inch) layer pans at 350° for 35 minutes or until cake springs back when punched.
When cool, cut each layer in two with dental floss, making 4 layers and spread with the following mixture.

title: squash casserole
directions: Boil squash and onions until tender.
Drain well and mix with sour cream.
Layer in casserole dish as follows:
1 layer squash, 1 layer cheese and 1 layer crumbled Ritz crackers.
Repeat layers, ending with crackers.
Dot top with margarine.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until golden brown.

title: bearnaise sauce
directions: Combine the first 6 ingredients in a small heavy saucepan; bring to a boil and cook 1 minute.
Strain mixture, reserving liquid.
Discard solids.
Return liquid to saucepan; stir in sour cream.
Place over low heat and cook 1 minute or until warm, stirring frequently.
Yields 3/4 cup (serving size:
3 tablespoons).
Calories 76; protein 2.4 g; fat 5.1 g; carbohydrate 6 g.

title: m&m's cookies
directions: Blend shortening and sugar.
Add vanilla and eggs.
Sift dry ingredients together and add to the sugar and egg.
Stir in the 1/2 cup M&M's and reserve the rest for the tops.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: sour cream cake
directions: Blend butter, brown sugar, white sugar, flour and cinnamon. Save 1 cup for topping on cake.
Add to balance of mixture the sour cream, eggs and soda.
Mix together.
Add chocolate chips, nutmeats or both.
Pour batter in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle with the 1 cup dry mixture for topping with added chips or nuts. Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: corn salad
directions: Salt and pepper to taste.
Line bowl with lettuce and fill with salad.

title: party pizzas
directions: Brown sausage; add cheese (cut into chunks), stirring until mixture is creamy. Spread on party rye. May be frozen.

title: empress xi west meets east sukiyaki-japanese
directions: Saute onion in butter in a large skillet until transparent. Season beef with salt and pepper.
Add to onion and cook until browned on all sides.
Stir in mushrooms, celery, bean sprouts, baby corn, water chestnuts, leeks and soy sauce.
Cook 5 to10 minutes, then add spinach or watercress.
Cook 2 minutes. Meanwhile, dissolve the bouillon cube in hot water in a saucepan. Stir in rice.
Pour into center of ingredients in skillet.
Cover and let simmer over low heat 5 minutes.
Do not overcook.
Serve with additional soy sauce, if desired.
Makes 4 servings.

title: seafood de george
directions: Saute onion in butter over medium heat until almost clear.
Add pressed garlic and mushroom stems; saute for about 2 to 3 minutes. Add scallops; saute 2 minutes.
Add shrimp; cook until almost "red," about 6 minutes.
Squeeze in juice of 1/2 lime.
Add red bell pepper, green onions, tomatoes and mushroom tops; cook about 4 to 5 minutes, until tomatoes "wilt."
Add crab and stir.
Pour white sauce; stir in and cook over low heat until sauce thickens. Remove from heat.
Serve over bed of white rice.
Serves 4.

title: company chicken cordon blue
directions: Place each piece of chicken between 2 sheets of wax paper. Flatten to 1/4-inch thickness, using a meat mallet or rolling pin. Sprinkle with salt and pepper. Combine eggs and milk. Brush both sides of chicken with milk mixture. Place a piece of ham and a piece of cheese in center of each chicken piece. Brush top of cheese slices with milk mixture. Fold ends over ham and cheese. Roll up, beginning with long side. Secure with toothpicks. Dredge chicken in flour. Dip in remaining milk mixture and coat with bread crumbs. Cover and chill 1 hour.

title: oriental hot mustard
directions: In a bowl, combine mustard, cooking or salad oil and salt. Stir in boiling water; mix.
Serve with egg rolls.

title: brownie trifle
directions: Bake brownies as directed in 9 x 13 pan. Cool; crumble. Prepare pudding mix with milk. Do not chill. In trifle bowl, layer 1/3 crumbled brownies, 1/3 pudding, 1/3 Cool Whip and 1/3 candy. Repeat twice. Cover. Chill at least 8 hours, up to 24 hours.

title: hamburger tomato soup
directions: Brown hamburger and onions.
Add other ingredients and put in crock-pot and cook for 3 to 4 hours.

title: lemon chicken with thyme
directions: In a plastic bag, combine flour, salt and pepper.
Shake.
Add chicken and shake to coat lightly.
Remove chicken and reserve excess flour.
In a large skillet, warm 1 tablespoon oil over medium heat.
Add chicken and brown on one side, about 5 minutes. Add remaining 1 tablespoon oil; turn chicken and brown on other side, about 5 minutes.
Transfer chicken to a plate and set aside. Coarsely chop onion.
Add margarine to the skillet.
When melted, add onion and cook, stirring, until softened, 2 to 3 minutes. Stir in reserved seasoned flour and cook, stirring until flour is completely incorporated, about 1 minute.

title: spice tea
directions: Make tea.
Add spices; bring to boil.
Remove from heat.
Add juices and sugar; simmer or heat before serving.

title: chili
directions: Brown meat with onion. Add everything else in a large stockpot. Season to taste. Let simmer over low heat for 2 to 3 hours. Best if cooked the day before.

title: rice krispies balls
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in a saucepan.
Cook until like a thin jam, about 10 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add nuts and Rice Krispies.
Mix well.
Roll about 1 teaspoon at a time in coconut to form balls.
Cool and store in airtight container.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: homemade marshmallows
directions: Soften gelatin in 1/2 cup cold water. In 2-quart saucepan, combine sugar, corn syrup and 1/3 cup water. Cook to soft-ball stage, stirring only until sugar dissolves. Remove from heat and stir in gelatin until dissolved. Set aside to cool for 10 minutes. Beat egg white in small bowl to stiff peaks. Slowly add syrup, beating on high speed until candy stands in soft peaks. Pour onto plain brown paper and spread into 12 x 10 rectangle pan. Let stand overnight. Dust top with powdered sugar. Turn over onto another piece of paper. Moisten brown paper and peel off.

title: summer relish
directions: Combine all ingredients; toss gently.
Chill for 1 hour before serving. Yields 8 servings.

title: chocolate marshmallow turtles
directions: Put pecans in groups of 4 on a microwave baking sheet lined with non-stick paper.
Place a marshmallow on top of the pecans. Microwave on High for 15 to 30 seconds or until
the marshmallows just start to puff.
Place the chocolate chips and the vegetable shortening in a small bowl.
Microwave on medium for 2 to 4 minutes, stirring frequently until the chocolate melts.
Spoon over the top of each turtle to cover the marshmallow.
Leave to set completely before serving.

title: chicken curry
directions: Brown onions and celery in oil.
Blend in flour and broth. Cook, stirring, until thickened.
Add juice, Worcestershire sauce and seasonings.
Add chicken; heat thoroughly.
Serve over cooked rice.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake in greased casserole at 350° for 1 hour.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix thoroughly (looks like a mess); pour into a greased and floured Bundt or tube pan.	Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 10 minutes.

title: chocolate billionaires
directions: Microwave caramels and water in 2-quart glass measure on 100% power for 3 minutes, stirring after 1 1/2 minutes.
Stir well; mix in pecans and cereal.
Drop mixture by teaspoonful onto greased waxed paper-lined baking sheets.
Insert a toothpick in center of each candy; chill until firm.
Microwave chocolate chips in 1-quart glass measure on 100% power for 2 minutes.
Stir in vegetable shortening.
Dip candies into chocolate.
Place onto waxed paper.
Chill.
Store in an airtight container.
Makes 4 dozen candies.

title: devil's fudge cake
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Add vanilla and eggs.
Blend in cocoa.
Sift flour, soda and salt.
Add to creamed mixture with the ice water.
Bake in a greased and lightly floured pan at 350° for 30 minutes or until done.

title: brown sugar coconut pie
directions: Combine sugar and eggs; beat well.
Add butter, water, vanilla and coconut; mix well.
Pour into pie crust.
Bake at 350° until firm.

title: oreo pie
directions: Mix all ingredients well and pour into a ready made Oreo pie crust.
Freeze for 6 hours before serving.

title: lemon nut cake
directions: Sift flour.
Mix raisins, nuts and flour.
Cream butter and sugar.
Add beaten egg yolks.
Add soda and water.
Add raisins, nuts and flour.
Add lemon extract.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Cook 2 3/4 hours at 250°.
Put pan of water under cake when cooking and aluminum foil on top.
Bake in a greased tube pan.

title: refrigerator bread dough
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients.
When mixture becomes lukewarm, add yeast, then add eggs.
Mix well.
Place dough in loaf pans; let rise until it doubles.
Bake at 375° until golden brown and when tapped on top a hollow sound will result.
Any extra dough may be stored in refrigerator for up to one week.

title: lazy lady stuffed cabbage
directions: Using a 4 qt. pot, brown pine nuts
in butter until golden brown.
Remove nuts with slotted spoon.
Saute meat in remaining butter.
Add rice and all seasonings.
Stir. Add water, tomatoes, pine nuts, garlic and cabbage.
Bring to a boil and simmer with lid for 25-30 mins. until rice is done.

title: polish noodles and cabbage(kluski z kapusta po polski)
directions: Melt butter in large skillet.
Add onion; saute until soft. Add cabbage; saute 5 minutes.
Stir in caraway seed, salt and pepper.
Cook noodles as directed on package, then drain.
Stir noodles into cabbage.
Add sour cream.
Cook 5 minutes longer, stirring frequently.

title: trail mix
directions: Mix oats, banana chips, pumpkin seeds, peanuts and raisins in ungreased rectangular pan (13 x 9 x 2-inch).
Pour margarine over mixture and toss until evenly coated.
Cook, uncovered, in 350° oven, stirring occasionally, for 15 minutes.
Cool.
Store in tightly covered container no longer than 4 weeks.

title: orzo and feta stuffed tomatoes
directions: Cut 1/4-inch off the top of each tomato.
Scoop out pulp and seeds.
Reserve pulp; discard seeds.
Finely chop 2 tomato shells; set aside.
sprinkle the insides of the remaining tomato shells with salt.
Invert on a paper towel and let drain 30 minutes.
Pat dry.
Combine orzo or rice, Feta, black olives, pine nuts, green onions, parsley, olive oil, basil, garlic, pepper and chopped tomato.
Mix well.
Spoon mixture into tomato shells.
Cover with plastic wrap and chill at least 1 hour before serving.
Serves 8.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Saute broccoli, margarine and onion.
Mix all together and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: creamy vegetable medley
directions: Steam vegetables until tender.
Place in casserole and top with soup, cheese and onion.
Bake at 350° until bubbly (about 45 minutes).
Serve hot.

title: vegetable rice casserole
directions: Run hot water over frozen vegetables to thaw.
Mix all ingredients.
Bake, uncovered, in 2-quart baking dish for 35 minutes at 350°.
(Sliced carrots may be added to make a more colorful dish.)

title: hot wings
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Bread chicken wings.
Fry chicken wings.
Mix remaining ingredients in saucepan.
Add chicken wings to sauce mix.
Place wings on cookie sheet, top with cheese and put in oven until cheese is melted.

title: coconut cream cake
directions: Bake cake according to box directions.
Mix Eagle Brand milk and creamed coconut together in bowl; set aside.
When cake comes out of oven, while hot, jab holes in cake and pour liquid mix over hot cake.
Let cool.
Top with Cool Whip and mix coconut flakes in Cool Whip.

title: old fashioned chess pie
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into an unbaked pie shell.
Bake in 350° oven for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: basic grilled salmon steaks(easy; see variations)
directions: If you are using charcoal, build a fire about 45 minutes before you plan to start cooking. If you're using a gas grill, turn it on about 10 minutes ahead of cooking.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix first 8 ingredients well.
Bake at 400° for 40 minutes. The last 5 minutes of baking, cover top lightly with crushed potato chips.
This should be mixed the day before and let set overnight.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Cut sirloin into small strips and brown in 1 tablespoon oil. Slice onion. Add to meat. Simmer about 5 minutes to let onions cook. Add all ingredients to meat and onions except the sour cream. Simmer until almost done. Add the sour cream, but do not bring to a boil (it will curdle). Simmer a few minutes and serve over noodles or rice.

title: amber's best brownies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
In large microwave-safe bowl, place butter.
Microwave 2 minutes or until melted.
Stir in sugar and vanilla.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well with spoon.
Add cocoa; beat until well blended.
Add flour, baking powder and salt; beat well.
Stir in nuts.
Pour batter into pan.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes or until brownies begin to pull away from sides of pan.
Cool completely. Cut into bars.

title: shoe peg corn casserole
directions: Mix.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: baked custard(heritage recipe)
directions: Scald milk in top of double boiler over hot water or on very low heat.
Beat eggs until slightly mixed, add sugar and salt. Stir the milk and vanilla slowly into the egg mixture. Pour custard into cups and sprinkle with nutmeg.

title: cheese cake
directions: In
bowl,
combine graham cracker crumbs, margarine and 1/4 cup
sugar.
Press	on bottom and 2 1/2-inches up sides of 8-inch spring-form pan; set aside.

title: squash patties
directions: Mix all ingredients well and drop by spoonful into hot grease.

title: irish potato soup
directions: Cook potatoes and onions together until tender.
Drain and save liquid.
Butter 6 quart saucepan.
Add parsley and basil, blend in flour, salt and pepper.
Gradually stir in cold milk. Add scalded milk and potato water.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly until thickened.
Add potatoes and onions; mix.
Serve with sprinkled parsley or paprika on top.

title: vegetable pickle
directions: Cut vegetables into bite-size pieces.
Add other ingredients and let stand at least 48 hours before serving.

title: michael's pirate pie
directions: Beat eggs slightly; add to meat (or fish).
Add mushrooms. Place in the bottom of a well-greased pie tin.
Top with tomato slices and cheese slices.
Spoon mashed potatoes over cheese. Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
Cut into wedges and serve hot.

title: scalloped chicken
directions: Cook chicken in 3 cups water.
Drain, reserving broth.
Remove from bone, skin and dice.
Break toasted bread into small pieces. Combine bread, chicken, eggs, oleo, celery and onion; mix well. Stir in broth, salt and pepper.
Spread mushroom soup over top. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes in a 3-quart plate that has been greased with oleo.

title: grilled turkey tenderloins
directions: In a shallow pan, blend all marinade ingredients together. Add turkey, turning to coat both sides.
Cover.
Marinate in refrigerator several hours or overnight, turning occasionally.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Combine cream cheese, peanut
butter,
sugar
and milk. Beat until smooth.
Gently fold in
Cool
Whip.
Pour into pie shell. Freeze 4 to 6 hours.
Thaw 10 minutes before serving.

title: texas potatoes
directions: Mix well the hash browns, soup, sour cream and butter.
Add salt, pepper and onion.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch glass dish.

title: okra and tomatoes creole style
directions: Fry bacon.
Drain and crumble.
Cook onion, stirring frequently, until soft.
Add okra and cover.
Stir occasionally until almost tender or until mixture is dry.
Add tomatoes, salt and pepper.
Mash tomatoes with a slotted spoon.
Cook over medium heat until tender.
Then add ketchup and bacon, stirring well. Adjust seasoning to taste.

title: popcorn balls
directions: Melt marshmallows with butter; add coloring, then pour over popped popcorn.
Butter hands.
Make balls; place on waxed paper.

title: potato casserole
directions: Combine all of the ingredients, except corn flakes and butter. Mix corn flakes with butter and spread on top.
Bake at 300° for 45 minutes.

title: apple dumplings
directions: Peel apples and cut into quarters.
Wrap in crescent rolls. Mix sugar, orange juice and margarine.
Pour over crescent wrapped apples and bake 1 hour in a 350° oven until rolls are brown.

title: veggie dish
directions: Fry bacon strips; drain.
Put onion, peppers, celery, zucchini and tomatoes in grease and saute until tender.
Add tomato sauce, water, wiener, crumbled bacon and rice.
Put lid on and simmer for 20 minutes.

title: cheese and broccoli casserole
directions: Melt Velveeta cheese,
mushroom
soup
and milk.
Layer broccoli and rice
in buttered casserole.
Pour cheese mixture over top.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour, until brown on top.

title: ladonna dip
directions: Mix cream cheese, picante, grated cheese, olives and onions. Use for tortilla chips.

title: hash brown potato casserole
directions: Combine potatoes, 1/2 cup butter, onion, pepper, soup, sour cream and cheese; stir well.
Spoon into a greased casserole. Crush cereal; stir in remaining butter.
Sprinkle over potato mixture.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.
Yields 10 to 12 servings.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Cook sugar, margarine and milk over medium heat, stirring constantly, until all is melted.
Cook until soft ball stage. Remove from heat; quickly stir in marshmallow cream and peanut butter until all is melted.
Pour into a buttered 9 x 13-inch pan. Set on wire rack until cool.
Cut into pieces and remove from pan.

title: white taffy
directions: Start glucose, sugar and paraffin boiling, then strain gelatin through cloth into mixture.
Flavor while pulling.

title: pizza crust
directions: Mix yeast, sugar and water. Let stand 10 minutes. Add salt and oil, then 2 1/2 cups plain flour. Place remainder of flour on table and pour dough out on it and knead and roll until no longer sticky. Place in bowl with 2 teaspoons oil. Coat with oil.
Cover and let rise for 1 hour.
Punch down and then spread in lightly oiled pizza pan. Let set 15 minutes, then top and bake at 425°.

title: alphabet treats
directions: Combine syrup, sugar and jello in saucepan.
Stir over low heat for 5 minutes or until sugar and jello are completely dissolved.
Combine peanuts and cereal in large mixing bowl.
Add jello mixture.
Mix well.
Moisten hands in cold water. Form cereal mixture into 2-inch balls.
Wrap each in plastic wrap.

title: yeast bread
directions: Put all ingredients in mixing bowl and let yeast soften.

title: a southern boy's crab cakes
directions: Combine crab meat and mayo in medium-size bowl.
Add finely crushed crackers.
Add garlic.
Add Old Bay seasoning to taste. Fry in 1/2-inch of hot oil until golden brown.
Enjoy!!!!

title: pumpernickel rye dip
directions: Place bread on a large serving tray or platter.
Cut off top of the bread and pick out center.
Place bread pieces around the bread on the platter.
Mix all ingredients, place inside hollow bread.
Cut up the top of bread and place with the rest of bread pieces.
Use these pieces to eat dip with your fingers.

title: green rice casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients and place in a 2-quart casserole dish. Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: chocolate chip pie
directions: Mix together and put in graham cracker crust.
Bake at 325° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: easy lasagna
directions: In a large saucepan, cook beef and sausage.
Drain off fat. Stir in spaghetti sauce.
In a mixing bowl, beat egg; then stir in Ricotta or cottage cheese.

title: easy casserole
directions: Pan-fry sausage; drain and cut in pieces.
Cook and drain macaroni.
Add butter or margarine.
Add tomato sauce, Worcestershire sauce and seasoned salt.
Mix well.
Add sausage. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: 9 day cole slaw
directions: Grate cabbage, onions, celery and peppers.
Heat oil, vinegar, salt and sugar.
Bring to boil and add to cabbage.
Let set until cool and refrigerate.

title: best-in-the-world cookies
directions: Combine flour, soda, baking powder, salt, orange peel and cinnamon.
Mix well and set aside.
Cream together shortening and sugars.
Beat in eggs, then vanilla and orange juice.
Add flour mixture, blending well.
Stir in oats, cornflakes, rice cereal and raisins.
Drop by heaping teaspoonfuls onto lightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 325° for 12 to 14 minutes.
Cookies will flatten when removed from oven.
Cool slightly on cookie sheet.
Remove to rack to cool completely.
Makes 4 to 5 dozen.

title: million dollar fudge
directions: Cook sugar, milk and margarine together to 236°.
Add all other ingredients and pour into large buttered pan.

title: pineapple dip
directions: Drain canned pineapple and mix with cream cheese.
Add green onion, green pepper, pecans and seasoned salt.
Mix ahead 24 hours.

title: oreo cheesecake pies
directions: Crust:
Moisten cookie crumbs with melted margarine.
Divide mixture in half, pressing into two pie plates.

title: mother-in-law cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350° and grease a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.

title: hard pretzels
directions: Put pretzels on cookie sheet.
Mix remaining ingredients. Pour over pretzels.
Stir.
Bake at 250° or 275° for 20 minutes.

title: apple dessert
directions: Grease 6 x 8-inch baking dish with margarine.
Slice apples and put into dish.
Mix sugar, margarine, peanut butter and flour until crumbly.
Spread over top of the apples.
Bake in moderate oven until done (about 25 or 30 minutes).
Serve with whipped cream or ice cream.

title: hello dolly bars
directions: Melt butter in square cake pan.
Add remaining ingredients in order given.
Pour milk over mixture.
Bake at 320° for 20 or 30 minutes or until brown on top.
Cut into squares when cool.

title: brandy eggnog sauce
directions: Combine sugar and egg yolks.
Beat until smooth. Stir in brandy and vanilla. Fold whipped cream in.
Makes about 1 cup sauce.

title: ham puff
directions: Moisten potatoes with milk and beat well.
Add ham and yolks of eggs.
Season to taste.
Fold beaten egg whites into mixture. Turn into buttered pan, like an 8-inch pie pan.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes or until puffed and brown.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together with as much Miracle Whip salad dressing as desired.
Serve chilled.

title: barbecued ribs
directions: Prepare spice rub ingredients.
Mix in a small bowl.

title: corn pudding
directions: Beat eggs well and mix with other ingredients.
Place in buttered casserole.
Set in pan of water.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: cream cheese bars
directions: Mix cake mix, butter and 1 egg.
Press out in 9 x 13-inch greased pan like pizza dough.
Mix cream cheese, 2 eggs and 3/4 box of powdered sugar gradually to cheese and eggs.
Spread over top of dough.
Bake 35 to 45 minutes in 350° oven (until top is light brown).
Cool; sprinkle rest of powdered sugar over top of cool cake and cut into squares.

title: hawaiian bread cake
directions: Combine flour, soda, salt, sugar and nuts in large bowl and mix well by hand or large spoon.
Set aside.
Combine eggs with pinch of salt and beat well.
Add cooking oil, pineapple, coconut, mashed bananas, vanilla and cherries.
Beat slowly in large mixer bowl until combined slowly adding flour mixture.
Bake in greased Bundt pan for 1-1/2 hours at 325° or in mini loaf pans at 325° not as long as for Bundt pan.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Heat oven to 425. Melt butter in large saucepan over low heat.
Mix in flour and spices.
Cook over low heat and stir until mixture is smooth and bubbly.
Remove from heat.
Add broth and milk.
Heat to boiling stirring constantly.
Boil and stir 1 minute.
Remove from heat.
Add chicken and vegetables. Pour mixture into pie crust bottom.
Place refrigerated crust on top, trim, and seal edges.
Cover edge of pie with foil strips and bake for 35 to 40 minutes.
(Remove foil strips during last 15 minutes of baking.)

title: ribs with turnip
directions: Cut the ribs into 3 cm. (1 1/3 inch) long strips.
Blanch in boiling water and then drain.
Pare the turnips, then cut them into bite-size pieces.
Heat the wok, then add 1 tablespoon oil; stir-fry the green onion until fragrant.
Fry the ribs, then add water, soy sauce, sugar and salt and stir to mix.
Cook for 15 minutes over medium heat.
Add the turnips and cook for another 10 minutes, then serve.

title: mock chicken-noodle casserole
directions: Mix and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: banana pudding
directions: Separate eggs.
Mix sugar, flour, Pet milk, water and egg yolks and put with oleo in pan cooking over slow
heat.
Stir constantly until thickened.
Add vanilla.
Remove from heat and let pudding cool.
This keeps the bananas from turning brown. Once pudding is cooled, add the amount of sliced bananas and wafers that you like.
Use egg whites to then make the meringue and brown in oven.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Mix together first 4 ingredients.
Rounding tops, stuff mixture into washed and stemmed mushroom caps.
Place in an 8 x 11-inch shallow baking dish.
Add wine to cover bottom.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Garnish mushrooms with fresh parsley and serve.

title: smothered chicken
directions: Cut chicken and onion into pieces.
Put in a casserole dish. Dab butter on top of chicken and onion. Cook until chicken is white.
Add mushrooms.
Cook 10 to 15 minutes.
Cover chicken with cheese and melt.

title: cornbread for two
directions: Mix all ingredients well. Pour into greased iron skillet, muffin pans, etc.
Bake in a 475° preheated oven about 20 minutes or until browned.

title: nacho chicken casserole
directions: Mix soups, tomatoes, chicken, 1/2 bag tortilla chips, onion and cheese in a casserole dish.
Bake at 350 degrees for 45 minutes.
After 35 minutes, crush remaining tortilla chips and put on top.
Bake for the final 10 minutes.

title: baking powder biscuits
directions: Sift flour once, measure, add baking powder and salt and sift again.
Add shortening and cut into the dry ingredients until the mixture resembles fine meal.
Add milk (amount depends on kind of flour used) and stir until flour is dampened and mixture forms a soft dough and follows the spoon about the mixing bowl.
Turn out onto a lightly floured board and knead lightly one-half minute. Roll out 1/2 to 3/4 inch thick and cut with a floured biscuit cutter.
Arrange on baking sheet and bake in a 450° oven for 12 to 15 minutes, or until golden brown.
This will make 12 medium size biscuits.

title: banana cake
directions: Sift and measure dry ingredients.
Cream sugar and shortening. Add eggs and beat.
Add bananas and mix.
Add flour, milk and vanilla alternately; mix well.
Bake in two layers at 375° for about 25 to 30 minutes.
Frost with Buttercream Frosting.

title: shrimp jambalaya
directions: Heating cooking oil, add flour; cook slowly until golden brown, stirring constantly.
Add onions, peppers, garlic and celery and cook slowly until transparent, stirring often.
Add tomato sauce and Creole seasoning.
Let cook until oil rises to top.
Add rice, shrimp and 2 1/2 cups water.
Cook, covered, over low heat until rice is tender.
Add more water if mixture appears too dry. Just before serving, mince parsley and green onion tops and add to mixture.

title: nesselrode pie
directions: Make and bake a basic pie crust.

title: chocolate cake frosting
directions: Have butter in bowl at room temperature. Add 1 cup sugar and all cocoa and some milk. Beat well. Add remaining ingredients, alternating wet/dry. Frosting should be fluffy and easy to spread.

title: jello dessert
directions: Mix all ingredients and chill until firm.

title: marshmallow treats
directions: Bring Karo and sugar to boil and stir in peanut butter.
Pour over Rice Krispies and mix.
Press mixture in pan, firm, but not too hard.
Melt chips together and pour over for frosting.

title: texas brownies
directions: Combine flour, sugar and salt in mixing bowl.
In saucepan, mix 1 stick margarine, Crisco, 4 tablespoons cocoa and water. Bring to boil and pour over dry ingredients.
Add eggs, buttermilk, soda and vanilla to mixture.
Pour mixture into ungreased jelly roll pan.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: rice broccoli casserole
directions: Cook rice and broccoli according to directions.
Layer in 9 x 13-inch baking dish or other large casserole.
Top with Velveeta chunks.
Combine soup and egg; season to taste and pour over vegetable, rice and cheese.
Top with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: peanut butter cups
directions: Melt oleo in large 4-quart pan.
Stir in remaining ingredients except chocolate chips and wax.
Use hands, dough is stiff; form balls.

title: wassail bowl
directions: Put the water in an enamel pan and heat slowly.
Stir in the cloves, ginger, grated nutmeg, mace, coriander and cardamon seeds and boil for 5 minutes.
Rub the sugar on the rind of the lemon to extract the zest and add this to the pan.
Carefully stir in the sherry.
Break the 3 eggs into a large basin and add the egg yolks, beat well and pour over them, a little at a time, 1 and 1/2 cups of the hot liquid from the pan.
It must not be too hot.
Bring the rest of the liquid to near boiling point and pour it into the basin, stirring vigorously until the mixture is light and frothy.

title: weight watchers vegetable soup
directions: Mix all ingredients and cook until vegetables are tender.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Flour and quickly brown pork chops in Crisco.
While browning pork chops, wash and peel potatoes.
Cut into medium size slices. Place potato slices in bottom of a 2-quart baking dish.
Peel and cut onion into slices and place in a layer on top of potatoes. Salt and pepper to taste.
Pour cream of soup on top and spread over entire casserole.
Remove bones from pork chops and place them on top of casserole ingredients.
Cover and bake 45 minutes at 400°.

title: king's hawaiian french toaststilwell, kansas
directions: Slice King's Hawaiian Bread and set aside.
Allow slices to dry.
Blend all ingredients well.
Before dipping each slice rapidly on both sides, stir ingredients to keep spices blended. Do not soak!
Place dipped bread into a heated skillet, turn when golden brown.

title: party crackers
directions: Mix oil, dill weed and dressing mix together.
Dip crackers in mix.
Lay out to dry on paper towels.

title: chocolate sheet cake
directions: Cake Mixture:
Melt 2 sticks margarine, 4 tablespoons cocoa and 1 cup water.
Add to 2 cups sugar, 2 cups flour and 1 tablespoon baking soda.
Add this to the 1 1/2 cups buttermilk, eggs and 1 tablespoon vanilla.
Mix together well.
Pour into greased and floured 17 x 11 x 3/4-inch jelly roll pan.
Bake for 15 to 20 minutes at 350°.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Use one box of yellow cake mix; follow directions on package and bake.
Let cake cool completely and then crumble half of cake into punch bowl.
Mix pudding and pour over cake.
Add a layer of crushed pineapple and a layer of fruit cocktail.
Crumble the remaining cake over the fruit cocktail.
Cover with cherry pie filling.
Cover pie filling with Cool Whip and sprinkle with nuts. Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: baked chicken or swiss steak
directions: May also use for Swiss steak. Use round steak or chicken fry. Roll in flour and brown. Cover with sauce. May also add sliced onion. Use 9 x 12 Pyrex baking dish. Bake 1 hour in oven at 350°.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients (first 7). Pour into 9 x 13 casserole dish sprayed with Pam. Top with corn flakes. Pour melted margarine on corn flakes. Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: pecan crescents
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Stir in water and vanilla.
Then stir in nuts and flour.
Chill 3 to 4 hours or overnight.
Form in thin long logs and form into crescents 2 to 3-inches long.
Bake at 325° for 15 minutes on ungreased cookie sheet.
Do not brown. When cool, roll in powdered sugar.

title: cream banana pudding
directions: In large bowl, combine sweetened condensed milk and water; add pudding mix.
Beat well.
Chill 5 minutes in refrigerator.
Fold in whipped cream.
Spoon 1 cup of mixture in 2 1/2-quart glass serving bowl.
Top with 1/3 wafers, banana and pudding.
Repeat ending with pudding.
Refrigerate.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: diabetic fat free sugarless granola
directions: Mix dry ingredients. Add vanilla to water and mix with dry ingredients. Spread in shallow nonstick pan. Bake in preheated oven at 350° for 15 minutes. Lower heat to 225° until cereal is dry. Drying time is approximately 2 hours.

title: toasted coconut pumpkin pie
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
In a large bowl combine pumpkin, milk, eggs, spices, salt and 1/2 cup coconut.
Mix well.
Pour into pastry shell.
Bake 15 minutes.
Reduce oven temperature to 350° and bake 35 to 40 minutes more, until knife inserted comes out clean.
Cool.
Garnish with whipped cream and remaining coconut. Refrigerate leftovers.

title: caramel crunch popcorn
directions: In a large bowl (greased), combine first 4 ingredients.
Set aside.

title: broccoli cheese soup
directions: Saute onion in oleo until tender. Bring water with bouillon cubes to a boil. Add noodles and cook for 5 minutes. Don't drain. Add onion to water and noodles. Add broccoli, garlic salt, salt and pepper; cook until broccoli is thawed. Add milk and Velveeta. Stir until cheese melts.

title: meat loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients thoroughly.
Shape into a loaf in a baking pan.
Bake 1 1/4 hours or until done. Drain off excess fat.

title: shrimp boats
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Add salt and pepper to taste. This recipe will serve 4 people.

title: italian spaghetti sauce
directions: Saute green
pepper
and onion in olive oil.
Add meat; drain fat.
Add remaining ingredients; simmer for 2 1/2 hours. Add spaghetti.	You may freeze sauce for up to 3 months.

title: santa clara chicken
directions: Flour, salt and pepper chicken breasts.
Brown both sides of breasts in olive oil.
Place chicken in large baking dish.
Mix remaining ingredients and pour over chicken.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Uncover and continue to bake for 15 minutes.

title: family punch
directions: Combine banana, milk, honey, vanilla and ice in container of electric blender; whirl until smooth.
Pour into two 10-ounce highball glasses.
Garnish with lime wedges.

title: cayenne chicken breasts
directions: Beat eggs; add buttermilk and mix well.
Sprinkle red pepper and salt on chicken breasts to taste.
Dip in eggs and buttermilk, then flour.
Fry in peanut oil until tender.

title: beer batter for fish
directions: Mix all ingredients together to make the batter.
Clean fish; wash and pat dry.
Flour on both sides, then dip in batter.
Fry in 1/4 inch of oil; brown.

title: ham sauce
directions: Mix together in a medium saucepan and let simmer slowly about 1/2 hour.

title: italian chicken
directions: Place chicken in casserole dish.
Pour the dressing over the chicken.
Bake in a preheated 350° oven for 30 to 45 minutes. Remove from oven.
Let set for 5 minutes before serving.

title: corn dogs
directions: Pat hot dogs dry with paper towel.
Heat oil (2 - 3 inches) to 365°.
Mix flour, cornmeal, baking powder and salt.
Cut in shortening.
Dip hot dogs in batter, allow excess batter to drip off.
Fry 6 minutes turning once.
Insert wood skewers in end of each.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Mix shortening and 1 1/2 cups sugar.
Add eggs and mix well. Add flour, soda, baking powder and salt; mix well.
Roll in walnut size balls and roll in cinnamon and sugar mix.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet and bake 8 to 10 minutes at 400° until lightly brown but soft.

title: barbecue sauce (texas style)
directions: Mix ingredients in large pot and cook on high until begins to boil. Lower heat so contents cook just below a boil for 2 hours. Let simmer on low heat for 2 additional hours or until thick. Be sure to stir every 15 to 20 minutes.

title: petite cream puffs(about 60)
directions: In saucepan, melt butter in boiling water and salt.
Add the flour all at one time.
Remove from heat.
Beat the mixture by hand, vigorously.
Add to the mixture, 1 egg at a time, beating vigorously each time, until all eggs are done.
Drop by tiny teaspoonfuls onto a greased baking sheet.
Bake at 450° or until golden.
This makes a lot.
You can fill the puffs with a variety of fillings.
My favorite is chicken salad.
Can fill with puddings, ham salad, tuna salad, etc.
These can be prepared and frozen (unfilled).

title: sugar-free quick and easy spoon on topping
directions: Whip chopped fruit in a blender until smooth.
To prepare, whip at high speed until peaks form.
Yields 1 3/4 cups.

title: marshmallow delights
directions: Separate rolls into 8 triangles.
Combine sugar and cinnamon. Dip each marshmallow into butter, roll in cinnamon/sugar and place on a triangle.
Pinch dough around marshmallow, sealing all edges. Dip tops of dough into remaining butter and cinnamon/sugar. Place with sugar side up in greased muffin cups.
Bake at 375° for 13 to 15 minutes.
Serve warm.
Yield:
8 servings.

title: punch
directions: Mix boiling water, Jell-O and sugar together, then add 1 gallon of water and 2 liter bottle of 7-Up.
Chill in refrigerator.

title: fig turnovers
directions: Combine first 8 ingredients and cook slowly until thickened. Cool. Roll pastry 1/8-inch thick and cut into 4-inch circles. Place a tablespoon of fig mixture on half of each circle. Moisten edges and fold other half over filling.
Pinch edges together and prick top.
Place on baking sheet and bake at 450° for 15 minutes. Makes 8 to 10.

title: snap bean casserole
directions: Drain green beans.
Mix cheese, soup and beans.
Mix in half the onions.
Cook in oven for 30 minutes at 350°.
After 25 minutes, spread on other half of onions, then cook remaining 5 minutes.

title: fruit salad
directions: Cook pudding according to directions using fruit juice for liquid.
Completely cool.
Add fruit and chill for several hours or overnight.

title: apricot orange tea
directions: Steep tea bags in boiled water for 5 minutes.
Remove tea bags and add apricot nectar, orange juice, sugar and cinnamon sticks. Stir well and simmer for 10 minutes.
Remove cinnamon sticks, insert cloves into lemon slices and float atop tea in mugs.

title: creamy chocolate cheesecake pie
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Prepare crust but do not bake.
Beat cream cheese slightly.
Add eggs, sugar, vanilla and lemon peel.
Beat until light and fluffy.
Yo may add chocolate chips. Pour into crust.
Bake until firm, about 25 minutes.
Spread with topping if you didn't use chocolate chips.

title: hopping john
directions: Cook onions and celery with bacon and thyme until tender, drain. stir in remaining ingredients, bring to a boil. Reduce heat; cover and simmer for 20 minutes or until rice is tender.

title: spaghetti amore
directions: Brown lightly the first 3 ingredients in the shortening.
Add the soups, water and garlic.
Heat all until warm, then add the cheese and spaghetti.
Place in a 3-quart casserole.
Top with the 1/2 cup additional cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until bubbly.
Enjoy.

title: congo squares
directions: Mix
all of ingredients and spread fairly thin in large pan. Cook
to
minutes at 350°.	Cut in squares after cooling.

title: cinnamon crispas
directions: Place flour tacos on a baking sheet.
Cut each into 6 wedges. Bake according to package directions.
Coat wedges with cinnamon and sugar mixture while hot.
Yield:
2 dozen.

title: chicken spaghetti casserole
directions: Boil chicken until done.
Cool and tear apart.
Reserve 1/4 cup broth.
Use remaining broth to cook the spaghetti until done. Saute the onion, green pepper, celery and garlic in the margarine. Drain spaghetti and add sauteed vegetables.
Add soup, 1/4 cup broth, tomatoes, Worcestershire sauce, pepper, salt and hot sauce. Mix well and add chicken.
Bake in lightly greased 13 x 9-inch pan. Top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: small pecan pies
directions: Cream softened cream cheese and 1 cup butter together.
Blend in flour.
Chill one hour.

title: egg custard(makes 2 pies)
directions: Place milk and cream in a boiler and heat.
Do not boil.
Set aside.
Mix eggs, sugar, vanilla and lemon extract.
Pour milk into this mixture.
Pour into 2 pie shells.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes or until middle is done.

title: milk chocolate cake
directions: Mix and bake in bundt pan at 350 for 1 hour or until done.

title: white lightning texas chili
directions: Sort and wash beans; place in a large Dutch oven.
Cover with water 2 inches above beans; let soak 8 hours.
Drain beans, return to pan.
Add 3 cans chicken broth, chopped onion and next 5 ingredients.
Bring to a boil; cover, reduce heat and simmer 2 hours or until beans are tender.
Add remaining can of chicken broth, chicken and next 4 ingredients.
Bring to a boil; cover, reduce heat and simmer for 1 hour, stirring occasionally.
Serve with remaining ingredients.

title: sassy spinach rolls
directions: Cook spinach as directed on box.
Drain spinach; squeeze out liquid.
Combine all ingredients except tortilla.
Mix well. Spread about 2 heaping teaspoons of mix on tortilla.
Be sure to spread it thin and evenly.
Roll and cut into desired lengths. Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: jambalaya
directions: Saute onion, celery, pepper and garlic in peanut oil.
Add canned tomatoes and chicken broth.
Simmer for 1 hour.
Add sausage, ham, parsley, Tabasco, Worcestershire and thyme; simmer 20 minutes more.
Add rice; cook 25 minutes more.
Best in a big kettle.
Enjoy!

title: apple pizza
directions: Combine flour, salt and shortening as for pie crust. Mix egg yolk to milk.
Add egg mixture to flour mixture.
Mix well.
Roll to fit pizza pan, saving 1/2 for crust.

title: ham and cream cheese spread
directions: Combine all ingredients; mix well.
Serve with Ritz or Club crackers.

title: toffee crackers
directions: Line a large cookie sheet with tinfoil.
Break graham crackers into sections and cover the entire surface of the pan.
In a saucepan on the stove, melt butter; add sugar and bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Boil for exactly 2 minutes.
The mixture will look light yellow and fluffy.
Remove from heat and spread evenly over the crackers.
Sprinkle with chopped nuts or coconut (or both).
Bake at 300° for 10 minutes.
Cool until bottom of pan is warm to touch.
Remove from pan.

title: asparagus-carrot casserole
directions: Melt butter.
Slowly stir in milk.
Cook until smooth.
Add salt, pepper and paprika.
Stir in cheese until it is melted. Alternate layers of carrots and asparagus and sauce in a baking dish.
Top with crumbs.
Bake at 350° until bubbly.
(If using fresh vegetables, precook slightly; also if using frozen veggies.)

title: chinese coleslaw
directions: Shred cabbages, chop onions, and mix together.

title: orange waldorf salad
directions: Mix fruits, celery and walnuts.
Combine sour cream, honey and salt.
Fold into fruit mixture.
Spoon onto lettuce, which is placed on serving plate.
Garnish with additional walnuts, if desired.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: pasta salad
directions: Cook spaghetti; rinse in cold water.
Add all ingredients; marinate overnight.
Serve for dinner the next day.
The longer it is in the refrigerator, the better.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Spread dough on a lightly greased cookie sheet; bake 10 minutes at 400° and allow to cool.
Mix cream cheese, mayonnaise, dill weed and onion powder; spread on crust.
Top with any combination of vegetables listed.

title: creamy egg coleslaw
directions: Chop eggs into medium pieces.
Combine eggs, cabbage, onion and pickle relish.
Mix together mayonnaise, mustard, salt and pepper.
Toss dressing mixture with coleslaw mixture.
Put into serving bowl. Sprinkle with paprika.
Makes 8 servings.

title: seasoned oyster crackers
directions: *The kind you mix with milk; but do not mix, use the mix dry.

title: smothered chicken
directions: Line a 13 x 9-inch baking dish with chicken breasts.
Saute all vegetables in butter; then pour over chicken.
Cover with foil and bake 45 to 50 minutes at 350°.	Remove foil and top chicken with Provolone cheese.
Bake 10 minutes more or until cheese melts.

title: tapioca pudding
directions: In saucepan, combine egg yolks, milk, 1/4 cup sugar, tapioca and salt.
Mix well.
Cook over medium heat until mixture comes to a full boil, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Blend in vanilla.
In bowl, beat egg whites until frothy.
Gradually add 2 tablespoons sugar; beat until mixture forms soft peaks.
Fold into tapioca mixture just until well combined.
Spoon into serving dishes and cool.
Makes 4 to 5 servings.

title: green chili rice
directions: Break eggs into blender; turn on slow.
Add oil slowly.
Pour egg and oil mixture over remaining ingredients; mix well. Sprinkle grated cheese on top.
Bake in greased casserole at 350° for 1/2 to 1 hour, depending on depth of dish.

title: pie crust
directions: Mix together, roll out and place in pan.

title: baked fish
directions: Wash fish.
Place crushed croutons on waxed paper.
Mix with Parmesan cheese and paprika.
Roll fish on crumbs and place in well-greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Drizzle oleo over top. Bake at 300° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: million dollar pound cake
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake 80 minutes at 325°.

title: oven-fried chicken
directions: Combine all the dry ingredients and use to coat chicken.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour, or until done.
Serves 8.

title: chuck wagon carrots
directions: In 2-quart saucepan, place carrots; add enough water to cover. Bring to boil; cook over medium heat until carrots are crisply tender (8 to 12 minutes).
Drain.
Return to pan.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cover and cook over medium heat, stirring occasionally, until heated through, 5 to 7 minutes.

title: hominy casserole
directions: Combine soup and seasonings in saucepan.
Heat thoroughly, stirring.
Place hominy in greased casserole dish.
Pour soup mixture over hominy.
Top with bread crumbs and almonds.
Bake at 300° for 15 minutes.
Makes 10 to 12 servings.

title: easy beef tips
directions: Place meat in 2-quart casserole. Do not season. Pour dry soup and mushroom soup on top. Add 7-Up or ginger ale. Bake at 275° for 4 hours. Do not open oven door while cooking. Let stand 30 minutes before serving. Serve with mashed potatoes or over rice.

title: english muffin bread
directions: Combine 3 cups flour, sugar, salt, yeast and baking soda. Heat liquid until very warm, add to dry ingredients and beat well. Stir in rest of the flour.
Divide dough in half.
Grease and cornmeal two loaf pans.
Put dough in pans and sprinkle cornmeal on top.
Cover and let rise for 45 minutes.
Bake 25 minutes at 400°.

title: peggy's boiled custard
directions: Mix all together with hand mixer.
Cook over medium heat to low heat very slowly, until coats a metal spoon.
Do not burn; stir constantly.
Set off heat and let cool.
Refrigerate.
If too thick when serving, add a little milk to thin.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Cook vegetables according to directions on package.
Crush crackers and mix with oleo.

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Prepare whipped topping according to package directions, adding almond extract.
Beat in softened cream cheese.
Fold in drained fruit and marshmallows.
Freeze in 9 x 9-inch pan or you may freeze in individual servings by using paper baking cups. Freeze several hours or overnight.
Makes 9 to 12 servings.

title: brown bread
directions: Stir only enough to mix.
Bake in 350° oven.

title: spicy pot roast
directions: Pat roast dry with paper towel.
Rub with peppers and salt. Heat oil in pot over moderate heat. Brown roast on all sides.

title: porcupine balls
directions: Mix ingredients all together, except tomato juice.
Form into medium size balls.
Bring tomato juice to a boil in a large pan. Add meatballs and boil 5 to 10 minutes.
Reduce heat and simmer 45 minutes.

title: butterfinger pie(kids love it!)
directions: Scoop half of the ice cream into the crust.
Poke holes in the ice cream with a fork and drizzle about half of the chocolate syrup over it.
Repeat with the rest of the ice cream and chocolate syrup.
Top with the crushed candy bar.
Freeze.

title: polly's chicken delight
directions: Boil chicken until tender; then cut into small pieces.

title: saucy meatballs
directions: Mix together the first 3 ingredients.
Bring to a boil and set aside.
Roll the sausage into small meatballs, approximately 36 per pound.
Place on cookie sheet and bake at 350° until brown.
Drain off grease.
Add meatballs to sauce.
Heat and enjoy.
Prepare ahead of time and freeze.

title: crumb cake
directions: Mix together the Crisco, flour, sugar and baking powder like for pie crust.
Save 3/4 cup for top of cake.
Add to reserved pie crust mixture the cinnamon.
Add to the rest well beaten eggs and milk.
Beat well and pour into greased pan.
Add topping to this and bake at 350° until done.

title: jellied applesauce
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water.
Let cool in refrigerator until consistency of egg whites.
Add fruits and celery.
Stir well. Pour in pan or molds.
Refrigerate 4 to 5 hours.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together, except Ritz crackers and margarine. Pour into greased casserole dish. Mix Ritz crackers, crumbled, and melted margarine. Cover vegetable mixture with crumb topping.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: hobo dinner
directions: Form ground beef into four patties.
Slice onion and place slices on beef.
Place peeled and cubed potatoes and carrots on beef.
Sprinkle salt and pepper on ingredients.
Place this on aluminum foil and cook in oven at 350° for approximately 1 hour.

title: key lime pie
directions: Combine condensed milk, egg yolks and lime juice together until well blended.
Pour into pie crust.
Bake at 325° for 20 minutes.
Top with whipped cream or use the egg whites to make a meringue.

title: sauerkraut polish style
directions: Boil meat for 1/2 hour and then add all ingredients. Let cook for 2 to 3 hours.
The longer it cooks, the better it tastes.

title: molded vegetable salad
directions: Mix gelatine, sugar and salt thoroughly in saucepan.
Add 1/2 cup water.
Place over low heat and stir until gelatine is dissolved.
Remove from heat and stir in remaining 3/4 cup water and lemon juice.

title: hello dolly cake
directions: In 9 x 12 1/2-inch pan, spread cracker crumbs, coconut, chips, nut meats and milk.
Sprinkle with 1 stick melted oleo.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.
Cool and cut.

title: peanut brittle
directions: You also need 2 buttered cookie sheets and 1 greased spoon.

title: brunch dish(working family breakfast dish)
directions: Lightly oil the bottom of a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Line the bottom of it with cheese slices (thin).
Brown sausage.
Saute chopped onion and mushrooms until tender (about 5 minutes).
Beat eggs and mix with sausage, onion and mushrooms.
Pour over cheese and lightly sprinkle with seasoned salt and pepper.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.
Serve with toast.
This dish is delicious reheated in the microwave.

title: skillet corn bread
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Mix until smooth.
Pour in greased cast-iron skillet.
Bake at 450° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: vermicelli salad
directions: Break vermicelli in thirds.
Boil until done; drain, but do not rinse.
Sprinkle generously with Accent, lemon juice and salad oil.
Mix and cover tight; refrigerate overnight.
Next day, add vegetables, salt and pepper to taste and enough mayonnaise to mix. Blend and let sit several hours.

title: buttermilk pound cake
directions: Cream together Crisco and sugar.
Add egg yolks, one at a time.
Scald soda in boiling water and add to buttermilk.
Add alternately with flour.
Add vanilla.
whip 5 egg whites and fold into batter.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 25 minutes.

title: chili con carne
directions: Heat Crisco shortening or oil in large saucepan or Dutch oven on medium heat.
Add onion and green pepper.
Saute until softened.
Add meat.
Brown lightly.
Stir in undrained tomatoes, tomato sauce, chili powder, salt, pepper and hot pepper sauce, if desired.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat.
Simmer 45 minutes. Add undrained kidney beans.
Bring to a boil to heat beans.
Makes 8 one-cup servings.
Contains 185 calories, fat 5 g (51 cal or 28% of total calories), sat fat 1 g (7% of total calories), carb 18 g, protein 17 g, chol 35 mg and sodium 505 mg.

title: spanish rice
directions: Brown rice lightly in oil in a 10-inch skillet.
Add onion and green pepper, saute until onion is transparent.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Simmer, covered, over medium heat 20 to 25 minutes.

title: south texas shrimp dip
directions: Cream softened cheese with dressing and mayonnaise.
Stir in all other ingredients.
Happy dipping.
Yields 3 pints.

title: kleeman's apple pie
directions: Stir flour into melted butter, add nutmeg, orange juice and sugar.
Mix together.
Place chopped apples in unbaked pastry shell and pour above mixture over them. Put strips of pastry over top and bake 15 minutes at 450.
Reduce heat to 300 and bake until done, usually 25 to 30 minutes.

title: apple pie
directions: Place apples into pie shell and sprinkle with Sugar Twin, cinnamon and water over apples.
Place butter on top and cover with pie crust.
Bake at 375° until crust is brown and apples are tender.

title: banana nut bread
directions: If using all-purpose flour, use 3 1/2 teaspoons baking powder and 1 teaspoon salt.

title: glazed strawberry pie
directions: Cut half of the berries in halves, reserving 6 small berries with stems left on for garnish.
Put halved berries in pie shell. Crush remaining berries and combine with sugar, water, cornstarch, lemon juice and salt. Cook until thick and clear. Cool.
Pour cooked mixture over berries in pie shell. Chill.
Put a ring of whipped cream around top of pie and decorate with reserved berries.

title: dad's chili
directions: In Dutch oven brown ground beef and onion.
Add flour.
Add remaining ingredients and bring to a boil.
Adjust seasoning to personal taste.

title: glazed orange pork chops
directions: Brown chops on both sides.
Place an orange slice on each chop; sprinkle with cinnamon and nutmeg.
Add broth and sugar. Cover; cook over low heat 35 minutes.

title: sweet yeast rolls
directions: Mix yeast, flour, sugar and salt in bowl.
Put water, milk and melted margarine in another bowl; heat until warm.
Add warm liquid to dry ingredients and beat well.
Add beaten eggs and melted butter.
Beat at high speed for 1 to 2 minutes.
Stir in enough flour (4 to 5 cups).

title: sweet stewed tomatoes
directions: If using fresh tomatoes, peel and dice them.
Heat the butter in a nonstick skillet and saute the onions and garlic, stirring to prevent the garlic from burning.
Transfer the onions and garlic to a heavy bottom pot.
Add the tomatoes and house seasoning, cover the pot and cook over medium-low heat for 35 minutes.
Add the sugar or Splenda and the parsley.
Mix the cornstarch and milk until smooth.
Bring the tomatoes to a boil and pour in the cornstarch/milk mixture, stirring constantly.
Add the Parmesan cheese, if using, and stir well.
The stewed tomatoes are wonderful served over rice.

title: raspberry cream salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water in medium bowl.
Add sugar, stirring to dissolve.
Add raspberries.
Chill until syrupy, stirring once or twice.
Whip the cream or Dream Whip until stiff and fold into thickened jelly.
Fold in marshmallows.
Pour into 4-cup mold. Chill.

title: cold cucumber soup
directions: Combine soup, milk and sour cream in bowl; blend well.
Fold in cucumbers.
Add seasoning to taste.
Chill covered until serving time.
Adjust seasoning if necessary.
Ladle into chilled glass bowls.
Garnish with finely chopped walnuts.
Makes 4 servings.

title: popcorn cake(a snack)
directions: Pop corn and place in large bowl. Melt margarine and marshmallows over low heat (do not boil). Pour over popcorn. Add the M&Ms and peanuts; mix well. Press into a greased angel food cake pan. Refrigerate one hour, unmold and slice with a sharp knife.

title: eulene roberts' rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in water.
Set aside.
In large bowl, beat egg.
Add yeast and water.	Then add half of flour mixed with salt and sugar.	Add melted shortening.	Then rest of flour mixture. Let rise double in bulk.
Make out rolls 2 hours before baking and let rise.
(Cover tightly and this dough can be left in refrigerator for 3 days if you want to use only part of it.)
Bake 15 minutes at 350°.

title: mini cheesecakes
directions: Combine graham cracker crumbs and margarine, stirring well. Line muffin pans with foil baking cups.
Spoon approximately 1 teaspoon crumb mixture into each liner.
Gently press into bottom. Beat cream cheese at high speed of mixer until light and fluffy. Gradually add sugar and mix well.
Add egg and vanilla; beat well. Spoon mixture into liners.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Spoon 1 tablespoon apricot spread on each cheesecake.
Chill thoroughly. Yields 2 dozen.

title: german fruit cake
directions: Grease and flour loaf pan or large angel cake pan.
Cream together butter or margarine and sugar.
Add eggs.
Sift together flour (leave rounded on top of cups), cinnamon, nutmeg and allspice.
Mix soda with buttermilk.
Add to first ingredients alternately with dry ingredients.
Fold in cherry preserves, pineapple preserves, apricot preserves, nuts and vanilla.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 325°.
Let stand for 15 minutes before removing from pan.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Form into any shape on a lined platter. Cover and chill 4 hours.
Serve with assorted veggies or crackers.

title: lemon fluff frosting
directions: Cream butter at medium speed; gradually add sugar, beating until light and fluffy.
Add lemon rind and lemon juice; beat until smooth.
Yield:
2 cups.

title: apricot cake
directions: Grease and flour an 11 x 17-inch pan.
Cream the butter and sugar well, add one egg at a time, beating well between additions. Stir in the flour, baking powder and vanilla.
It will be stiff. Spread evenly in the pan.
Arrange the apricots over the batter, cut side up.
Bake at 325°f. 160°c. gas mark 3 for 25 minutes, then turn up to 350°f. 180°c. gas mark 4 and bake for further 25 minutes or until a nice golden brown.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients.
Press into a 9 x 13 pan.
Bake at 400° for 8 minutes.
Cool.	Beat cream cheese and sugar until creamy.
Fold in whipped topping; spread on cooled crust.
Dissolve gelatin in boiling water; stir in strawberries.
Let mixture stand 10 to 15 minutes until slightly thickened.	Pour on top of cheese mixture; chill.

title: pasta con broccoli(a la "rich and charlie's")
directions: Cook shells and drain.
Cook broccoli and drain.
Saute mushrooms in butter; mix all ingredients together and simmer over low heat.
Add salt, pepper and garlic to taste.
It requires a lot of garlic.
I use liquid garlic, it works better.

title: microwave fudge
directions: Stir in sugar and cocoa in bowl.
Add milk and melted butter. Microwave on High 2 minutes.
Remove from oven.
Add vanilla and nuts.
Pour in oblong dish that has been buttered.
It will be ready to eat in 30 minutes.

title: lil's cheese ball
directions: Blend the cream cheese, margarine, onions and olives.
Roll into ball and refrigerate until firm.
Roll in pecans (after slightly roasting pecans).
Refrigerate until firm and serve.

title: instant hot chocolate
directions: Mix thoroughly and store in tightly covered jar.
To use, put 1/3 cup mixture in mug, fill with hot water and stir.
Use marshmallows, if desired.

title: elegant potato salad
directions: Cool potatoes completely.
Mix sour cream and Miracle Whip together; add all other ingredients together and mix well.
Pour this mixture over cooled potatoes and mix well.
Flavor mixes best if chilled at least 3 to 4 hours before serving.
This salad keeps well in refrigerator.

title: hot sauce
directions: Chop. Bring to a
boil and cook 15 to 20 minutes.
Put through blender.
Seal in sterilized jars.

title: mary lou's oreo ice cream dessert
directions: Crush cookies and mix with melted oleo.
Press into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Freeze for 1 hour.
Let ice cream soften; put over crust and freeze.
Pour fudge topping over ice cream and freeze.
Spread Cool Whip over fudge topping; sprinkle with nuts.
Freeze.
Put Saran Wrap over top when frozen.
Keep frozen until a few minutes before serving.

title: mini sour cream biscuits
directions: Combine butter and sour cream. Blend well. Add flour and mix well. Fill greased mini muffin cups 3/4 full. Bake at 425° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: butternut pound cake
directions: Cream Crisco, sugar and eggs for 1 minute at high speed.
Add 1 cup flour (which as been sifted with self-rising).
Beat for 1 minute, then add the other 2 cups of flour alternately with milk. Add flavoring and pour into tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour. Turn oven to 350° and bake 10 to 20 minutes or until golden brown.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Cream butter and cream cheese.
Add sugar gradually and mix well.
Add eggs, 1 at a time, mixing well after each.
Gradually add flour and then vanilla; mix well.
Start in cold oven.
Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: bratwurst and cabbage skillet
directions: Melt margarine in a large skillet.
Add cabbage, onion, celery seed, salt and pepper.
Stir to coat; then cover and cook over medium heat for about 10 minutes.
Stir occasionally.
Stir in the apples and sugar.
Cook, covered, 5 minutes longer.
Saute the bratwurst until golden brown on all sides.
Stir in 1 cup of cheese and sour cream into cabbage mixture.
Add bratwurst.
Cook, covered, 5 minutes.
Sprinkle with remaining cheese.

title: hot fudge sundae
directions: Stir and cook over low heat in double boiler until thick the first 4 ingredients.
Add vanilla and butter or margarine.
Makes 16 ounces.

title: banana cake
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add bananas.
Alternately beat in dry ingredients and buttermilk.
Add vanilla.
Bake in 3 greased 9-inch layers for 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.
This recipe can be used to make banana bread.

title: enchilada casserole
directions: Brown onions and meat.
Combine tomato paste, water, and chili sauce; add to meat and bring to boil.
Layer 1/4 of meat in greased casserole.
Cover with 3 tortillas, then cheese and olives; alternate layers.
Add chili and beans before top layer of cheese and olives.
Bake 1 hour at 325°.
Freezes well.

title: coconut fingers
directions: Put first 5 ingredients together and boil slowly for 2 minutes. Add Rice Krispies and vanilla.
Cool until you can handle.
Shape into fingers or balls and roll in coconut.

title: lemon meringue pie 1
directions: Mix sugar, cornstarch and flour; add the cold water.
Stir well.
Add the boiling water and cook until clear in double boiler about 8 minutes.
Add the lemon rind and juice and cook again. Then add the egg yolks.
Let it cool and put into a baked pie shell.
Cover with meringue and bake until well browned.
Let it get cold before cutting.

title: sugarless applesauce cookies
directions: Sift together flour, salt, cinnamon, cloves and soda.
Combine margarine, sweetener, vanilla and egg.
Cream until light.
Add flour mixture and applesauce alternately to creamed mixture, mixing well after each addition.
Fold in raisins and oats.
Bake on nonstick baking sheet at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes or until golden brown.
Yields 4 dozen.
Each serving = 3 cookies.
Each serving: 1 bread, 1/2 fat exchange.

title: banana-nut bread
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Cream butter (or oleo) with sugar until light and fluffy.
Add eggs and beat thoroughly.
Mix in buttermilk and lemon juice.
Stir in flour with baking powder, soda and salt and mix well.
Add bananas and nuts; fold in.
Turn the batter into two well-greased mini or one 9 x 5-inch loaf pan; bake at 350°.
Minis about 40 minutes, larger pan about 50 minutes.

title: mocha cheesecake
directions: Crust:
Combine cookie crumbs with sugar and melted butter. Pat crumbs firmly on bottom and sides of buttered square baking dish.
Chill crust.

title: easy apple crisp
directions: Arrange apples in buttered 9-inch pie pan.
Combine brown sugar, flour, oats and cinnamon.
Cut in 1/4 of butter until crumbly.
Press mixture over apples.
Melt remaining butter and pour over top.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: chocolate gravy
