directions: Mix cocoa and sugar.

Have the 1 cup of water boiling in sauce pan. Add cocoa mixture and salt. Gradually stir in flour mixture, (which has been mixed well with the 1/2 cup of water). Stir until thicken. Remove from burner. Stir in vanilla. Serve hot or cold over ice cream.

title: apple crisp
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Grease baking pan, 8 x 8 x 2-inches. Arrange apples in the pan.
Mix remaining ingredients with a fork. Sprinkle over apples.
Bake until tender and topping is golden brown, about 30 minutes.
Serve with cream, whipped cool cream, ice cream or a hard sauce.
Serves 6.

title: lemonade tea
directions: Boil water and brew tea.
Add sugar and lemonade.
Just before serving, add ginger ale.
Serve over crushed ice.

title: angel buns
directions: Dissolve yeast and sugar in medium bowl.
Mix in baking mix and milk until dough forms.
Gently smooth into ball on surface dusted with Bisquick.
Knead 10 times.
Roll 1/2-inch thick.
Cut with 2-inch cutter.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Let rise in warm place 30 minutes.
Heat oven to 425°.
Bake 6 to 8 minutes until golden brown.

title: chocolate mousse
directions: Melt chocolate and butter together over low heat; stir in 2 tablespoons sugar and salt.
Pour into blender container; add tofu, egg yolks and vanilla.
Whirl until smooth; set aside.
Beat egg whites until soft peaks form.
Gradually sprinkle in remaining 4 tablespoons sugar, beating until stiff, glossy peaks form. Gently fold in chocolate mixture until blended.
Spoon into 4 stemmed glasses or custard cups.
Chill 2 hours before serving. Makes 4 servings.

title: graham cracker cookies
directions: Boil the butter and the sugar for 2 minutes, stirring frequently.
Line a cookie sheet with the graham crackers. Sprinkle with the nuts and then pour the butter mixture over. Bake in a 350° oven for 10 minutes.

title: bourbon pound cake
directions: Combine fruit and toss with bourbon. Let stand several hours. Grease and flour a 10-inch tube pan. Sift flour, baking powder and nutmeg onto waxed paper.

title: crispy chocolate-peanut butter bars
directions: In a 2-quart saucepan, combine corn syrup, brown sugar and dash of salt.
Cook and stir until mixture comes to a full boil. Stir in peanut butter.
Remove from heat.
Stir in cereals, chocolate pieces and vanilla.
Press into an ungreased 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Chill 1 hour.
Cut into bars.
Makes 36.

title: chow mein fudge
directions: Melt chips and add noodles, nuts and cream together.
Spoon out onto wax paper.

title: butterscotch pie
directions: Take sugar and butter in heavy skillet and brown.
Add milk until it melts.
Mix eggs and cornstarch with a little milk.
Add vanilla.
Cook until thickened.
Let cool, pour into baked pie shell.
Cover with meringue.

title: green bean bake
directions: Cook beans and drain.
Fold soup into beans, adding salt and pepper.
Place half of mixture in greased casserole.
Sprinkle half of onion rings over it.
Add remaining bean mixture, then top with other half of onion rings.
Heat until bubbling, in slow oven.

title: pepperoni roll up
directions: Separate sliced of pepperoni.
Spread about 1 tablespoon, more or less, cream cheese on each slice.
Roll up by taking one side of round and then the other side of round to form cone shape. Arrange on platter.

title: chocolate fudge cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. In a large bowl, combine cocoa and boiling water; mix well. Add shortening, buttermilk, eggs and vanilla to cocoa mixture; mix well. Let cool. Mix flour, sugar, salt and soda together in bowl. Combine dry ingredients to wet. Mix 1 minute. Bake in a 9 x 13 greased pan for 35 minutes or until done. Let cool in pan, then put icing on cake in pan.

title: carrot cake
directions: Mix dry ingredients first.
Add oil, eggs and vanilla and blend well.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: apple pie
directions: Peel, core and slice apples and sprinkle with lemon juice. Stir together 1/3 cup sugar, 1 tablespoon flour and cinnamon and sprinkle over apples.
Stir together another 1/3 cup sugar and 1 tablespoon flour and sprinkle over bottom of 8-inch pie crust. Arrange apples on top.
Sprinkle last 1/3 cup sugar on apples and dot top with butter slices.
Arrange top crust.
Bake in preheated oven at 400° for 15 minutes.
Reduce oven to 350° and continue baking until apples are tender when pierced with a fork, about 45 minutes.

title: potato casserole
directions: Melt margarine in bottom of 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Add hash browns, onion and soup.
Stir well.
Top with grated cheese and potato chips.
Bake, uncovered, at 375° for 1 hour.

title: ham and potato casserole
directions: Combine cheese and half and half in a medium saucepan.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until cheese melts.
Remove from heat; stir in potato and remaining ingredients.
Spoon into a lightly greased 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Cover and bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until hot and bubbly.
Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: icebox cookies
directions: Place 1 layer of whole graham crackers in large pan.
Melt margarine.
Add sugar, egg and milk; bring to boil and boil 1 minute.
Add nuts, coconut and graham cracker crumbs.
Pour over layer of graham crackers.
Add another layer of whole graham crackers.

title: spinach casserole
directions: Drain thawed spinach.
Mix all ingredients and pour into greased casserole.
Bake one hour at 325°.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving.

title: flank roll-up
directions: Microwave 1 1/2 to 2 minutes mushrooms, oleo and onion.
Mix stuffing with water to moisten.
Combine 4 ounces tomato sauce, Worcestershire, salt and garlic powder.
Mix all mixtures together.
Spread down center of meat.
Roll to enclose mixture in meat.
Secure with toothpicks.
Place seam side down in glass baking dish.
Pour remaining 4 ounces tomato sauce over top. Microwave High 5 minutes, then Medium, 25 to 30 minutes.

title: pineapple cake
directions: Sift sugar (1 1/2 cups), flour, soda and salt.
Add pineapple and egg.
Pour into a greased and floured (9 x 13-inch) pan and bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
For topping, boil sugar, Milnot and oleo for 5 minutes; then add vanilla.
Pour over hot cake.

title: okra fritters
directions: Combine first 9 ingredients; sir in okra.
Pour oil to the depth of 2 inches in a Dutch oven.
Heat to 350° and drop mixture by tablespoonfuls into oil, until golden brown, turning once. Drain on paper towel.
Sprinkle with salt.
Serve immediately.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Beat eggs.
Add sugar, oil and vinegar.
Sift flour and soda together, add flour to mixture, buttermilk, vanilla and cake color.
Bake 35 minutes at 350°.

title: festive cheese ball(party starter)
directions: Combine cheeses, mayonnaise, Worcestershire and onion, garlic and celery salts.
Blend until smooth.
Cover and chill until firm.
Shape cheese mixture into a ball; combine dried beef and parsley, then roll ball in this mixture.
Cover and chill.
Serve with crackers.
Makes a 4-inch ball.

title: apple dapple
directions: Beat Crisco and sugar well and cream.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Sift together, flour, soda and salt.
Add vanilla, apples, pecans and coconut.
Mix well and bake in greased and floured Bundt pan for 1 hour and 20 minutes at 325°.
I started testing at 1 hour because my oven is hotter then normal.

title: oatmeal bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in the cup of milk or water.
Put into large mixing bowl the 2 cups lukewarm water.
Add shortening, syrup and molasses and then add yeast.
Add oatmeal.
Add salt to a cup of bread flour and add with more flour to make dough.
Mix well.
Add more flour as needed to make a stiff dough.
Knead for about 10 minutes.
Let rise until double.
Makes 2 loaves.
Form into loaves and let raise again until double.
Bake at 400° for 30 to 35 minutes.
(Grease pans.)

title: diet salad
directions: Mix dry gelatin and all other ingredients.
Refrigerate.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Mix sugar, milk and chocolate together. Boil 2 minutes, hard. Remove
from
heat
and
add
Marshmallow
Creme and peanut butter.
Mix well and put in greased pan.

title: penuche nut frosting
directions: Bring slowly to rolling boil while stirring.
Boil 1 minute (1
1/2 minutes on a rainy day).
Cool to luke warm and add vanilla.
Beat until thick enough to spread.
Add 1/2 cup nuts.

title: plum cobbler
directions: Melt butter in baking pan.
Combine plums and sugar and place in pan.
Mix flour, sugar and baking powder.
Pour over plums. Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done.

title: summer shepherd's pie
directions: Mix above ingredients (except potatoes) and pour into an ungreased 1-1/2 quart casserole.
Top with prepared instant mashed potatoes.
Bake at 450° until potatoes are brown and pie is bubbly.
This can also be put in the microwave for 8 minutes until pie is bubbly.

title: best baked beans
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Pour into large greased or sprayed glass baking dish.
Place bacon strips on top and bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: new cream
directions: Mix in a food processor or blender or beat with an electric eggbeater until smooth.
Refrigerate in a covered dish.
Add chopped chives and dollop on a baked potato.
Add another teaspoon of lemon juice and use to replace mayonnaise in tuna fish or Waldorf salads.
Add sugar substitute to taste and top waffles or fresh fruit.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs and pumpkin; beat.
Add sifted dry ingredients in thirds, alternately with water.
Stir in nuts.
Bake in 2 well-greased and floured pans in a 350° oven for 35 minutes, or until browned.

title: french dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients in a shaker or blender.
Blend until well mixed.
Store in fridge.
Makes 1 1/3 cups.

title: cranberry pineapple (molded) salad
directions: Blend mayonnaise and sugar in softened cream cheese. Fold in cranberry. Add pineapple and nuts and then the Cool Whip. Freeze in an 8 x 8 baking dish overnight. Serves 10.

title: cranberry sauce
directions: Cook cranberries in microwave on High power for 6 to 6 1/2 minute, until mushy.
Add sugar, raisins and orange juice.
Mix and then cook another 6 minutes on High power.

title: seven-up salad
directions: Combine 7-Up and marshmallows in a heavy pan over a low heat and stir until marshmallows are melted.
Pour over jello.
Have cheese at room temperature.
Add to hot mixture and beat until smooth.
Add pineapple and nuts.
Chill until partially set.
Fold in whipped cream.

title: homemade salsa
directions: Combine all ingredients. Serve with baked tortilla corn chips or fresh vegetables, cut up.

title: blueberry banana pie
directions: Combine cream cheese and sugar.
Beat at high speed until light and fluffy.
Spread in cooled pie shell.
Arrange banana slices on cream cheese layer.
Spread blueberry filling over bananas.
Top with Cool Whip.
Chill.

title: vegetable deer soup
directions: Cook venison until tender.
Put all ingredients into large pot and cook until vegetables are tender.

title: stromboli
directions: Step 1:
Dissolve yeast in warm water for 4 to 5 minutes.

title: cashew salad
directions: Combine all ingredients, stirring well.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix sugar, mayonnaise and vinegar.
Then add rest of ingredients.
Refrigerate.
Add seeds before serving to keep them crispy.

title: garlic bread
directions: Rub entire outside of the bread with the garlic clove.
Slice loaf lengthwise down the middle and cover with butter.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese and parsley.
Sprinkle lightly with paprika. Place slices in hot oven and cook until crisp.
Serve at once.

title: spanish rice
directions: Fry bacon crispy.
Break in small pieces.
Fry hamburger; drain grease off both meats.
Mix all ingredients in large casserole pan.
Cook in oven at 350° until rice is done.
If casserole starts getting dry before rice is done, add tomato juice to it.

title: beef ragout
directions: Combine flour, salt and pepper; coat beef cubes.
Save leftover flour.
In 3 tablespoons oil brown beef in Dutch oven. Add more oil if needed.
Add onions, celery, pepper and garlic. Saute until tender.
Remove from heat and stir in leftover flour until well blended.
Slowly stir in remaining ingredients.
Bring to boil, stirring as needed.
Reduce heat and simmer covered 2 1/2 hours or until meat is done.
Serve with rice, large noodles or buttered potatoes.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: curried fruit
directions: Arrange fruit in dish; save 2 cups juice.
Cook juice, brown sugar, butter, cornstarch, curry powder and salt until thick. Stir constantly.
Pour on top of arranged fruit.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: russian tea
directions: Mix well together and store in jar.
When serving, use 2 teaspoons to a cup of hot water.

title: raw apple muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease 16 muffin tins.
Put 3 mixing bowls on counter.
Mix the apples and sugar in one bowl and set aside.
Put the eggs, oil and vanilla in second bowl and stir to blend well.

title: german chocolate upside-down cake
directions: Grease cake pan. Spread coconut and pecans in bottom of pan. Mix according to directions on box. Spread in pan.

title: pineapple muffins
directions: Mix together.
Spray muffin tin with Pam and fill 2/3 full. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Exchange: 1 bread, 1 fruit, 1 protein, 1 milk.

title: baked chicken and rice
directions: Mix rice, 2 cans soup and 1/2 can water.
Spread in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Add chicken parts on top.
Sprinkle chicken with 1/2 package dried onion soup mix.
Cover tightly with foil.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour.
Uncover and bake 15 minutes more.

title: honey baked black-eyed peas(slow cook)
directions: Cover peas with water and cook on low overnight.
Fry bacon until crisp; discard fat.
Combine all ingredients in cooker. Cook on low for 8 to 9 hours.

title: pennsylvania dutch pepper cabbage(instead of coleslaw)
directions: Combine cabbage, peppers, celery and carrot in medium bowl. Cook sugar, vinegar, water and salt for a few minutes or until it begins to boil.
Pour over cabbage mixture and allow to set for 1 hour.
Mix thoroughly.
Serve chilled.
It will keep for two weeks.

title: dirt cake
directions: You will also need a plastic flowerpot with no holes.

title: anytime snack
directions: Heat in microwave until bubbly.
Serve with Fritos.

title: grilled chicken
directions: Marinate chicken in soy sauce and garlic mixture for several hours in refrigerator.
Remove chicken from marinade and place on grill. Cook slowly for about 30 to 45 minutes. Can place chicken in Ziploc bag to marinate.

title: rice that's right
directions: In a small sized saucepan, cook rice according to package directions.
After rice is done, remove pan from heat.
Pour into a serving bowl.
Pour 1/4 cup of milk over every bowl.
Mix in anywhere from 2 to 4 tablespoons sugar.
Stir.

title: frosted punch
directions: Mix all juices, water and sugar.
Add the ice cream just before serving.

title: walter's beans
directions: Do not cut onion and bell pepper too small or they will cook up.

title: cheese sausage balls
directions: Mix all ingredients together until crumbly.
Form into small balls.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 400° for 10 minutes.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Cook green beans until limp.
Place in buttered flat casserole.
Next, melt butter in skillet; add onion and simmer until transparent.
Add flour; mix together and set to cool.
In top of double boiler, melt cheese in half and half.
Add mushroom pieces and drained chopped water chestnuts.
Add the butter onion mixtures; pour over green beans.
Season with salt and pepper. Sprinkle with almonds.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 35 minutes.

title: pasta and vegetables(lo-cal)
directions: Saute margarine and large onion in pan for about 3 or 4 minutes; add broccoli and carrots and cook 5 more minutes.
Add broth, lemon juice and flour.
Cook until thickens, stirring constantly.
Cook noodles using package directions.
Drain.
Pour sauce mixture over noodles.
May use rice instead of noodles. Yields 6 servings.
Fat grams less than 1.

title: nice spice rice
directions: Brown meat, onion and green pepper.
Add tomato sauce, chili beef soup, water and rice.
Pour mixture into casserole dish and top with enough grated cheese to cover.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: ratatouille
directions: Over medium heat, cook pine nuts, stirring, until brown.
Heat 2 tablespoons oil, add onion and garlic and cook, stirring, until onion is soft.
Stir in remaining 2 tablespoons of oil, thyme, eggplant and green pepper; cook, stirring for 5 minutes.
Add zucchini, spinach, tomatoes and parsley.
Reduce heat and simmer, uncovered, stirring occasionally until tender, 30 minutes.
Season to taste with salt and pepper.
Serve hot or at room temperature. Sprinkle with grated lemon rind.
Makes about 4 cups.

title: brown sugar icebox cookies
directions: Sift flour, baking soda and salt together. Set aside.

title: dried beef cheese ball
directions: Mix together well.
Use 1 or 2 tablespoons of milk to make mixing easier.
Refrigerate.

title: pumpkin muffins
directions: Stir all dry ingredients together and then mix in the rest. Pour into pre-greased muffin tins and bake until golden at 350° (about 25 minutes).

title: marinated carrots
directions: Pare and slice carrots into 1/2-inch pieces.
Cook only until crisp-tender.
Whip the tomato soup, sugar, salad oil, salt, vinegar, pepper and dry mustard for 5 minutes or place in blender. Combine carrots, pepper, onion, and pour dressing over.
Let stand several hours or overnight.

title: gingerbread cookies
directions: Cream shortening, sugar and salt.
Stir in egg, molasses and vinegar; beat well.
Sift dry ingredients; stir into molasses mixture.
Chill for about 3 hours; then roll on lightly floured surface.
Roll to 1/8 inch thickness.
Cut with gingerbread cutter.
Place 1 inch apart on a greased cookie sheet.
Use red hots for faces and buttons.
Bake for about 6 minutes at 375°. Cool slightly and decorate with confectioners icing.
Makes about 5 dozen.

title: honey sourdough bread
directions: Mix all ingredients and pat into bread maker on rapid bread setting.
If no break maker, knead until smooth (adding flour as needed).
Let rise until double.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Line a 13 x 9-inch pan with half Doritos and add bite size chicken pieces.
Top with soup and tomatoes, then cheese. Sprinkle top with remaining Doritos.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chicken salad
directions: Cook chicken (in crock-pot).
Let cool completely.
Dice and chop chicken.
Dice and cut everything else.
Put in large bowl, add salad dressing and mix.
Refrigerate.
Good if made the day before.

title: herbed roast leg of lamb
directions: Crush garlic
with salt and pepper; mix with olive oil. Spread on	lamb.
Sprinkle lamb with marjoram, thyme, rosemary and flour. Pour
wine
and
water
in roasting pan with lamb. Roast at 325° for 2 1/2 hours, basting frequently.

title: easy baked chicken
directions: Mix mayo, Miracle Whip and mustard in a bowl.
In another bowl, mix cheese and Italian bread crumbs.
Brush both sides of breasts with mayo mixture and coat well with bread crumb mixture. Arrange chicken in a lightly greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until golden brown and fork tender.

title: barbecue beans(makes 6 servings; prep time: 8 minutes)
directions: Fold together all ingredients in a large bowl.
Transfer to an aluminum baking pan.
Place in smoker, uncovered, at medium heat (225° to 275°) for about 90 minutes or until heated through.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar lightly.
Add eggs, then sour cream. Mix salt and soda with flour and add slowly to mixture.
Pour in greased tube pan and bake at 325° for about 1 1/2 hours.
Cool in pan about 10 minutes.

title: nancy's pie crust(no rolling of this pie crust)
directions: Whip milk and oil and pour into dry mixture.
Put into pie plate and just pat around to form the crust.

title: beefaroni
directions: Brown meat with onion and bell pepper; drain excess fat.
Cook macaroni and drain thoroughly.
Mix meat, macaroni, grated cheese and tomato sauce.
Bake at 300° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: jerky
directions: Mix meat with spices and roll between waxed paper, about 1/4-inch thick.
Put on cookie sheets.
Mix liquids together and brush on meat.
Place on oven rack and bake for 3 to 4 hours at lowest setting with oven door cracked open.
To brush liquid on top meat, take wax paper off top side.

title: overnight meringues
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat egg whites with salt until they form peaks.
Gradually add sugar by teaspoon, beating constantly, until 2/3 cup is used.
Add flavoring and chocolate morsels.
Drop in small amounts on foil lined cookie sheet.
Put in oven and turn oven off; leave overnight.

title: salted peanut cookies
directions: Sift the flour, soda and baking powder; set aside.
Cream the shortening and brown sugar.
Beat in eggs.
Add oatmeal, flakes and peanuts.
Add flour mixture.
Drop by teaspoons on cookie sheet.
Bake in moderate oven (350°) for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: frosted strawberry squares
directions: Mix together first 4 ingredients.
Place in 9 x 13-inch pan; bake in preheated oven (350°) for 20 minutes, stirring often with fork to prevent scorching.
Reserve 1/2 crumbs for topping.
Cool. In large bowl, beat egg whites stiff.
Beat in sugar a little at a time.
Add strawberries with lemon juice; beat 10 minutes by clock.
Fold in Dream Whip.
Pour over crumbs.
Top with reserved crumbs.
Freeze 8 hours or more.
When frozen, cover with plastic wrap.

title: fried lumpia (eggrolls)
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Wrap in lumpia or eggroll wrapper. Grease steamer and steam for 10 minutes.
Brush with egg whites and sprinkle with sesame seeds.
Cool.
Deep fry till golden brown.

title: rosemary chicken
directions: Use a large cast iron skillet.
Use 2 tablespoons oil.
Rub lemon over chicken.
Salt and pepper to taste (fleshy side down). Brush olive oil all over.
Put rosemary on chicken.
Put another skillet over chicken, then put 5 to 10 pieces in skillet.
Turn chicken every 10 minutes for 35 minutes.
Serve with wild rice and salad.

title: microwave peanut brittle
directions: Mix 1 sugar and 1/2 cup white corn syrup.
Stir together. Microwave at High for 4 minutes.
Add 1 cup roasted peanuts and stir.
Microwave at High for 3 to 5 minutes.
*Note: If raw peanuts are used, add to sugar syrup mixture along with 1/8 teaspoon salt.

title: teriyaki sauce
directions: Combine and marinate for 3 hours or overnight.
For chicken, steaks, shish kabobs or roast.

title: taco salad
directions: Crumble nachos on bottom of pan.
Add fried hamburger (fried with onions, taco sauce, water, salt, salsa and a little cheese). Cook about 30 minutes.
Add cheese, lettuce, sour cream and tomatoes on top after dish has cooked.

title: spaghetti
directions: Saute bell peppers, onions and garlic in butter.
Mix ingredients and cook slowly for 1 hour.
Cook spaghetti until tender and drain.
Add 1 tablespoon butter.

title: mimosa
directions: Mix chilled champagne and orange juice.
Serve immediately.

title: katerina cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, vanilla and sour cream. Sift together flour, soda and baking powder.
Add to creamed mixture.
Freeze for 2 hours, then shape into small balls and roll in powdered sugar.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes at 400°.

title: french silk chocolate pie
directions: Cream butter.
Add sugar, creaming until light.
Blend in melted and cooled chocolate and vanilla.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating for 3 minutes after each addition on medium speed with electric mixer.
Pour into pie shell.
Chill 4 hours.
Garnish with whipped cream and chocolate curls.
Serves 8.

title: pheasant in milk
directions: Dredge pheasant in seasoned flour.
Brown in fat on both sides.
Add approximately 2 inches of milk or cream.
Simmer on top of stove, or bake in oven until done (1 to 1-1/2 hours until it reaches a temperature at least 165 degrees).
If desired, add 1/2 to 3/4 Cup carbonated lemon-lime drink when you add the milk.

title: baked corn
directions: Beat eggs slightly; add sugar, salt and pepper.
Mix thoroughly.
Add corn and butter.
Pour mixture into a buttered baking dish and cover top with buttered crumbs.
Set in a pan of water.
Bake 45 minutes in a moderate oven.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Break chocolate into small pieces.
Add to milk in saucepan. Cook over low heat, stirring constantly until mixture is smooth. Add sugar and salt and stir until sugar is dissolved and mixture boils.
Cook slowly without stirring, until a small quantity dropped into cold water forms a soft ball (236°).
Remove from heat.
Add vanilla without stirring.
Cool to lukewarm (110°). Add peanut butter and beat until fairly thick.
Pour at once into greased pan.
Cool and cut into squares.
Makes about
1 1/4 pounds.

title: chilled salmon pasta
directions: Cook spaghetti according to package directions; drain.
Drain salmon, reserving 1 teaspoon liquid.
Break into small chunks. Combine reserved liquid with oil, vinegar, basil, salt and pepper. Pour over warm spaghetti.
Cool.
Toss with salmon, tomato, celery, cucumber, green onions and parsley, then chill thoroughly. Garnish with tomato wedges and sprinkle with cheese before serving.
Makes 6 servings.

title: steak pizziola
directions: Saute the onion and red pepper, cut up, in a little oil.
Add the tomatoes, sauce, salt, pepper and parsley.
Add the steaks. Cover; simmer for 45 minutes.
Add the mushrooms; simmer 5 more minutes.

title: fiesta onion dip
directions: Combine the ingredients and chill well. Serve with corn chips.

title: apple nut pudding
directions: Beat eggs until fluffy.
Add sugar gradually, beating in each addition thoroughly.
Sift together flour, salt, baking powder, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Stir into egg mixture.
Add the almond extract, chopped walnuts and diced apples.
Mix thoroughly.
Pour the batter into a well-greased glass 8-inch square baking dish. Bake at 325° for about 50 minutes.
Serve with whipped cream.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Brown hamburger, onions and bell pepper together.
Drain.
Add noodles, soups and 3/4 cup cheese; mix together.
Put in casserole dish.
Add remaining cheese on top. Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: french crepes (pancakes)
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Warm crepe pan or 10-inch iron skillet. Pour thin layer of batter to cover all of skillet.
Cook until golden on both sides.

title: zesty potato salad
directions: Cook the potatoes until tender, but firm.
Drain and cube. Place
in a large bowl; add artichokes, chilies, pimentos, peppers, onion, basil and salt.
Combine remaining ingredients in a jar with a tight fitting lid.
Shake well.
Pour over salad and toss well.
Chill at least one hour before serving.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: sour cream apple pie
directions: Peel and cut apples into thick slices. Arrange slices in overlapping rows in pastry lined pie pan. Sprinkle with lemon juice.
In a bowl, mix sugar, flour, salt, cinnamon and nutmeg. Cut in butter until crumbly.
Spoon over apples.
Spread sour cream over top.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes or until apples are tender.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Cream sugar, peanut butter and cream cheese together.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Pour into pie shell.
Let chill one hour.

title: creamy mac and cheese
directions: Cook and drain macaroni.
Cool by mixing in milk and butter first.
Then add sour cream and cheese, then egg.
Save some cheese for topping.
Put in casserole dish, top with cheese and bake at 425 degrees until bubbly.

title: stuffed cabbage soup
directions: Saute beef in oil in 6-quart pot over medium heat.
Add cabbage and onion, cooked covered about 4 minutes, stirring once.
Add tomatoes, broth, water, sugar, lemon juice and salt.
Bring to boiling; add rice.
Reduce rice to medium low.
Simmer covered 45 minutes or until rice is tender.
Yields 8 servings.

title: coconut-pecan frosting
directions: Blend milk, sugar, butter and egg in saucepan.
Place over medium heat.
Cook and stir until mixture comes to a full boil. Boil and stir 2 minutes.
Cool slightly.
Add coconut, pecans and vanilla.
Cool until spreading consistency, stirring occasionally.

title: lemonade pie
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into 2 graham cracker crusts. Chill.

title: shrimp jambalaya
directions: Saute onion, garlic, green pepper and celery in lard (moderate heat) until onion is golden.
Add parsley, ham, thyme and bay leaves.
Cook 5 minutes, stirring often.
Add Tabasco, tomatoes and juice, tomato sauce, 2 cups water and 2 teaspoons salt.
Simmer 5 minutes.
Add rice.
Reduce heat to simmer and cook, covered, 30 minutes.
Add shrimp and simmer, covered, 10 to 15 minutes longer until rice is tender and all liquid is absorbed.
Season to taste with salt and Tabasco sauce.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Combine in order given and mix thoroughly.
Pour into unbaked pie crust.
Bake 15 minutes at 450°, then 40 minutes at 325° or until firm.

title: easy berry pie
directions: Place 2 cups berries in bottom of pie crust.
Bring to a boil 2 cups berries, flour (or cornstarch) and sugar.
Add lemon juice and pour over whole berries in pie crust.
Cool.
Top with the whipped cream.

title: heavenly kisses
directions: Cream together butter and powdered sugar.
Gradually add flour, vanilla and nuts.
Shape into small balls.
Bake at 325° for 25 minutes.
Cool and roll in powdered sugar.

title: nut bread
directions: Pour boiling water over sugar and soda and let cool.
Then add shortening, flour, baking powder, salt and egg yolks.
Fold in whites and nuts.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: mother's persimmon pudding
directions: Combine all dry ingredients, persimmon pulp and eggs.
Mix with electric mixer; stir in melted butter and add vanilla.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for about 35 to 40 minutes.
This is an oldie but goodie.

title: sauteed salmon fillets
directions: Mix all ingredients except salmon.
Pour mixture over salmon in shallow glass pan.
Marinate 1 hour.
Preheat nonstick skillet; remove fillets from marinade and saute 5 minutes on each side.
Remove to warm platter.
Bring remaining marinade to a boil; pour over fillets and serve.
Serves 4.

title: corn and oysters
directions: Beat egg and add milk.
Mix all ingredients together; mix lightly.
Pour into buttered pan or baking dish.
Cover with grated cheese and dabs of butter.
Bake in medium 350° oven until firm, about 25 minutes.

title: easy italian linguini
directions: Mix all ingredients except pasta together in large bowl. (Does not need to be cooked.)
Cook pasta by directions; drain and while hot, toss thoroughly in sauce.

title: grandmother souder's chow chow
directions: Grind tomatoes and cabbage; add the onion (if you preferred) and grind also.
Put in a large pan, cook until tender.
Put spices in a cloth when cool.
Add to tomatoes and bring to a boil. Put in hot jars and seal.

title: yeast rolls
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Knead as though making biscuits. Roll to 1/2-inch thick.
Cut with biscuit cutter and place on greased baking sheet.
Dot with butter and let stand 30 minutes. Bake at 400° until brown.

title: hot fudge pudding cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°. In a medium bowl, combine 3/4 cup granulated sugar, flour, 3 tablespoons cocoa, baking powder and salt.
Blend in butter, milk and vanilla. Beat until smooth.
Pour batter into 8 or 9-inch square baking pan.

title: iced tea
directions: This makes 2 quarts.

title: chow-chow
directions: Chop first 5 ingredients.
Sprinkle with salt and let stand overnight.
Drain.
Tie pickling spices, celery seed and cinnamon in a thin cloth.
Mix brown sugar with enough vinegar to cover cabbage mixture.
Cook only until tender.
Pack into sterilized jars and seal.
Process for 10 minutes at simmering temperature (about 200°).
Makes 12 to 14 pints.

title: blackberry jam cake
directions: Soak raisins for several hours or overnight in pineapple and juice.
Cream butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each one.
Stir in jam.
Sift together dry ingredients.
Add alternately to creamed mixture with buttermilk.
Stir in pineapple, raisins and pecans.
Pour batter into wax paper-lined pans (13 x 9 x 2-inch).
Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes.
Dust with sifted confectioners sugar to serve.

title: beef nacho casserole
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Brown meat; drain.
Stir in salsa, corn, dressing (mayonnaise) and chili powder.
Layer 1/2 each of meat mixture, chips and cheese in a 2-quart casserole.
Repeat layers. Bake 20 minutes or until thoroughly heated.
Top with shredded lettuce and chopped tomatoes if desired.
Makes 6 servings.

title: pumpkin spice cake
directions: Cream first 3 ingredients together.
Blend in eggs and pumpkin.
Add dry ingredients alternately with milk.
Blend in nuts and lemon flavor.
Bake in 350° oven about 30 minutes in three 8-inch greased and floured cake pans.
Frost cooled layers with fluffy white frosting.

title: chet atkins easy pickin' chicken pie
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Grease a shallow 2-quart baking dish. Spread chicken and vegetables evenly in dish.
Stir together soup, broth and pepper in small mixing bowl; pour evenly over chicken mixture.
Combine flour, milk and butter in separate bowl; stir until smooth.
Pour flour mixture over ingredients in baking dish. Bake for 45 to 50 minutes or until golden brown.

title: pasta primavera
directions: Snap off tough ends of asparagus and cut diagonally into 1 1/2-inch pieces.
Place asparagus and broccoli in a vegetable steamer over boiling water; cover and steam 6 to 8 minutes or until vegetables are crisp-tender.
Remove from heat; set aside.

title: miracle whip cake
directions: Sift dry items 3 times.
Combine water and salad dressing. Add vanilla; beat until smooth.
Bake in layers or in a flat pan at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: layered fiesta dip
directions: Spread bean dip in shallow baking dish.
Spread avocado dip over bean dip.
Sprinkle with olives, tomatoes, green chilies and green onions.
Dot with sour cream.
Top with cheese.
Chill until serving time.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: manly kraut slaw
directions: Mix all ingredients.
This slaw is best made 2 days in advance and keep in "frig" until serving.
Good with choice of weiners, pork sausage, brown beans and other hearty combinations.
Women like it too!

title: fish chowder
directions: Fry bacon in large (stock) pot until crisp; drain and crumble. In the reserved bacon grease, saute the chopped onion, potatoes and carrots until tender, about 6 minutes.
Move the veggies over to one side.
Add the flounder and water; bring to a boil, then reduce heat.
Cover; simmer for 15 minutes, or until fish flakes with a fork.
Turn over and break up fish.

title: hot chocolate mix
directions: Mix ingredients together and store in a covered container. Use 1/3 cup of mix with boiling water for each cup of hot chocolate.

title: zucchini parmesan
directions: Cut zucchini into 1/4-inch slices.
Saute onions in oil.
Add zucchini; cover and cook over low heat 10 to 15 minutes, or until tender, occasionally turning with spoon.
Remove zucchini mixture from heat; mix in about 1/2 of grated cheese.
Pour in a mixture of tomato sauce, salt, garlic and pepper.
Blend thoroughly.
Put into 2-quart casserole.
Sprinkle with remaining cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: quick cottage cheese salad
directions: Mix together orange Jell-O and cottage cheese.
Set aside. Prepare Dream Whip and mix all 4 ingredients together.
Chill in refrigerator.
Can be served within 20 minutes after being mixed.

title: homemade crackers
directions: In a large bowl, mix flour and salt.
Using pie blender, cut in oleo and cottage cheese until mixture forms a dough.
Divide into 4 parts and cover with wax paper.
Refrigerate at least 1 hour.
Take 1/4 of the dough and roll it out on floured board to 1/8-inch thick.
Using a pizza cutter, cut dough into 2-inch squares and place on a greased baking sheet and pierce each cracker with a fork.
Bake at 450° for 10 to 15 minutes.
Be careful not to let them burn.

title: mayonnaise muffins
directions: Mix ingredients
together until batter is smooth.
Drop by spoon onto
greased
bread
pan, leaving space between each muffin.
Bake at
until
golden brown.
Makes about six. (If batter seems too stiff, add just a little more milk.)

title: barbecue meat balls
directions: Mix the first 7 ingredients well and form into small meat balls.
Put in frypan and brown.
Put in slow cooker.
Add the chili sauce and grape jelly.
Simmer for 45 minutes, or until serving (the longer, the better).
Serve with toothpicks and eat.

title: ratatouille
directions: Cut eggplant into 1/2-inch cubes (about 5 cups).
Cook and stir onion and garlic in oil in 12-inch skillet until onion is tender.
Add eggplant and remaining ingredients.
Heat to boiling; reduce heat.
Cover and simmer, stirring occasionally, until vegetables are crisp-tender, about 10 minutes.
Makes 8 servings.

title: pie crust
directions: Combine and press in a 9-inch pie pan.
Bake at 300° for 20 minutes.
Fill with any kind of cream filling.
May put nuts on top of crust before filling.

title: hungarian goulash
directions: In large skillet, heat oil.
Add beef, onion and garlic; cook and stir until meat is browned and onion is tender.
Stir all other ingredients and 1 1/2 cups water; cover and simmer for 2 to 2 1/2 hours.
Blend flour and 1/4 cup water; gradually add to goulash.
Heat to boiling, stirring constantly.
Serve over noodles.

title: easy broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli spears and drain.
Chop spears and place in casserole dish.
Mix together the soups and milk and pour over the broccoli.
Mix and top with layer of stuffing mix.
Bake covered at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: easy blueberry cobbler
directions: Heat oven to 375°
(350° if glass pan).
Scatter berries on bottom of 10 x
6 x 1 1/2-inch baking pan.
Sprinkle with lemon juice.
In a large bowl, sift together flour, sugar and salt.
Add egg and vanilla.
Mix with fork until crumbly.
Sprinkle over berries.
Drizzle with margarine.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes.
Keeps well, covered, in refrigerator.
Can be frozen and makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into a greased casserole dish.
Place, uncovered, in a 350° oven and cook until set and golden brown, approximately 40 to 45 minutes.

title: double stuffed potatoes
directions: Bake potatoes until done and the skin is crispy.
Cut in half; scoop out potatoes and mix with sour cream, cheese, onions, garlic salt and cinnamon.
Return to potato skins and bake at 350° for about 10 minutes or until just lightly crisp on top.

title: cream of garlic soup
directions: Blend garlic in processor to coarse paste, stopping occasionally to scrape down sides of bowl.
Heat oil in heavy large saucepan over low heat. Add garlic paste and cook until just beginning to color, stirring frequently, about 12 minutes. Add stock and wine; bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer 30 minutes. Add milk, cream and potato; simmer 30 minutes.
Puree soup in blender in batches. Return to saucepan and bring to simmer. Season to taste with salt and pepper.
(Can be prepared 1 day ahead.
Cover and refrigerate. Bring to simmer before continuing.) If soup is very thin, simmer until thickened to desired consistency.
Ladle into bowls and serve.
Makes 6 servings.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Trim fat from heat and cut in 1/2-inch strips.
Heat butter in large frying pan.
Add meat, onion and mushrooms to butter.
Saute over high heat until meat is nicely browned.
Add seasonings.
Add cream of mushroom soup.
Cook over low heat for 15 minutes.
Fold in sour cream.
Simmer 5 minutes.
Do not boil.
Serve with cooked egg noodles or rice.

title: artichoke appetizer
directions: Cut up artichoke hearts and drain.
Mix in a cup of mayo and a cup of Parmesan cheese.
Sprinkle a dash of Tabasco and mix.
Put into dish and bake at 350° until brown and bubbly, approximately 20 to 25 minutes.

title: welcome to our home aroma(not for consumption)
directions: Simmer in open tea kettle or pan.
Add water in small measures as needed.
A simmering tea kettle on the stove spells "Welcome to our Home!"

title: barbecue coon
directions: Need good treeing dog to catch coon.
Clean and cut up meat. Pressure cook for 45 minutes at 10 pounds or until meat falls off bone.
Debone.
Place meat in casserole dish and cover with barbecue sauce.
Bake in slow oven (200° to 250°) until meat is hot.
Enjoy!

title: baked round steak
directions: Place meat on foil covered cookie sheet.
Place meat on foil. Dust lightly with Lawry's and meat tenderizer.
Spread on onion soup mix.
Add drained mushrooms and spread evenly over meat.
Dot with margarine.
Cover with more foil and seal tightly.
Bake at 325° for 2 hours.

title: chicken and pasta
directions: Cook chicken in water to cover with bay leaves and garlic until tender, add salt and continue cooking until ready to remove meat from bones, cut chicken into bite size.
Heat margarine, add onions and celery and cook until tender.
Stir in flour, then add 2 cups chicken broth.
Cook until slightly thickened.
Mix all ingredients with 1/2 of the cheese, reserving peas until last to prevent mashing.
Sprinkle remaining cheese on top.
Bake 20 minutes in large shallow pan at 350° until cheese is melted. Sprinkle with paprika.

title: taco pie ii
directions: Brown ground beef with taco seasoning mix.
Line a 9 x 9-inch baking dish with the rolls.
Pour 1/2 cup Fritos on the dough. Add meat mixture.
Spread sour cream over meat.
Sprinkle cheese over sour cream.
Sprinkle on remaining Fritos.
Sprinkle the water over all.

title: vegetable soup
directions: Cut all vegetables into bite sized pieces.
Quantity of each vegetable depends on what's available and how much you want to make.
In large pot, put longest to cook veggies with water to cover and bring to simmer for 5 to 10 minutes.
Add next longer to cook veggies and whatever water needed to cover, and simmer another 10 minutes.
Add remaining vegetables, salt, pepper and additional water.
Simmer until as you like it.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix all ingredients and serve with your favorite fresh vegetables.
Dip can be made beforehand, as flavor improves with a little age.
This can also be served with baked potatoes.

title: plain pizza crust
directions: Mix together.
Allow to rise.
Divide the dough into 2 pieces; roll each piece to fit a greased 12-inch pizza pan.
Place dough on pizza pan and pinch the dough around the edges to form a small rim.
Spread with favorite sauce, cheese and your favorite toppings.
Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes or until done.
Makes two 12-inch pizzas.

title: pecan pie
directions: Melt margarine and set aside to cool.
Mix together brown sugar and flour.
Add milk.
Beat eggs and add to mixture.
Stir in vinegar and vanilla.
Add pecans and margarine.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 300° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: cole slaw
directions: Wash and shred cabbage.
Cut bacon in small pieces and brown. Add sugar, lemon juice, cream and mayonnaise.
Mix thoroughly through cabbage.
Serve on lettuce leaves and garnish with mayonnaise and paprika.

title: my favorite bran muffins
directions: Stir Nabisco Bran into the boiling water and cool.
Cream sugar and margarine.
Add the eggs and beat well.
Add the cooled bran mixture.
Add the buttermilk.
Stir the salt and soda into the flour and sift into the liquid ingredients.
Fold in the All-Bran and raisins.

Batter may be stored in the refrigerator for several weeks and baked as needed, or they may all be baked in greased muffin tins at 375° for 25 minutes for large muffins and 15 to 20 minutes for smaller ones.
These freeze well.
The recipe may be doubled if you have a very large mixing bowl.

title: sugarless apple pie
directions: Heat apple juice with cornstarch in saucepan, stirring constantly.
Stir in cinnamon and salt.
Pour over apples in a bowl mixing carefully.
Spoon into pie crust and dot with butter. Top with crust.
Bake at 400° approximately 30 minutes.
Cut slits in top crust.
Makes 2 (9-inch) pies.

title: rachel's pizza casserole
directions: Boil noodles until tender then drain.
Combine all ingredients.
Refrigerate 4 hours.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: banana spice cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients into a large bowl.
Add shortening, buttermilk and bananas; mix until flour is dampened.
Beat at low speed for 2 minutes.
Add eggs and beat 1 minute.
Turn into greased and floured pans.
Bake at 350° in 2 pans (8 or 9-inch) or a 9 x 13-inch pan for 30 to 35 minutes.
Cool and ice with Quick Caramel Frosting.

title: grandma brian's oatmeal pie
directions: Mix ingredients in order.
Pour into unbaked pie crust.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Combine raisins and nuts in a bowl.
Sift flour, salt, baking soda, cinnamon and cloves together over fruit-nut mixture and toss together.
Beat shortening, sugar and egg together until fluffy. Add this mixture with applesauce; beat or blend well.
Pour or spoon into a greased loaf pan.
Heat oven to 350°.
Bake 1 hour and 15 minutes or until a toothpick stuck in the center comes out clean.
Cool and turn out pan.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix well.
Bake at 350°.
Makes about 5 dozen drop cookies.

title: barbecue brisket
directions: Sprinkle brisket with salt, pepper, onion salt and garlic salt.
In large Pyrex dish, put Worcestershire sauce and liquid smoke.
Lay meat side down in mixture, cover with foil and marinate overnight.
Cook in slow oven at 275° for 5 hours. Uncover and add your favorite prepared barbecue sauce; spread evenly over top of brisket.
Cook 1 hour more, uncovered.
Remove from oven and cool before slicing.
To thicken sauce, mix flour in water, add to sauce and cook until slightly thick.

title: salmon spread
directions: Drain salmon; remove skin and bones.
Flake salmon with a fork.
Combine next 7 ingredients; mix well and gently stir in salmon.
Spoon mixture into a well-oiled 5-cup mold.
Chill several hours or overnight.
Unmold on serving platter and gently pat chopped nuts over surface; garnish with parsley sprigs.
Serve with assorted crackers.
Makes 15 servings.

title: squash casserole
directions: Melt oleo.
Mix with dressing mix.
Grease 9 x 13-inch pan. Spread dressing in bottom of pan, reserving some for top.
Mix remaining ingredients and pour over dressing.
Top with reserved dressing.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.

title: crisp vegetables with clam dip
directions: Beat cream cheese in medium bowl until fluffy.
Beat in mayonnaise, sour cream, chives and parsley.
Stir in clams. Serve with assorted vegetables.
Makes 1 1/2 cups.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Cut up broccoli in small pieces.
Crumble bacon.
Mix broccoli, bacon and onion.
Make dressing with remaining ingredients.
Pour over vegetables just before serving.

title: crunchy nut crust
directions: Heat oven to 450°.
Place ingredients in bowl.
Stir until nuts are thoroughly coated.
Press mixture firmly and evenly against bottom and sides of buttered 9-inch pie pan.
Bake 6-8 min.
Cool. Fill with a chiffon type pie filling and chill.
Or, chill empty shell and serve filled with your favorite ice cream.

title: texas tamale casserole
directions: While warming chili, remove husks and discard liquid from tamales.
Place a layer of tamales on bottom of casserole dish. Add a layer of onions, cheese and 1/3 of chili.
Repeat layers and cover with corn chips and remainder of chili.
Bake at 300° for 15 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: skillet crab
directions: Combine soup and milk in skillet; bring to boiling point, stirring frequently.
Add crab meat and peas; simmer 5 minutes. Garnish with paprika.
Serve over rice.

title: peas pagoda
directions: Mix peas and liquid, chicken stock, ginger, sugar, oil, sliced water chestnuts and mushrooms.
Cover.
Heat through.
Blend cornstarch with soy sauce.
Stir into mushroom mixture.
Cook until thickened.
Serve hot.
Yield:
4 to 5 servings.

title: banana crush punch
directions: Blend sugar and water.
Cook to syrup.
Remove from heat.
Add orange juice and bananas; cool.
Freeze.
Large containers to single ice cube trays can be used to freeze mixture in.
Place all cubes in large bowl.
Pour over ginger ale.

title: maryland crab cakes
directions: Melt butter; cook onion until yellow.
Mix in bread crumbs. Add crab that you have picked of extra shells.
Add eggs, slightly beaten.
Add parsley, mustard, Worcestershire sauce, salt and ginger.
Mix together, using enough mayonnaise to hold ingredients in patties.
Dust with crumbs.
Refrigerate patties for 30 minutes. Fry.

title: anise cookies (grandmother kimbrel)
directions: Beat eggs and sugar 1 hour until sugar is dissolved.
Use mixer now days.
Add flour and anise seed.
Drop by teaspoon on buttered pans far enough apart so as not to run together.
Let stand overnight.
Keep in cold place until you are ready to bake.

title: grilled vegetables
directions: Amounts vary depending on how many are being served.
Slice zucchini or potatoes about 1/4-inch thick.
Brush with oil. Sprinkle with seasoned salt.
Grill.

title: pork and sauerkraut
directions: Put all ingredients into a Dutch oven or large pot.
Bring to a boil.
Simmer for 1 1/2 to 2 hours or even longer.

title: applesauce muffins
directions: Cream margarine, sugar, eggs and 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Sift together flour and spices.
Add to creamed mixture.
Mix 2 teaspoons vanilla into can of applesauce.
Add baking soda and stir with a wooden spoon.
Add to batter.
Stir until well mixed. Add raisins and nuts.
Stir well as batter is very thick and stiff.

title: "funky" chicken
directions: Sprinkle chicken lightly with garlic powder.
Cook, covered, for 45 minutes at 350°.
Uncover and drain liquid.
Cover with sauce.
Bake, uncovered, until chicken is very tender, 1 1/2 hours, at lowered temperature of 325°.

title: nonie's salad dressing
directions: Beat altogether; will thicken.
Store in fridge.

title: fragrance of christmas
directions: Simmer in an open pan or potpourri pot during the holidays. Makes a wonderful holiday aroma.

title: rice artichoke salad
directions: Cook rice according to directions, but leave out margarine. Drain artichokes and chop, set aside the marinade.
Slice green onions and slice stuffed olives.

title: sausage cheese balls
directions: Mix biscuit mix and shredded cheese.
Work sausage into mixture with hands.
Form into small balls.
Cover and refrigerate until ready to serve.
To bake, place on cookie sheet in 400° oven for 10 minutes.

title: classic caramel apples
directions: 1) Generously butter 6 paper muffin cups, (2 1/2-inch In diameter).
Insert wooded sticks into stem end of each thoroughly dried apple.

title: stuffed boulangers(eggplant)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Boil boulangers (eggplant) until tender. Season meat to taste, adding all ingredients.
Divide boulangers in half; remove pulp and crush finely.
Do not destroy outer skin. Cook meat and add pulp in fat.
Return meat filling to skins, reshaping neatly.
Sprinkle with dried crumbs.
Place on greased baking sheet and bake until brown.

title: refrigerator pickles
directions: You will need a 1-gallon jug.
Fill jug with sliced cucumbers, green pepper and sliced onions.
Layer cucumbers, onions and pepper until jug is full.
Heat sugar, vinegar and other ingredients. Pour over cucumber mixture.
Seal and put in refrigerator.
You can add more cucumbers, pepper and onions along so the jug stays full.

title: pistachio pudding dessert
directions: Mix margarine, flour and pecans for a crust.
Spread in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 325° for 10 to 15 minutes.
Cool.

title: peach crisp
directions: Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: blueberry coffee cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add egg yolks.
Add milk alternately with dry ingredients.
Blend in vanilla.
Add berries.
Beat egg whites and fold in.

title: tracy's manicotti
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix cheeses and spices together in mixing bowl.
Stuff uncooked manicotti shells with the cheese filling.
Grease 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Place stuffed manicotti shells in dish.
Cover with spaghetti sauce.
Cover pan completely with aluminum foil.
Bake for 40 minutes.

title: chicken noodle casserole
directions: Combine ingredients in large bowl. Mix well. Pour into buttered dish. Crush 1 tube of Ritz crackers. Sprinkle over noodle mixture. Melt 1 stick margarine and drizzle over crackers. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: pea and almond salad
directions: If using fresh peas, shell and blanch for 3 to 5 minutes or until tender yet firm.
Drain and cool.
Combine peas, almonds and green onions.
Combine mayonnaise and curry; pour over peas and almonds.
Toss well.

title: corny dogs
directions: In skillet, brown wieners in butter.
Remove from skillet. Add together soup and water.
Heat in skillet.
While heating soup and water, toast hot dog buns.
Place wieners on buns and spoon chili soup mixture over them.
Add onions, pickles, cheese, mustard and catsup if desired.

title: texas red chili
directions: Heat oil and brown beef cubes.
Add onion, bell pepper and garlic.
Fry them with beef for about 5 minutes.
Add all the remaining ingredients except beans and simmer for 1 1/2 hours or until the meat is tender.
Add beans and simmer 30 minutes longer.

title: peanut reese's
directions: Melt margarine and peanut butter together.
Remove from heat and add confectioners sugar.
Spread in a 13 x 9-inch buttered dish.
Place Hershey bars on top.
Place in a moderate oven just until bars start to melt.
Spread chocolate.
Cool and cut into bars.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Brown hamburger, onion and oregano.
Add sauce.
Cook macaroni; drain.
Add milk and egg.
Layer meat mixture, macaroni mixture and cheese in a 9 x 13-inch dish.
Bake at 350° to 375° until cheese melts or until bubbly, about 30 to 45 minutes.

title: seafood salad
directions: Trim crusts from bread.
Butter each slice and cut into strips.
Toss bread, green onions and chopped, hard-boiled eggs together and refrigerate overnight.

title: chinese chicken salad
directions: Mix ingredients; place in 9 x 13-inch pan or casserole.

title: pineapple jello mold cake(a light dessert after a heavy meal)
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Chill until slightly firm. Whip jello until foamy.
Whip evaporated milk separately just until it foams.
Fold whipped evaporated milk into jello.
Drain pineapple.
Fold into jello.
Grease Bundt pan with thin layer of Crisco.
Pour jello mixture into Bundt pan and chill.
When serving, dip pan in warm water a few seconds, then invert onto platter.

title: corned beef sandwich spread
directions: Place in a bowl.
Break corned beef apart and blend other ingredients.
Great with rye crackers.

title: chocolate delight
directions: Mix ingredients and press into 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake for 15 minutes at 350°. Cool.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Form into ball and roll in chopped nuts. Chill and serve.

title: hot chocolate mix
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Place 3 heaping tablespoonfuls of mix in cup.
Pour in boiling water.
Stir well.

title: autumn soup
directions: In a large saucepan, cook and stir meat until brown.
Drain off fat.
Cook and stir onion with meat for 5 minutes.
Stir in remaining ingredients; heat to boiling.
Cover; simmer for 20 minutes.
Serve.

title: mini bagel pizzas
directions: Half bagels.
Grate cheese.
Heat tomato sauce and all spices. Line cookie sheet with bagel halves, insides face up.
Spread sauce over bagel.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Place 4 slices of pepperoni on each bagel and sprinkle with more cheese.
Pop in the oven at 400° until cheese is well melted.
Vary toppings as you like.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve sugar in water.
Add jello, pineapple, nuts and cranberries.
Place in refrigerator overnight or until congealed.

title: parmesan corn on the cob
directions: In microwave-safe dish, place corn that has been silked and husked.
Cover with water and cook for 10-13 minutes turning once. In another bowl, combine butter, parmesan cheese, and Italian seasoning.
Drain corn and brush with butter mixture.
Sprinkle salt to taste.

title: no calorie gelatin
directions: Bring 6 ounces of the drink to a boil.
Pour in unflavored gelatine.
Dissolve.
Stir in remainder of drink.
Chill.
Makes 2 servings.

title: cucumber and onion salad
directions: Combine salt, celery seed, sugar and vinegar.
In large airtight bowl, slice cucumbers and onions.
Pour dressing mixture over cucumber mixture.
Let marinate 24 to 48 hours in fridge. When ready to serve, dice tomatoes and pour into bowl; toss. Delicious side dish!!

title: easy deep dish pizza
directions: Mix until soft dough forms.
Knead on floured surface 5 minutes.
Roll into rectangle, 5 x 10-inch.
Punch edge.
Put in jelly roll pan or cookie sheet.

title: cookie dough cheesecake
directions: Cut one roll of dough into slices and press firmly onto bottom of a 13 x 9 x 2-inch buttered pan until completely covered. Mix eggs, sugar, cream cheese and vanilla; pour over dough.
Cut remaining roll into 24 slices and place on top of filling.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Cool; cut into squares.

title: chocolate crinkles
directions: Mix oil, chocolate and sugar.
Blend in eggs one at a time. Add vanilla, flour, baking powder and salt.
Chill overnight.
Drop by 1 teaspoon of dough in sugar.
Roll in sugar.
Shape into balls. Bake at 350° for 10 minutes (do not overbake).

title: 5-cup salad
directions: Drain mandarin oranges, but reserve pineapple juice.
Combine oranges, pineapple, coconut and marshmallows.
Stir in sour cream. Chill until set.
Makes 4 to 5 servings.

title: creamy pineapple pie
directions: Mix milk, pineapple and lemon juice.
Fold in whipped topping. Chill until ready to serve.

title: pineapple passion cake
directions: Grease a 15 1/2

by 10 1/2 inch baking pan. Mix cake and bake according to package directions for 15 minutes; cool. Mix pudding and milk as directed, stir in soften cream cheese. Spread over cooled cake. Spread whipped topping over pudding. Sprinkle pineapple evenly over whip topping. Sprinkle coconut evenly over pineapple. Sprinkle chopped pecans over coconut and top with maraschino cherries. Chill for 4 hours before serving.

title: elegant and easy pork tenderloin
directions: Coat tenderloins with mustard.
Place in large ziploc bag. Add garlic, Dale's marinade and pineapple juice.
Marinate all day or overnight.
Bake at 450° in foil lined pan 25 to 30 minutes or grill until internal temperature is 160°.
Let the meat rest 5 minutes before slicing.

title: shrimp ball
directions: Mash shrimp with fork and mix cheese, onion and garlic with just enough mayonnaise to stick together.
Roll into ball and roll around in parsley flakes and nuts.
Chill before serving.

title: dirt pudding
directions: Crush the cookies.
Mix butter (softened), cream cheese (softened), sugar, milk and pudding.
Layer mixture and cookies in large bowl.
Chill 2 to 3 hours.

title: molasses batter cake
directions: Mix
shortening,
sugar,
molasses
and
eggs, then add remaining
ingredients
(add buttermilk and baking soda last). Bake
in 3 nine-inch or 4 eight-inch baking pans at 350°.
Use applesauce or dried apples as filling.

title: gooey bars
directions: Mix together (like pie crust) and pat into a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan that has been greased and floured.

title: raisin sauce
directions: In a medium saucepan, combine brown sugar and cornstarch. Gradually stir in water.
Add raisins, lemon peel, lemon juice and vinegar.
Cook and stir until thickened and bubbly.
Cook and stir a couple of minutes more.
Serve with ham, pork or poultry.

title: beef stew with lentils
directions: Cut meat into 1/2-inch pieces.
Spray a 4-quart Dutch oven with nonstick coating.
Brown the meat, half at a time, over medium-high heat.
Drain fat.
Return all meat to pan.
Add the broth, onion, celery and carrot.
Bring to boiling; reduce heat. Simmer, uncovered, for 5 minutes.
Add the lentils, undrained stewed tomatoes and bay leaf.
Return to boiling; reduce heat to medium.
Cook, uncovered, about 45 minutes or until lentils are tender and stew is thickened.
Add beans.
Cover; cook for 10 minutes more or until beans are tender.
Remove bay leaf.
Ladle stew into bowls.
Yield:
8 servings.

title: currant scones
directions: Combine flour, sugar, baking powder and salt.
Cut in butter with a pastry blender until mixture resembles coarse meal.
Stir in currants.
Gradually add enough milk to the mixture to form a soft dough, stirring just until dry ingredients are moistened. Turn dough out onto a lightly floured surface; knead lightly, 4 or 5 times.
Roll dough to 1/2-inch thickness; cut with a 2-inch biscuit cutter.
Place on lightly greased baking sheets.
Bake at 450° for 8 to 10 minutes, or until lightly browned.
Serve warm. Makes 2 dozen.

title: no crust quiche
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Cook bacon and drain.
Crumble bacon and mix all ingredients together and bake in a 9-inch greased deep dish pie pan for 35 minutes.
(Cooked broccoli florets or cauliflower may be added in place of bacon.)

title: amazing raisin cake
directions: Grease and flour tube pan.
Mix all but the last 3 ingredients in large bowl; beat 2 minutes low speed.
Stir in apples, raisins and walnuts. Pour into pan; bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: chocolate fudge
directions: Mix margarine, sugar and milk in Dutch oven pan and cook over medium heat; stir constantly.
Cook for 5 minutes after mixture comes to a complete rolling boil.
Remove from heat and melt chocolate chips in mixture first, then add vanilla and Marshmallow Creme.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan lined with butcher's paper. When completely cool and hardened, fudge can be removed by pulling up on paper.
Also makes for easier cutting.

title: mimi's potato chip cookies
directions: Cream together the oleo, sugar and vanilla, then add crushed potato chips, flour and chopped nuts.
Make balls out of dough. Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Press with the bottom of a glass dipped in sugar.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Makes approximately 3 1/2 dozen.

title: corn chowder
directions: Cut pork into small pieces.
Cook until some fat is in pan. Add onions.
Cook until tender.
Add potatoes, boiling water, corn and hot milk.
Season with salt and pepper.
Heat until boiling. Serve garnished with parsley.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: apple cake
directions: Put apples and sugar into medium size mixing bowl, and stir together.
Let stand 15 minutes.
Add butter and egg to apples; stir.
Sift dry ingredients together and stir into apple mixture. Mix in raisins and nuts.
Pour into oiled, or Pam sprayed 8 inch square pan.
Bake 325 for about 45 minutes.

title: old fashioned coconut pie
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into uncooked pie shell.
Dust nutmeg over the top, if desired.
Bake at 350° until set, about 30 minutes.

title: cabbage slaw
directions: Place cabbage and onions in bowl in layers.
Cover with sugar. Make dressing with vinegar, salt, celery seed and mustard.
Bring to boil.
Add oil.
Pour hot dressing over cabbage.
Cover and place in refrigerator.
Toss several times.
Will keep in refrigerator for weeks.
Very good.

title: molasses crinkles
directions: Mix wet ingredients.
Mix dry ingredients.
Mix together. Chill dough.
Roll into balls the size of walnuts.
Dip tops in sugar.
Place sugar side up 3 inches apart on greased sheet. Sprinkle each cookie with water so it cracks.
Bake just until set, but not hard (10 minutes) at 325°.

title: cornbread from the south(johnnycake)
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake.

title: egg rolls
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients.
Add shredded cabbage & carrots a little at a time.
Wrap in egg roll skins.
Deep fry to golden brown.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook
broccoli
and drain.
Place in bottom of buttered dish. Mix other ingredients except cheese and crackers.
Pour over broccoli.
Sprinkle
cheese
on
top of this.
Cover with Ritz crackers.
Bake 20 minutes at 400°.

title: nutty fruit cake
directions: Chop all fruit and nuts; dredge in coconut.
Mix with milk. Line tube or loaf pan with waxed paper.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour. Remove from pan and peel paper off while hot.

title: cinnamon brownies
directions: Chop chocolates and put in medium bowl.
Combine butter, sugar, corn syrup and 1 tablespoon water in saucepan.
Boil until sugar dissolves, 1 to 2 minutes.
Stir sugar mixture into chocolate until completely melted.
Let cool slightly.
Mix together the flour, cinnamon, soda and salt.
Stir vanilla into chocolate mixture.
Beat in eggs.
Stir in flour mixture until just combined.
Stir in pecans.
Bake at 325° for about 25 minutes.

title: angel food cake
directions: In large bowl, beat egg whites with salt until foamy.
Add cream of tartar and vanilla and beat until it begins to get stiff. Add sugar and continue beating until very stiff (until when bowl is tilted on side it won't move).
Mix another cup of sugar with self-rising flour in a small Tupperware bowl; shake up to mix. Sprinkle that into egg white mixture and fold in by hand (not a mixer).

title: cheesy bacon potato slices
directions: Heat oven to 425°. Place butter in 10 x 15-inch pan. I use a jelly roll pan. Place in oven until butter melts. Add potatoes and sprinkle with salt and pepper. Toss until potatoes are thoroughly coated. Spread out into even layer. Bake 20 minutes. Turn, then sprinkle with bacon pieces and cheese. Continue baking 15 minutes longer or until potatoes are tender, crusty and golden brown. Serves 4.

title: broccoli and ricotta pizza
directions: In large heavy skillet, heat 2 tablespoons oil over moderately high heat until it is hot but not smoking and saute the broccoli, stirring for 1 minute or until bright green and coated well with hot oil.
Add water, cook the broccoli, covered, for 3 minutes, or until crisp-tender and let stand, uncovered, off the heat.

title: baking powder biscuits
directions: *If using self-rising flour, omit baking powder and salt.

title: crowd-pleasing baked beans
directions: Sort and wash beans; place in a Dutch oven.
Cover with water 2 inches above beans.
Let soak overnight.
Cover and bring to a boil; reduce heat and simmer 45 minutes.
Drain, reserving liquid. Add enough water to bean liquid to make 1 3/4 cups; set aside. Combine brown sugar, molasses, mustard and salt; stir well.
Layer half of the beans, brown sugar mixture, onion and bacon in a 4 1/2-quart casserole.
Top with remaining beans.
Pour reserved bean liquid over top.
Cover and bake at 300° for 5 hours.
Yields 20 to 22 servings.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Mix well.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: maroo's baked cheese
directions: Mix everything and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Can add crab, shrimp, hot peppers, ham, etc., if desired.

title: party meat balls
directions: Spread out meat and sprinkle with salt, pepper and garlic. Soak bread in milk.
Put meat in bowl with bread and mix thoroughly; use hands.
Shape into small meat balls; place in baking dish.
Mix jelly and chili sauce and pour over meat balls. Bake in 375° oven for about an hour or until sauce thickens. Depending on size of meat balls serves 35 to 40.

title: blender pecan pie
directions: Put eggs, sugar, salt, corn syrup, butter and vanilla into blender bowl.
Blend well.
Add 1 cup pecans and blend just enough to chop nuts coarsely.
Pour into pie shell.
Place halves on top. Bake at 350° until done.

title: lasagne
directions: Brown meat and onions.
Add tomatoes, sauce and seasonings. Cook noodles and drain.
In separate pan, combine sour cream and cheeses.
Melt together.

title: baked fish
directions: Roll fish fillets.
Place seam side down in ungreased baking dish.
Sprinkle salt and pepper over fish.
Mix sour cream, cheese and paprika, then spread over fish.
Cook, uncovered, in oven at 350° until fish flakes easily with fork, 20 to 30 minutes. Sprinkle onions over fish.

title: chocolate cream cake
directions: Prepare cake mix according to package directions, making 2 layers.
When completely cool, split both layers.
Combine sugar, sour cream, coconut and pecans, blending well.
Chill.
Reserve 1 cup sour cream mixture for frosting.
Spread the remainder between layers of cake.
Combine the reserved sour cream mixture with Cool Whip.
Blend well until smooth.
Spread on top and sides of cake. Seal cake in an airtight container and refrigerate overnight.

title: burritos
directions: Brown the hamburger.
Saute the onion, chilies and garlic 1 minute. Add the flour, salt, cumin and 1 cup hot water blended with 1 heaping teaspoonful of taco seasoning mix.
Add the hamburger.

title: sweet potato and apple casserole
directions: Layer half each of sweet potatoes and apples in an 8-inch square baking dish coated with vegetable cooking spray.
Combine sugar, cinnamon and white pepper; sprinkle half of mixture over potatoes and apples.
Drizzle with half of margarine.
Repeat procedure with remaining ingredients.
Cover casserole.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: tuna spread
directions: Blend all ingredients until smooth.
Serve with crackers. This can be rolled into a log and used for all types entertaining.

title: chicken strata
directions: Butter bread and set aside.
Combine chicken, onion, pepper, celery and mayonnaise in a large bowl.
In another bowl, combine eggs, milk and soup.
Cube 2 slices of bread and put in bottom of a 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Cover with half of the chicken mixture and half of the soup mixture.
Cube 2 more slices of bread.
Layer chicken, soup and top with bread.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes. Remove from oven and top with cheese. Bake another 30 minutes. Let stand 30 minutes.

title: pudding pie
directions: Prepare pudding according to package directions, using 1 1/2 cups milk for each package.
Fold in 1/2 cup of whipped topping into each prepared pudding.
Spread vanilla pudding on bottom of pie crust.
Top with chocolate pudding.
Sprinkle with chocolate pieces.
Chill 1 hour or until pudding is firm.
Just before serving, garnish edge of pie with some of the whipped topping.

title: shante's goulash
directions: Cook and drain macaroni.
Fry hamburger with onions and green peppers; drain.

title: orange delight
directions: Mix and chill for 1 hour.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown ground chuck.
Drain any grease.
Add taco seasoning and beans.
Mix.
Add crushed chips.
Spray a 9 x 14-inch baking dish with Pam.
Place ingredients in dish.
Add Mexican cheese cubes. Add additional crushed chips to top.
Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes or until cheese is melted.
Serve over chips.
Top with lettuce, grated cheese and tomatoes (optional).

title: pineapple bread pudding
directions: Beat eggs, sugar and butter.
Break bread up in pieces and then mix pineapple in bread.
Put all together and put into a greased baking dish.
Cook at 350° for 1 hour.
Serve with Cool Whip or ice cream.

title: fay's banana pudding
directions: Mix milk and pudding mix.
Stir in sour cream and Cool Whip. In bottom of dish, put a layer of wafers and bananas.
On top of that put 1/2 of the pudding mix.
Repeat with wafers, bananas and pudding mix.
Refrigerate.
That's all!

title: catfish
directions: Mix seasoning together.
Mix milk and egg together.
Season fish and dip into milk mixture.
Coat well.
Heat oil and fry fish until golden brown.

title: apple-blueberry muffins
directions: Sift together all dry ingredients.
Cream shortening and sugar; beat in egg.
Add milk alternately with flour mixture. Stir in applesauce.
Mix the blueberries with some of the flour. I use fresh blueberries that I freeze.
I mix them in frozen so the dough does not turn blue, then lightly mix in with the other ingredients.
Fill muffin tins 1/2 full.
Bake at 400° for about 20 minutes.
Makes about a dozen or more.

title: chuck roast in foil
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place roast on large piece of aluminum foil.
Sprinkle with dry onion soup mix.
Spread mushroom soup on top.
Wrap roast in foil.
Seal well.
Bake 2 hours or until done.

title: namie's fresh apple cake
directions: Beat eggs and oil.
Add sugar and continue beating.
Add sifted flour with salt, soda and baking powder.
Add finely chopped apples, flavoring and nuts.
Bake 1 hour at 350° or until done in long cake pan.

title: trout amandine
directions: Skin and fillet trout; soak in cold milk for 10 minutes or so, then drain.
Roll in seasoned flour; shake off excess.
Fry in one stick of melted butter in heavy frying pan, a few at a time, only long enough to just cook a few minutes on each side until golden and crisp.
Keep warm on heated platter.

title: cucumber salad
directions: Dissolve brine.
Peel and slice cucumbers very thin.
Pour brine over cucumbers.
Let stand overnight.

title: no peek chicken casserole
directions: Melt oleo in Dutch oven.
Pour in soups and water.
Add rice, then chicken.
Bake, tightly covered, at 300° for 3 hours.
No lookin' while cookin'!

title: barbecue green beans
directions: Brown bacon and onions.
Pour off grease.
Add ketchup, brown sugar and Worcestershire sauce.
Simmer for 2 minutes. Drain beans.
Put in greased 2-quart casserole.
Pour bacon dressing over beans.
Do not stir!
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: peanut butter bread
directions: In a large bowl, combine flours, sugar, baking powder, salt and peanuts.
In another bowl, blend egg and peanut butter; stir in buttermilk.
Quickly add liquid ingredients to dry ingredients. Spoon batter into greased pans.
Bake at 350° until tester comes out clean.
Cool in pans for 10 minutes.
Remove to rack.
Cool completely.

title: king ranch casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.

title: crab-stuffed shrimp
directions: Peel shrimp, leaving tails on.
Devein and butterfly.
Cook shrimp in boiling water 1 minute.
Drain and place in shallow baking dish.
Saute onion, green pepper and celery in 1/4 cup butter in skillet.
Combine crab meat and next 6 ingredients.
Mix, then stir into sauteed vegetables.
Top each shrimp with 3 tablespoons crab meat mixture.
Sprinkle with paprika and drizzle butter over shrimp.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Baste occasionally.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: easy vanilla ice cream
directions: In large bowl, combine ingredients; mix well.
Pour into ice cream freezer container.
Freeze according to manufacturer's instructions.
Freeze leftovers.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Boil and debone chicken; set aside and either sprinkle with chili powder or a little bit of enchilada sauce mix.
Combine soup, sour cream, green chilies, onion and chicken.
Soften each tortilla in an oil brushed skillet as you fill with chicken mixture.
Roll and put in an oblong dish for baking.

title: graham cracker pralines
directions: Line a jelly roll with graham crackers.
Put in saucepan the butter and brown sugar.
Boil for 1 minute after it comes to a complete boil.
Add nuts and pour over graham crackers.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Cut while warm.

title: cappuccino mix
directions: Combine all ingredients; mix well.
Store in an airtight container.
To Serve:
Place 1 tablespoon + 1 teaspoon mix in cup. Add boiling water.
Stir.
Makes 33 servings.

title: green onion dressing
directions: Combine yogurt and mayonnaise with wire whisk.
Add lemon juice, salt and onions.
Store in glass container in refrigerator, covered.
Yields about 4 cups.

title: impossible coconut pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 9-inch pie pan.
Mix all ingredients well and pour into pan.
Bake for 35 to 40 minutes.
Pie should be lightly browned and chewy.

title: chocolate peanut buddy bar
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In large mixer bowl, beat peanut butter and butter until smooth, about 1 minute.
Add sugar, eggs and vanilla extract.
Beat until creamy.
Blend in flour and salt; stir in 1 cup of chocolate chips.
Spread into ungreased 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes or until edges begin to brown.
Immediately sprinkle remaining chocolate chips over cookie layer.
Let stand 5 minutes until chips become shiny and soft. Spread chips evenly over top.
Cool completely.
Cut into 1 1/2-inch bars.
Makes 48 bars.

title: 4-day sweet gherkins
directions: First Day (Morning):
Wash cukes.
Place in container and cover with boiling water.
Six to 8 hours later (p.m.), drain. Cover with fresh, boiling water.

title: happy apple cake
directions: Spray 8-inch square baking dish with Pam.
Flour sides and bottom of dish.
Let apples and sugar sit 1/2 hour.
Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes or until toothpick inserted into center comes out clean.

title: if you love chocolate
directions: Bake fudge brownie mix as directed.
Chill.
Crush Heath bars while still in wrappers with hammer.
In a deep glass dish, start by crumbling part of brownies.
Next top with part of mousse, then some Heath bars.
Top that with Cool Whip.
Repeat layers and garnish top with a Heath bar.
Can be made a day ahead.

title: summer squash and tomatoes
directions: Place butter, onion, squash, salt, pepper and basil in 2-quart casserole dish.
Cover and microwave on High 3 to 5 minutes.
Stir in tomatoes and microwave on High 2 to 6 minutes.
Top with cheese and allow casserole to stand several minutes until cheese is melted.

title: cooked ham
directions: Wrap the fully cooked ham in tinfoil twice and put it in a pan.
Put it in the oven at 400° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours according to the size.
Take it out and mix and spread the brown sugar, mustard and vinegar.
Open foil and leave it open.
Put it back in the oven until that makes a glaze.
You can put pineapple slices with cherries in the center to make it look pretty.
Just brown all of it; it doesn't take but just a few minutes.
If the ham is not cooked, wrap in tinfoil and bake 16 minutes per pound at 400°.

title: turkey or chicken casserole
directions: Mix everything together and bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: 3 layer mississippi mud pie
directions: Melt butter.
Add flour, pecans and sugar.
Press into oblong pan.
Bake until brown at 350°.

title: sausage and macaroni casserole
directions: Cook macaroni in boiling salted water until tender, then drain.
Stir in butter.
Brown sausage lightly and drain.
Add sausage, macaroni, salt, pepper and spaghetti sauce together and place in glass casserole dish.

title: spicy-apple jello
directions: Boil water with red hots until red hots are dissolved.
Add jello to this and stir until dissolved.
Add applesauce and refrigerate in 8 x 8-inch pan.

title: no work chicken
directions: Marinate
chicken, skin down, for 6 hours or overnight. Turn chicken.
Cover dish and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Uncover; baste and
cook until done, about 15 minutes.
Serve with sauce over chicken.

title: lemon squares
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Grease 9 x 13-inch pan.
Combine flour, powdered sugar, salt and soft butter and press into pan.
Bake 20 minutes.
Cool slightly.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat eggs slightly.
Add combined flour, sugar and lemon juice.
Pour mixture over baked crust.
Bake 25 minutes.
Remove and sprinkle with confectioners sugar.
Cool.
Cut.
Refrigerate.

title: vermont scripture cake
directions: Combine in order given and follow Solomon's advice for making good boys:
Proverbs 23:14.
Pour batter into a greased and floured 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes.

title: renya's dip for apples
directions: Mix and serve with apple slices.

title: pastry dough
directions: Combine dry ingredients in food processor bowl.
Cut butter in 2 or 3 pieces; process with cutting blade until mixed.
With machine running, very slowly pour in the ice water through feed tube.
A ball of dough will form in 20 to 50 seconds.
If more dough is needed, repeat directions.
Do not double recipe.
Chill dough for 30 minutes before rolling out.
