title: asparagus fold-overs
directions: Cut crust from bread slices.
Roll flat with rolling pin. Then spread bread with cream cheese and add one spear of asparagus.
Roll bread around asparagus and secure with toothpick. Brush top of bread with butter.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese. Bake at 400° for 12 to 15 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Drain pineapple, reserving 3 tablespoons juice.
Combine sugar and flour; stir in reserved pineapple juice.
Add cheese and pineapple chunks, mixing well.
Spoon mixture into greased 1-quart casserole.
Combine melted butter and cracker crumbs, stirring well; sprinkle over pineapple mixture.
This is very good.
(Goes well with a ham dinner.)

title: country chicken vegetable soup
directions: In a 3-quart saucepan, combine broth and rice.
Over medium heat, bring to a boil.
Cover and cook over low heat for 15 minutes or until rice is tender, stirring occasionally.
Add mixed vegetables, chicken and parsley.
Heat through, stirring occasionally.
Serves 4.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Cook spaghetti; drain.
Let cool completely.
Chop cucumber, green pepper, onion and tomatoes.
Add to cooled spaghetti.
Pour on Italian dressing.
Mix well.
Best if chilled 2 to 3 hours before serving.
Re-stir just before serving, as dressing will settle in bottom of bowl.

title: coconut pie
directions: Mix everything in order.
Pour into greased pie pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until golden brown.

title: carl kabobs
directions: Cube cheese and pickles.
Cut ham into cubes.
Place cubes on toothpick.
Makes 40 to 60.

title: southwestern stew
directions: Brown beef in oil over medium heat in Dutch oven.
Combine liquid smoke and 3 cups of water.
Pour over meat. Simmer over low heat for two hours, occasionally basting with juices until fork-tender.
Remove meat.
Reserve liquid in Dutch oven.
Add potatoes and onion to liquid in Dutch oven.
Bring to a boil and simmer for 10 minutes.
Add corn, kidney beans and jalapeno peppers.
Simmer for 10 minutes.

title: pecan pie
directions: Combine sugar, cornstarch and salt; add beaten eggs, Karo syrup, melted butter and vanilla.
Arrange pecans in unbaked pie shell.
Pour ingredients on top.
Pecans will rise to the top as it bakes.
Bake at 425° for 15 minutes.
Decrease to 350° and bake approximately 3/4 hour or until solid but not dry.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix all and bake for 15 minutes.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Blend together and chill.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Cube steak and roll in flour.

Heat skillet with oil; add floured meat. When brown, add water, bouillon and Worcestershire sauce; simmer 1 to 2 hours. Five minutes before ready to serve, turn up heat. Bring to a boil. Add cream cheese. Serve over rice.

title: sugarless banana walnut cake
directions: In a mixing bowl, beat mashed bananas and margarine or butter. Add eggs; beat well.
Combine flour, baking powder, soda and cinnamon.
Add to banana mixture alternately with water.
Beat well after each addition.
Stir in walnuts.
Spoon into a greased 9-inch square baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until cake tests done.
Cool.
Yield:
9 servings.

title: zucchini cake
directions: Mix all together.
Bake in tube pan at 350° for 1 hour and 10 minutes.
If you want to prepare as cupcakes, bake for 30 minutes or until golden.
I enjoy using cupcake papers - freezes well.

title: barbecue dove
directions: Soak dove in salt water overnight.
Pressure cook dove for 15 to 20 minutes or until tender.
Wrap a slice of bacon around each dove and brush barbecue sauce on dove; put on grill.
Cook for 30 to 40 minutes.
Be sure to add sauce to dove to prevent them from drying out.
Turn frequently.

title: gussied up grandma
directions: Mix all but bacon.
Place in casserole.
Top with bacon.
Bake at 375° about 30 minutes.

title: garlic shrimp with twice-cooked green beans
directions: Shell and devein shrimp. Rinse shrimp under running cold water.
In a bowl, mix shrimp with soy sauce, minced ginger root, cornstarch, crushed red pepper and garlic.
Set aside.
Trim ends from green beans.

In a 12-inch skillet over high heat, in 1/2-inch boiling water, heat green beans to boiling. Reduce heat to low. Cover and simmer 5 to 10 minutes until green beans are tender-crisp; drain. Wipe skillet dry.

title: rita's salsa(the good stuff!)
directions: Combine in blender and process until desired consistency.
Let set in refrigerator for at least 6 hours before serving for flavors to combine.

title: surprise stuffing
directions: In a large skillet, saute the squash and onion in butter until tender.
Remove from the heat; stir in remaining ingredients. Transfer to a greased 1-quart casserole.
Bake, uncovered, at 350°. Yields 6 servings.

title: microwave peanut brittle
directions: Cook sugar and syrup 4 minutes on High heat.
Add peanuts; stir and cook 4 minutes again on High heat.
Add butter and vanilla and cook again for 1 1/2 minutes.
Thoroughly fold in soda.
Pour into buttered pan.
Let set for 1/2 hour before breaking into pieces.

title: german chocolate pound cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar; add eggs, one at a time, mixing well after each egg.
Add buttermilk and flavorings; mix and add dry ingredients, mixing well.
Melt chocolate over double boiler. Add to cake mix and blend.
Pour mixture into a greased and floured Bundt pan.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour.
After turning out of pan, put a powdered sugar frosting glaze over it or eat plain.

title: fantasy fudge
directions: In large saucepan, boil margarine, sugar and milk.
Stir constantly, boiling for 5 minutes over medium heat or until reaches 234° on candy thermometer.
Stir constantly to prevent scorching. Remove from heat.
Stir in chocolate chips and remaining ingredients until well blended.
Pour into greased 13 x 9-inch pan. Cool at room temperature.
Makes about 3 pounds.

title: taco dip
directions: Mix sour cream and taco mix.
Spread out flat on plate.
Then layer with Cheddar cheese, the olives, scallions, tomato and the peppers (peppers optional).

title: vegetable chili
directions: Saute onion and celery in hot oil until soft.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cover and simmer until vegetables are tender, about 30 to 45 minutes.
Serve with corn bread or buttery crackers.

title: savory pheasant
directions: Roll pheasant in flour with seasonings.
Brown in shortening.
Place in casserole.
Combine remaining ingredients and pour over pheasant.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours. Serve over wild rice.

title: easy chicken divan
directions: Cook broccoli and drain.
Arrange in baking dish.
Put cooked chicken on top.
Combine soup, mayonnaise, lemon juice and curry powder.
Pour over chicken.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Combine crumbs and butter.
Sprinkle on top of casserole.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: 1932 icebox cookies
directions: Cream butter with sugars.
Add beaten eggs.
Add spices and then stir in flour and nuts.
Mix well.
Form in a roll in wax paper and put in icebox overnight.
The next day slice thin and bake in a hot 400° oven about 8 minutes.
Watch close so they don't burn.

title: strawberry slush punch
directions: Combine the sugar and water in a medium size saucepan.
Bring to a boil.
Remove from heat and stir in the gelatin, stirring until completely dissolved.
Add remaining ingredients (except 7-Up or Sprite) and stir to mix well.
Pour into two 1-gallon plastic containers and freeze.
Remove from freezer 1 to 2 hours before you plan to serve it so that it will begin to thaw.
Break up the punch a little before pouring it into the punch bowl.
Pour in the 7-Up or Sprite and gently slush the mixture using a dull knife.
You will probably want to divide this punch into portions when serving, especially if you don't have a large punch bowl.

title: skillet chops 'n rice
directions: Brown chops in skillet.
Remove excess fat.
Season with salt and pepper.
Add soup, water, celery and thyme.
Cover skillet and let simmer 30 minutes.
Stir in rice.
Cover and cook over low heat about 20 minutes until rice and chops are tender.

title: celery seed salad dressing
directions: Combine and shake well.

title: rice meatballs
directions: *Or use 2 (8 ounce) cans tomato sauce mixed with 1/2 cup water.

title: bing cherry salad with coca-cola
directions: Drain juice from cherries and pineapple.
Two cups of juice are needed.
Add water to make this amount.
Bring juice to a boil and pour over jello, stirring, until completely dissolved.
When cool, add Cokes; stir and chill until partly congealed.
Add cream cheese and beat until it is dissolved; add cherries, pineapple and nuts. Chill overnight.

title: fruit salad
directions: Reserve juice; add additional water to make 3 cups liquid.

title: lemon pie
directions: Mix pie filling according to directions on box; let cool. Bake pie shell and let it cool. After filling is completely cooled, mix the cream cheese. Add to pie filling. Take the egg whites and beat stiff. Fold into filling with cream cheese added. Pour into cooled crust and top with Cool Whip. It's delicious!

title: lemon pie
directions: Mix cornstarch, 1/2 cup sugar, water and salt.
Cook until thickened, stir constantly.
Beat egg yolks and 1/2 cup sugar. Blend some of hot mixture into egg.
Stir into hot starch mix. Boil a few minutes.
Add lemon juice and butter.
Stir a while longer.
Set aside to cool.

title: baked bananas
directions: Spread melted butter and lemon juice over bottom of shallow baking dish that will hold 6 bananas. Stir butter and lemon juice together until blended. Turn bananas in dish until well coated with butter mixture. Put sugar and cinnamon in small bowl and stir with fork to blend thoroughly. Sprinkle sugar mixture evenly over bananas. Bake at 375° until butter begins to bubble, 18 to 20 minutes. Turn bananas over once after 10 minutes. Sprinkle coconut over bananas about 5 minutes before they finish cooking. Makes 6 servings.

title: lemon butter sauce(for fish)
directions: Combine all ingredients in a small saucepan and heat over low heat for 2 to 3 minutes.
Do not allow to boil.
Serve over fish.

title: spoon biscuits
directions: Dissolve yeast in hot water.
Set aside.
Add sugar to oleo. Add oleo to water.
Beat egg and add to other ingredients.
Add flour.
Beat with a spoon.
Cover mixture and refrigerate.
Cook as needed.

title: talerina
directions: Boil noodles until tender.
Put shortening in skillet with chopped onions, meat, garlic and green pepper.
When noodles are cooked and drained, add 1 can corn and 1 can olives (drained). Add tomato soup and 1/2 grated cheese.
Put in baking dish and sprinkle rest of cheese over top.
Heat through in oven 1/2 hour at 375°.

title: black magic cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: seafood casserole
directions: Saute the first 6 ingredients.
Add the flour, milk, seafood and pimentos.
May add can of water chestnuts if desired.
Top with 1/2 cup bread crumbs.
Bake or broil until hot.

title: spoon bread
directions: Combine corn meal, salt and fat.
Stir in boiling water; beat well.
Add milk and eggs; stir.
Add baking powder.
Turn into greased casserole.
Bake for 40 to 50 minutes at 350°.

title: orange jello salad
directions: Mix together.
Garnish with 2 oranges peeled and cut up. Add chopped nuts and mini-marshmallows if desired.

title: communion bread
directions: Mix flour and yeast in a bowl.
Mix molasses and water in a separate container.
Slowly add the water to the flour while mixing.
I use a large Kitchen Aid mixer because I have one, but mixing by hand is just as good.
Add more water if dough is too dry.
Knead.
My mixer with a dough hook takes about five minutes.
Allow dough to rise in a Pam-coated, covered bowl until about double in size.

title: hillbilly cake
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients in saucepan and boil for 1 minute. Cool.
Mix in other ingredients and bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: ham and potato bake
directions: Arrange diced potatoes and ham cubes in a shallow buttered casserole.
Stir together cheese, sour cream, eggs, green onion and seasoned salt.
Pour mixture over ham and potatoes.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until set.

title: bourbon franks
directions: Cut hot dogs in 4 pieces each.
Cut an x on the ends of each piece or 1 slit on the end of each cocktail sausage.

title: canning bread
directions: Butter the insides of the jars, being careful not to get any butter on the top inch of glass. Fill jars half full of bread batter. Pop into oven without lids and bake about 45 minutes. (If the jar loaves are done, they'll have the texture of regular bread, if they're not quite done, they'll feel and taste like bread pudding.) Remove each jar and screw a heated lid on tightly. The sealed bottle-bread will keep without refrigeration.

title: cobbler
directions: Spread pie filling on the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan. Sprinkle dry cake mix over the filling.
Place nuts on top of cake mix.
Sprinkle melted butter or margarine on top.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Cook in covered casserole dish in 270° oven for 1 1/2 hours.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Dissolve the yeast in water.
Set aside.
Mix flour, sugar and soda.
Cut in shortening and add buttermilk and yeast.
Work into flour.
Put into Tupperware and refrigerate until ready for use.

title: vegetable pizza squares
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Press crescent rolls to cover the bottom of a cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Cool completely.
Mix together the cream cheese and Ranch dressing until smooth.
Spread on cooled crust.
Sprinkle vegetables on filling. Press vegetables into crust, filling slightly.
Top with shredded Cheddar cheese.
Refrigerate and cut into squares before serving. Be sure to refrigerate leftovers.

title: texas cake
directions: Sift flour, sugar, cinnamon and soda together.
Melt margarine and add other ingredients.
Bring to a rapid boil and pour over dry ingredients.
Mix well.
Add eggs, buttermilk and vanilla to other ingredients.
Bake in large flat pan 20 minutes at 400°.

title: refrigerated slaw
directions: Boil together for 5 minutes.
Cool and pour over slaw.
Let set several hours or overnight.
Refrigerate.

title: spiced apple punch
directions: Pour apple juice and rum into 30-cup percolator.
Place lemon and orange slices, cloves and cinnamon sticks in percolator basket.
Perk through cycle.
Serve hot.
Yields 5 quarts.

title: stoby's cheese dip
directions: Mix the first 6 ingredients and bring to a boil.
(A double boiler works best.)
Add the cheese.
In a separate boiler, mix the butter and flour. Add to cheese mixture to thicken. Reduce heat to simmer and add the picante sauce, chili powder and lemon juice.
Blend well and remove from heat to cool.

title: haystacks
directions: Melt butterscotch morsels.
Add noodles and nuts.
Mix well. Drop by teaspoonful onto waxed paper.
Let cool.
Store in container.

title: apple-cheese casserole
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add cheese and cream well.
Add flour gradually
at
low speed.
Butter casserole dish and put in apples.
Cover with cheese mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: sweet and sour salad dressing
directions: Mix in blender the first 3 ingredients. Add remaining ingredients and blend well. Let stand at least 2 hours before serving.
Makes 1 quart.

title: green chili
directions: Saute onions and garlic. Brown pork with salt and pepper. Add all ingredients, except chilies. Simmer 2 to 4 hours. Add liquid as needed. Add green chilies for last half hour. Serve with cornbread and Tabasco Chipotle Sauce.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Combine dry ingredients and mix with sweet potatoes.
Mix milk and eggs.
Combine with sweet potato mixture.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake in a very hot oven (450°) for 10 minutes, then reduce temperature to 350° and bake 35 minutes.
Makes one 9-inch pie.

title: banana smoothie
directions: Pour milk in a blender.
Peel banana; break it in half and add to milk in blender.
Add vanilla and ice cubes.
Blend for 20 seconds; pour into glass.
Serve and enjoy!

title: lima bean and asparagus casserole
directions: Cook lima beans according to package directions and drain. Alternate layers of beans, asparagus and sliced water chestnuts in casserole dish.
Mix mushroom soup and milk.
Pour over vegetables. Top with grated cheese. Bake in covered casserole for 30 minutes at 300°.
Uncover and cook 25 minutes more. Serves 6.

title: vegetable bread
directions: Mix onion, green pepper, sausage, cheese and corn together. Cut biscuits in quarters, dip in melted butter and place a layer in a Bundt pan.
Place a layer of vegetable ingredients on biscuits.
Repeat layers.
Bake at 300° until done.

title: mexican salad
directions: Line oblong dish with Fritos.
Spread cooked rice over the Fritos.
Spread chopped onion over the rice.
Spread heated chili over this.
Put shredded lettuce over this.
Add chopped tomatoes over the lettuce.
Serve with Mexican style tomato sauce.
(You may add chili powder and fried ground beef to the chili; this adds so much.)
For a special dish, serve taco flavored Fritos.
Add cheese for topping.

title: zachary's peanut butter cookies
directions: Blend ingredients together.
Roll into balls and coat with sugar.
Bake at 375° for about 10 to 12 minutes.

title: mareta's brownies
directions: Mix butter, sugar, eggs, flour, melted chocolate, vanilla and pecan pieces.
Put into a greased baking pan and bake until firm in 350° oven.
I always triple or quadruple the recipe and bake in a 16 x 11-inch Mirro baking pan.

title: texas tortilla soup
directions: Saute onion, garlic, carrots, celery and meat in oil.
Simmer 5 minutes.
Combine seasonings and flour; add to sauteed mixture. Stir.
Heat chicken broth.
Add tomatoes and rest of ingredients, except tostados and garnishes.
Simmer 1 hour.

title: beef hot dish
directions: Cook noodles.
Brown hamburger and onion.
Mix in all soups. Heat in a 350° oven until bubbly.
Serves 10 to 12 people.

title: million dollar pie
directions: Mix milk and lemon juice until thick.
Set aside.
Drain fruit cocktail and add to milk mixture.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Pour into baked pie shells and refrigerate.

title: orange julius
directions: Combine all ingredients in a blender.
Mix well for 30 seconds until slushy.
Serve immediately.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: breakfast scramble
directions: In a skillet, cook beef and onion over medium heat until meat is no longer pink. Drain. Add potatoes, water, salt and pepper. Cover and simmer for 20 minutes or until potatoes are tender. Add tomatoes. Cook for 5 minutes. Pour eggs over mixture. Cook and stir until eggs are completely set. Top with cheese. Cover and cook for 1 minute or until cheese is melted. Yield: 4 to 6 servings.

title: mushrooms
directions: Cut stems off mushrooms and chop into very small pieces.
Fry onion, bread crumbs and salt in butter until onions are tender. Stuff in mushroom tops.
Broil 10 to 15 minutes.

title: bohne berrogi
directions: Use your favorite sweet dough recipe.
Cook beans, drain and mash; add salt and sugar.
When dough is ready to shape, form into balls the size of a large walnut.
Let rise about 30 minutes. Pull apart and place 1 rounded teaspoonful of bean mixture on dough and close by pressing edges together.
Place in greased pan and let rise about 30 minutes.
Bake in moderate oven for 25 minutes.
Serve with hot sauce.
(Dough can also be rolled out and cut into 3 to 3 1/2-inch squares and then filled.)

title: italian vegetable soup
directions: Simmer until macaroni is tender.

title: chicken puff pie
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In large saucepan, combine all ingredients, except crescent rolls.
Cook until mixture is bubbly and thoroughly heated, stirring occasionally.

title: baked chicken
directions: Bake 1 1/2 hours at 350°.
Do not cover.
You can substitute 1 can whole cranberry sauce instead of apricot jam.
Serve with Rice-A-Roni with almonds.

title: sweet potato puffs
directions: Mix sweet potatoes, butter and brown sugar together until smooth and creamy.
Place a small amount of mixture in palm of hand with a marshmallow in the center. Cover with more potato mixture and form into the shape of a small sweet potato.
Roll in crushed corn flakes and place on greased baking pan.
Bake at 400° for 5 minutes.

title: spicy oyster crackers
directions: Combine salad dressing mix, oil and spices.
Pour over crackers.
Stir to coat crackers.
Place in a pan.
Place in oven for 15 to 20 minutes at 250°.

title: frozen rum punch
directions: Mix all together.
Freeze for day or more (I always freeze at least 2 nights).

title: pistachio salad
directions: Mix together Cool Whip and dry pudding mix.
Add pecans, marshmallows and pineapple.
Blend together and refrigerate for 1 hour or more to serve.

title: fancy cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients in bowl except bacon drippings.
Put bacon drippings in a 9 x 9 inch pan or black skillet.
Heat in oven until dripping cover bottom of pan.
Pour in cornbread batter and bake for 20 to 25 minutes at 400.

title: chocolate chip cake
directions: Mix all ingredients well and stir in the package of chocolate chips.
Bake in a greased and floured Bundt cake pan at 350° for approximately 1 hour.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Brown hamburger and onion.
Mix other ingredients.
Simmer for at

title: corn bake
directions: Beat eggs.
Mix all ingredients together.
Top with grated cheese.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: chocolate brownies
directions: Beat eggs in a small bowl.
Gradually add sugar and vanilla. Beat well.
Blend in melted butter.
Combine flour and cocoa; gradually add to egg mixture until well blended.
Spread in a greased oblong pan.
Bake at 325° for 20 to 25 minutes, until brownie pulls away from edges of pan.
Cool in pan before cutting.

title: easy peach cobbler
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Pour peaches and syrup into a greased 8 x 8-inch pan.
Mix remaining ingredients except butter.
Pour over the peaches.
Place pats of butter all across the top.
Place in preheated oven and cook about 30 minutes or until top is golden brown.

title: strawberry cheese cake
directions: Blend flour, butter and pecans.
Press in a 13 x 9-inch pan. Bake for 20 minutes at 350°.
Cool.
Mix the powdered sugar and cream cheese; blend well.
Add Cool Whip; spread over crust.
Mix sugar, cornstarch and jello; add remaining ingredients.
Cook until thick.
Cool.
Add 1 quart of sliced strawberries or whole berries.
Spread over filling.
Chill overnight.
Keep refrigerated; do not freeze.
Remaining Cool Whip may be served on top, or decorate around edges.

title: microwave caramel corn
directions: Bring first 4 ingredients to a boil in a 2-quart glass measurer.
Boil 2 minutes on High in microwave.
Remove from oven and stir in soda.
Put popcorn in large brown bag (or Reynolds oven bag).
Pour syrup mixture over popcorn.
Fold over top of bag and place in microwave.
Microwave on High for a total of 4 minutes. Remove bag every minute and shake.
Spread caramel corn on waxed paper to cool.
Store in tightly covered container.

title: taco dip
directions: Mix sour cream and taco seasoning.
Spread in a pie plate or any plate with raised sides.
Top with chopped vegetables.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: creamed chicken and biscuits
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease the bottom and sides of an 11 x 7-inch baking dish.
Chop the onion.
Heat margarine in a small nonstick skillet over medium-high heat until melted.
Stir in onion.
Saut until tender.
Combine onion, chicken, soup, sour cream and milk in a medium bowl and mix well.
Spoon mixture into prepared baking dish.
Bake for 15 minutes.
Remove from oven. Sprinkle baked layer with 3/4 cup of the Cheddar cheese.
Arrange biscuits in a single layer over top.
Sprinkle with remaining Cheddar cheese.
Bake until biscuits are golden brown and the sauce is bubbly, about 20 minutes longer.
Serve immediately. Yield: 6 servings.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix
sugar, flour and cocoa.
Add butter, egg yolks and milk. Cook
on
top
of
stove
until partly thick.
Place in uncooked pie
shell	and
bake
at 350° until crust is brown. Beat
egg whites until stiff (add 2 tablespoons sugar per egg white
and
2 teaspoons vanilla).
Spread over cooked pie and brown in oven for 5 to 10 minutes more.

title: mexican delight
directions: Brown meat and onion; drain off fat.
Add taco seasoning and enough water to moisten mixture.
Mix soups and sauce together. Melt Monterey Jack cheese and Velveeta cheese together.
In a 9 x 12-inch pan, layer as follows:
1/2 meat mixture, 1/2 tortilla shells, 1/2 soup and sauce mixture and 1/2 melted cheese.
Repeat layers and sprinkle with grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until cheese browns.

title: barbecue chicken
directions: Combine all ingredients in a Dutch oven.
Bring to a boil. Add desired number of chicken pieces.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: linguini salad
directions: Cook the linguini as directed on the box.
Immediately cool in cold water; drain.
Toss all of the ingredients together in a large salad bowl.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.

title: chocolate zucchini cake
directions: Combine all ingredients except chocolate chips. Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle chocolate chips on before baking.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: chocolate eclair
directions: Cover the bottom of a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan with whole graham crackers.
Set aside.

title: cinnamon coffee cake
directions: Cream shortening, sugar and eggs.
Add milk alternating with flour and baking powder.
Put batter in greased cake pan. Sprinkle brown sugar over batter and cinnamon over brown sugar. Dot top with small pieces of butter.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: carolina fudge cake
directions: In saucepan, bring to boil, margarine, cocoa and water.
In bowl, mix together eggs, buttermilk, vinegar, soda and vanilla. Sift together flour, sugar and salt.
Add to milk mixture.
Add cocoa mixture and mix well.
Pour batter into greased and floured jelly roll pan (15 1/2 x 10 1/2 x 1-inch) pan and bake in preheated oven at 375° for 20 minutes.

title: file gumbo
directions: Saute onions, green onions, celery, parsley and garlic in small amount of fat in large pot.
When tender, add sausages and ham.
Simmer 15 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Add gizzards also.
Turn off fire.
Peel shrimp.
Place hulls in pan of water. Boil 20 minutes.
Strain water into pot with other ingredients. Turn on fire.
Cook slowly until meats are tender.
Add shrimp, crab, necks and oysters.
Turn off fire when necks are tender. One-half hour before serving, bring to boil.
Add 3 tablespoons file.
Mix well.
Serve over rice.

title: company tuna bake
directions: Cook macaroni.
Mix cream cheese and soup together.
Add next four ingredients.
Pour into casserole dish.
Mix crumbs and margarine and sprinkle over top.
Bake at 375° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: burnt caramel pie
directions: Sprinkle 3/4 cup sugar into skillet over medium heat. Caramelize sugar.
Stir all the time until sugar is golden brown. At once add the hot (scalded) milk.
I use part half and half for richness.
Combine 3/4 cup sugar and flour.
Beat egg yolks until foamy.
Add just enough warm milk to make a runny paste.
Pour slowly into hot milk mixture until it thickens, stirring constantly.
Add vanilla and pinch of salt; then pour into pie shell.
Beat egg whites adding about 1/4 cup of sugar, pinch of salt and 1/2 teaspoon cream of tartar.
When it stands in peaks, spread on pie.
Bake 20 minutes at 350° until meringue is a light golden brown.

title: hole-in-one-eggs
directions: First, put a hole in center of bread using a glass turned upside-down.
Melt butter in skillet.
Butter both sides of bread. Place in skillet.
Let one side brown a bit and add an egg to the hole of the bread.
Flip the bread over without breaking the yolk. Brown that side as well.
There you have a hole-in-one!

title: evan's extra easy lasagna
directions: Stir beef and pasta sauce together. Spread 1/3 of meat sauce in lightly greased 9 x 13-inch baking pan. Layer 5 noodles, half of Ricotta cheese and half of Mozzarella cheese. Repeat layers. Spread remaining meat sauce over Mozzarella cheese. Slowly pour 1/2 cup of hot water around inside edge of baking pan. Cover with heavy-duty aluminum foil or lid. Bake in 375° oven for 50 minutes. Uncover. Bake 10 minutes more. Let stand 10 minutes before serving. Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: cocoa mix
directions: Sift the ingredients together 3 times.
Put mixture in an airtight container.

title: calico beans
directions: Drain juice off all beans.
Brown bacon and drain.
Add beef and onions, brown.
Combine all beans with browned ingredients and put in crock-pot.
Combine brown sugar, catsup, vinegar and salt; pour over beans.
Add about 1 cup of water and simmer, cook 3 to 4 hours on low heat.

title: mint cookies
directions: Melt wax slowly in pan on stove.
Add chocolate chips and peppermint oil.
Dip crackers and place on wax paper.

title: easy popcorn balls
directions: Mix together.
Boil 1 minute and pour over 3 quarts popped corn.
Working quickly, form into balls.
(I dip my hands in cool water to keep balls from sticking to them.)

title: hot cheese dip
directions: Cook on high until cheese is melted.
Turn down to warm or simmer.

title: golden harvest muffins
directions: In a 4-quart bowl, combine flour, wheat flour, sugar, cinnamon, soda, salt and cloves.
Add apples, carrots, coconut, raisins and nuts.
Mix well.
Add oil, milk, vanilla and eggs. Stir until moistened.
Fill 3/4 full in lined muffin tins.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Makes 36 muffins.

title: pink lemonade pie
directions: In bowl combine, lemonade, condensed milk and half of the Cool Whip.
Stir until creamy and smooth.
Add drops of red food coloring to make a delightful pink color.
Pour into pie shell. Refrigerate.
Serve with leftover Cool Whip on top.

title: microwave hamburger stroganoff
directions: Crumble beef into a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Sprinkle with mushrooms and onion.
Microwave on High for 7 or 8 minutes, stirring twice.
Stir in next 5 ingredients with 1 cup water; mix well.
Microwave covered on High for 7 minutes; stir once.
Stir in buttermilk and parsley flakes.
Microwave covered for 2 or 3 minutes or until hot.
Yields 4 servings.

title: potatoes savoyarde
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Butter a 2-quart baking dish or souffle dish.
In a bowl mix together garlic, parsley, cheese and pepper. Layer 1/3 of potatoes, then 1/3 of garlic mixture.
Dot with 1 tablespoon butter; cut in pieces.
Repeat layers; top with potatoes.
Pour stock over potatoes and put on the last 1/3 of garlic mixture.
Dot with butter.
Cover with foil and bake 30 minutes.
Uncover and bake 30 to 40 minutes more, until brown and potatoes are tender.

title: strawberry microwave cake
directions: Important:
Do not follow directions on cake box!

title: pecan chess bars
directions: Mix by hand mixer and pour on top of crust. Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Cool completely. Refrigerate before cutting. Cut into bars. Refrigerate for up to two weeks.

title: one dish meal
directions: Saute ground beef and diced onion in frying pan until brown. Grease baking dish and place layer of Tater Tots, ground beef and Cheddar cheese soup.
Repeat layers, ending with cheese soup on top.
Bake in 350° oven for about 30 to 45 minutes or until Tater Tots are done.

title: company hot dish
directions: Cook noodles in salt water until done but not soggy.
Rinse in cold water and drain.
Brown ground beef.
Add salt, sugar, pepper and tomato sauce and simmer slowly while preparing remaining ingredients.
Combine cream cheese, cottage cheese, sour cream, green onions and green pepper.

title: million dollar pound cake
directions: Combine butter and sugar; cream until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add flour to creamed mixture alternately with milk, beating well after each addition.
Stir in flavorings.
Pour batter in well-greased and floured 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes or until cake tests done.

title: party eggnog
directions: Beat eggs, sugar, and salt slightly.
Stir in 3 cups chilled, scalded milk.
Cook in top of double boiler over simmering water, until mixture is thick enough to coat spoon.
Chill well.
Stir in 4 cans cream and 1 cup chilled milk.
Add cinnamon and nutmeg. Mix well and chill.
Serve in glass with spoon of whipped cream or Cool Whip.

title: quick garlic bread
directions: Spray rolls with the cooking spray.
Sprinkle with garlic powder and parsley.
Toast in toaster oven until brown and crunchy.
Serve hot.

title: basic pie dough
directions: Combine flour and salt in bowl.
Cut in margarine until like coarse meal.
Add water, a little at a time until pastry forms balls.
Two balls form flat circles, one inch thick.
Refrigerate one hour, cover first.

title: hershey's chocolate chunk butter pecan bars(makes about 3 dozen bars)
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
In large mixer bowl combine brown sugar, butter, egg yolk and vanilla.
Blend in flour and salt.
Press mixture into prepared pan.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes or until lightly browned.
Remove from oven; immediately sprinkle chocolate chunks on crust.
Let stand until softened, about 5 minutes.
Spread evenly over crust; sprinkle with pecans.
Cool completely; cut into bars.

title: party oyster crackers
directions: Place crackers in a large bowl.
Combine remaining ingredients in a jar with a tight-fitting lid.
Shake until well-blended. Pour over crackers and stir well.
Pour onto cookie sheet and bake at 150° for 15 to 20 minutes, or until golden brown.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Boil the sugar and milk together for 4 minutes.
Mix together the Marshmallow Creme and peanut butter.
Spread in greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Put walnuts on top.

title: son of a gun
directions: Brown hamburger.
Set aside.
Cook noodles, strain.
Put noodles in an 8x8-inch (or 9x13) pan.
Place hamburger meat on noodles, then cut Velveeta cheese into small squares and place on top of hamburger and noodles.
Finally, bake at 350° until cheese is melted (about 20 minutes).
Serve hot.

title: lemon poppy seed cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
In a medium bowl, combine flour, baking soda, lemon zest, coriander and poppy seed.
Mix well with a wire whisk and set aside.

title: chocolate brownie pie
directions: Prepare shell and chill.
Melt butter and chocolate in a heavy saucepan over low heat.
Pour into a medium size bowl. Cool slightly. Add eggs, sugar and corn syrup.
Beat with rotary beater until well blended. Stir in vanilla and pecans.
Pour into shell. Top with ice cream or whipped cream.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Place rice in pan and place chicken on top.
Add mushroom soup and water.
Top with Lipton onion soup mix.
Bake for 2 hours, covered with foil, at 325°.

title: quick lasagna
directions: Brown ground beef along with onion, garlic and oregano.
Drain off excess fat from ground beef.

title: yaki mon du(korean egg rolls)
directions: Brown ground beef.
Do not drain meat.
Add chopped cabbage, chopped onion, and shredded carrots.
Add soy sauce.
Cook on low to medium heat.
(Be sure to place lid on pot.)
Cook for 15 minutes, stirring frequently.
Turn on low heat.
Cook another 15 minutes.
Add more soy sauce if needed.
Place 2 Tbsp. of meat mixture into each won ton wrapper.
Seal wrapper by brushing water on sides of wrapper and then press together.
Press down the whole wrapper.
Deep fry until it floats.

title: german fried onions and potatoes
directions: Peel and cut onion into 1/4-inch thick slices.
Cut each slice crosswise to make about 1 1/2 cups coarsely diced onion.
Heat oil in skillet.
Add onion and bacon.
Saute over medium heat until onion is soft.
Stir in potatoes, salt and pepper, turning until browned, about 10 minutes.
Pour egg in.
Remove from heat; carefully mix with spatula until egg is set.
Sprinkle with parsley.
Makes 4 servings.

title: beer-cheese fondue
directions: In saucepan cook garlic in butter until garlic begins to brown.
Discard garlic.
Stir flour and mustard into butter.
Add beer.
Cook and stir until bubbly.
Stir in Worcestershire sauce; gradually stir in cheese until melted.
Transfer to fondue pot. Spear bread, vegetables or meat on fondue forks.
Swirl in fondue to coat.
Serves 6.

title: chocolate potato cake
directions: In a mixing bowl, cream the butter and 1 cup of sugar.
Add egg yolks; beat well.
Add potatoes and mix thoroughly.
Combine flour, cocoa, baking powder, cinnamon, salt, nutmeg and cloves; add to creamed mixture alternately with milk, beating until smooth.
Stir in vanilla and nuts.
In a mixing bowl, beat egg whites until foamy.
Gradually add remaining sugar; beat until stiff peaks form.
Fold in batter. Pour into a greased and floured 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes or until cake tests done.

title: vondell's cobbler
directions: Mix well (except fruit) and pour into buttered bake pan.
Pour 4 to 6 cups cooked sweetened fruit over batter.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes until done.

title: crock-pot barbecue
directions: Simmer roast, onion and cloves in water in crock-pot for 10 to 12 hours.

title: coffee cake
directions: Mix the first 4

ingredients and beat for 2 minutes. Spread in a greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan (will be sticky). Add remaining cake mix to 5 tablespoons of margarine; set aside. Pour 1 can of pie filling over dough.
Spread crumb mixture on top of filling.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.
Glaze with icing.

title: larry's scalloped potatoes and onion(low-fat; serves 6 to 8)
directions: Saute the onion and garlic in the oil in a nonstick skillet briefly, for about 2 to 3 minutes.
Place the sliced potatoes into a 9-inch glass baking dish. Add the wilted onion and garlic and mix.
Sprinkle with pepper, thyme and vegetable seasoning.
Pour the broth over the potato mixture and sprinkle with cheese. Bake in a preheated 425° oven for 30 to 40 minutes or until lightly browned and tender.

title: mother heller's chocolate cake
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Add eggs, cocoa, milk and flour. Mix well.
Add soda, vanilla and hot water.
Stir well.
Pour into prepared pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: butterscotch pie
directions: In heavy saucepan mix sugar, flour, egg yolks and salt; slowly add all milk and use a wire whisk or wooden spoon to combine. Cook over medium heat until it starts to thicken, add butter and cook until thick and creamy. Remove from heat and add vanilla. Pour into baked pie shell and top with egg whites which have been beaten until they hold soft peaks beating in 1/4 cup sugar. Spread over filling and bake until brown at 375°.

title: blintz casserole
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch glass dish.
Layer blintzes.
Whisk together and pour over blintzes:
eggs, sour cream, orange juice, vanilla, sugar and butter.
Sprinkle with cinnamon and sugar. Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: mexican jalapeno corn bread
directions: Mix all dry ingredients (except cheese) with buttermilk and oil.
Add water, if needed.
Pour 1/2 of ingredients in greased skillet.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Pour rest of ingredients in. Sprinkle a small amount of cheese on top, if desired.
Bake until done.

title: fresh strawberry dip
directions: Combine marshmallow cream and softened cream cheese. Mix until well blended.
Add flavoring and 1/2 cup pureed strawberries.
Mix again. Garnish with 1/2 strawberries on toothpicks.

title: pumpkin butterscotch cookies
directions: Beat sugar, pumpkin, oil and vanilla.
Sift dry ingredients and add to pumpkin mixture.
Blend in chips and nuts.
Drop by spoonful onto cooking sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 14 minutes. Makes 3 to 4 dozen.

title: butterscotch crunch cookies
directions: Combine the sugars, shortening and vanilla.
Add the eggs, one at a time; beat.
Add the remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Add chocolate chips if you like.

title: ham roll-ups
directions: Put ham slices between paper towel to dry.
Mix other ingredients together to spreadable consistency.
Spread mixture on ham slices, roll and stick with 5 toothpicks.
Refrigerate overnight and slice between toothpicks.
Serve attractively, using parsley to garnish.

title: banana salad
directions: Cook until thick and cool. Pour over sliced bananas. Add crushed peanuts and mini marshmallows.

title: kitchen scramble
directions: Cut up vegetables and stir into the egg; dip in cornmeal, salt and pepper. Fry in oil or bacon drippings (uncovered). Turn often until nicely browned, about 25 minutes.

title: grape jam
directions: May sprout any kind of raw seeds in the following manner:

title: baked beans
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Cook in a crock-pot on low for 8 to 12 hours or on high for 2 to 3 hours.

title: peach coffee cake
directions: With mixer, blend.
Pour batter into a greased 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Sprinkle topping over batter.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Will be very moist.

title: fruity rainbow
directions: Combine lemon juice, honey and cinnamon; pour over orange slices in a bowl and refrigerate overnight.
Drain oranges and set aside liquid.
Place oranges in bottom of large trifle bowl.
Layer fresh fruits until bowl is topped.
Pour the set aside liquid over the fruit.
Serve chilled.
Garnish with mint sprigs.

title: dutch easter men
directions: Dissolve yeast.
Melt butter.
Mix with cold milk and add to the yeast.
Stir in salt and flour.
Cover bowl and let rise 1/2 hour.
Knead until smooth.
Divide into 8 portions.
Shape each piece into oblong roll 5 inches long.
Place egg on the roll, a little above center.
Cut slits at 2, 4, 6, 8 and 10 o'clock. Pull the dough and shape arms and legs.
Put arms over and across the egg.
Place on greased cookie sheets and cover with kitchen towel.
Let rise, covered, until doubled in size.
Bake at 350° to 375° until lightly browned.
If you take them out of the oven too soon, the egg will not be cooked.
Be sure they are browned, not burned!
Can be frosted and/or decorated.
Makes a cute little egg man that can be your lunch!
Can use raisins for eyes.

title: roast venison
directions: Soak venison in salt and vinegar 5 or 6 hours or overnight. Rinse and put in roasting pan with 2 or 3 cups of water.
Salt and pepper to taste. Sprinkle 1 package onion soup mix over meat. Wrap entire meat in bacon and sprinkle other package of soup mix over the wrapped meat.
Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 4 or 5 hours or until tender.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix well and store in refrigerator.

title: elephant stew
directions: Cut elephant in bite-size pieces, this will take about 2 months.
Add enough brown gravy to cover.
Cook about 4 weeks. This will serve 3,800 people.
If more are expected the rabbits may be added.
Do this only if necessary, as most people don't like hare in their stew.
If feeding a multitude, add 5 loaves and 2 fishes.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Wash cukes; do not peel.
Slice cukes and onions thinly. Place in large deep pan.
Add all remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Bring to a boil, but do not boil.
Can hot.
Makes 7 to 8 pints.

title: easy baked chicken
directions: Spread rice in greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Rinse chicken and pat dry.
Arrange over rice.
Combine onion soup mix, chicken soup, water and butter in bowl; mix well.
Pour over chicken. Bake, covered, at 350° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours or until tender. Serves 4 to 6.

title: vegetable provencale
directions: In a large skillet, cook onions and garlic over medium heat until soft.
Stir in zucchini, summer squash and green peppers. Cook about 20 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients, except cheese. Cook about 10 minutes more.
About 1 minute before done, sprinkle liberally with cheese and mix in.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: quick cookies
directions: Melt oleo and sugar over heat for 2 1/2 to 3 minutes.
Remove from heat; add pecans.
Pour over graham crackers.
Bake 7 minutes at 350°.
Remove from oven and sprinkle chocolate chips over all.

title: fruit dip
directions: Mix together until smooth and well blended. Serve with fresh cut up fruit.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Mix together first three items and press in 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake for 10 minutes at 350° and cool.

title: sweet-and-sour rutabagas
directions: Peel rutabagas; cut into 1/2-inch cubes.
Combine with onion and bacon drippings in a 2-quart casserole.
Cover with heavy-duty plastic wrap and microwave at High for 16 to 20 minutes or until tender; stir every 4 minutes.
Add vinegar, sugar, salt and pepper to rutabaga; stir well.
Cover and microwave at High for 8 to 9 minutes or until thoroughly heated and sugar melted, stirring after 4 minutes.
Stir in green onions.
Let stand, covered, 2 minutes.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix the first 5 ingredients and put in a baking dish.
Mix flour and brown sugar together.
Sprinkle over top of sweet potatoes; then sprinkle on nuts and 1/3 cup of melted butter. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: no bake cake
directions: Blend sugars, Cool Whip and cream cheese in mixing bowl until smooth.
Place one layer of cake on plate; spread with some of sugar mixture and then spoon on some of pie filling.
Continue until all layers are stacked.
Ice the outside of cake with sugar mixture and then spoon rest of pie filling on top, letting some run down sides.

title: punch
directions: Mix together and add ice.

title: pumpkin muffins
directions: Sift 1/2 cup sugar and next 5 ingredients in large bowl.
Cut in butter until crumbly.
Combine egg, pumpkin, milk and raisins in bowl; blend well.
Add to flour mixture; stir until just mixed.

title: blueberry custard pie
directions: Before beginning your pie, thaw out your deep-dish pie crust and generously poke holes in the crust (bottom and sides). Bake it for 10 minutes at 400°. After you remove it, lightly brush with melted butter.

title: crustless pecan pie(or chewy squares)
directions: Beat eggs 1 minute (fluffy).
Add flour, sugar, salt, butter, vanilla and pecans.
Pour into greased and floured pie plate or square baking dish.
Bake at 325°.
It is done when top is golden brown (approximately 30 minutes).

title: zucchini appetizers
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease pan or miniature cupcake pan.
Mix all ingredients together, then spread in pan.
Bake until golden brown, approximately 25 minutes.
Let stand about 10 minutes before serving.
(Can be served hot or cold.)
Makes about 4 dozen.

title: fruity ice cream
directions: Mix bananas, orange juice, lemon juice, sugar, cream and milk together.
Pour into an ice cream freezer and freeze according to freezer instructions.

title: peanut blossoms
directions: Sift together flour, soda and salt.
Cream together butter and peanut butter and add sugar and brown sugar, creaming well.
Add unbeaten egg and vanilla.
Blend in the dry ingredients gradually and mix thoroughly.
Shape dough into balls using a rounded teaspoonful for each.
Roll balls in sugar and place on greased baking sheets.
Bake in moderate oven at 375° for 8 minutes. Remove from oven.
Top each cookie with a Hershey's Kiss, pressing down firmly so cookie cracks around the edge.
Return to oven and bake 2 to 5 minutes longer until golden brown.

title: peg's potato soup
directions: Cover vegetables with water; boil to near dry (do not dry). Add remaining seasonings. Semi-mash and add half and half and milk. Heat to simmer. Sprinkle with paprika.

title: green enchiladas
directions: Chop and heat chicken and onion in skillet.
In separate large pan heat soups, milk, chilies and cheese until melted. Place a large spoonful of chicken in tortilla.
Add a spoonful of cheese mixture.
Roll up each tortilla and place in 11 x 13-inch pan.
Repeat for each tortilla.
Pour remaining cheese mixture over all the rolled up tortillas.
It should cover all.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: hominy and corn casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Layer in a 12 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish 1/3 of the hominy and 1/3 of the corn. Sprinkle lightly with salt and pepper.
Add 2 to 3 tablespoons chilies. Dot with butter and 4 more tablespoons sour cream.
Sprinkle with 1/2 cup of both cheeses.
Repeat layers 2 times.
Bake for 35 to 40 minutes. Serves 12.

title: remedy for arthritis
directions: Use regular water glass.
Put in honey and vinegar.
Fill with water.
Drink 3 times a day.

title: raisin bars
directions: Cook the raisins and water for a few minutes; cool and drain (save juice).
Cream together the white sugar and margarine.
Add the eggs; beat.
Add raisin juice alternately with flour mixture (flour, soda, salt and cinnamon).
Add the raisins.
Put into greased and floured pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: goof balls
directions: Melt caramels, milk and margarine in double boiler.
Roll marshmallows in caramel mixture and then in Rice Krispies.

title: rice and peas salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Let stand overnight to marinate in refrigerator.

title: waldorf cantaloupe salad
directions: Blend fruit and nuts.
Add French dressing and chill 15 minutes.
Just before serving, drain off excess dressing and serve on a lettuce leaf with a dash of whipped cream and a sprinkle of paprika.

title: clams casino
directions: Mix ingredients.
Bake in baking shells at 350° for 20 minutes.
Squeeze lemon juice over shells before or after baking.

title: apple pizza pie
directions: Mix flour and salt.
Cut in shortening until crumbly.
Add cheese.
Sprinkle with water and form into ball.
Roll pastry into 15-inch circle.
Place on floured round baking sheet.
Combine creamer, sugars, flour, salt and spices.
Sprinkle with half the mixture over pastry.
Cut butter into remaining half until crumbly. Arrange apple slices overlapping in circles on crust.
Top with remaining crumbs.
Bake at 450° for 30 minutes.
Serve warm.
Makes 12 servings.

title: chocolate eclair cake
directions: Boil milk, cocoa, sugar and salt together.
Add the butter and vanilla, then set aside to cool.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Put cooked and deboned chicken into baking dish (9 x 13-inch). Dilute soups with 2 cans of chicken broth and pour over chicken (use broth chicken was cooked in). Melt margarine and add dressing mix, onion, loaf bread and egg. Mix well and pour over chicken and soup mixture. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: batter fried chicken
directions: Simmer 1 (2 to	2 1/2 pound) frying chicken (cut up) in lightly salted water for 20 minutes.
Drain.
Sprinkle chicken pieces lightly with
salt.	Coat
with
butter
and set aside. Sift together flour, baking powder and salt;
set aside.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni twirls according to package directions.
Rinse in cold water and drain.
Mix in other ingredients.
Chill.

title: blueberry bread
directions: Mix together and bake about 1 hour at 325°.

title: sukuma weki
directions: Fry onion and chopped tomato until tender in oil (a little oil).
Put in chopped spinach and fry until tender.
It is a must to eat with fingers!
Each bite is rolled with a pinch of Ugali.

title: beef stew(microwave)
directions: Put beef cubes in 3-quart microwave baking dish.
Sprinkle with salt.
Combine gravy mix and 1 cup water; stir.
Pour over meat.
Cover and cook on High 5 minutes; stir.
Cover and cook on Bake (60) for 20 minutes.
Add celery, carrots and potatoes.
Stir lightly so that vegetables are covered with gravy.
Add more water for a thinner gravy.
Cover and cook on Simmer for 25 to 30 minutes or until meat and vegetables are tender.
Remove and let stand 5 minutes before serving.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Cook spaghetti as directed; set aside. In Dutch oven, melt margarine.
Stir in flour.
Add chicken broth and cook, stirring constantly, until sauce is thickened.
Remove from heat.
Stir in half and half, sherry, parsley, salt, nutmeg and pepper.
Toss chicken, mushrooms and spaghetti into sauce. Put 1/2 of Mozzarella cheese into this mix.

title: chicken almond sandwiches
directions: Blend chicken and almonds together with the cream and add the seasonings.
Spread between buttered slices of bread.

title: healthy heart chicken
directions: In skillet, heat oil over medium-high heat. Add chicken. Sprinkle with mix. Saute 4 minutes each side or until done.
Add lemon juice and stir, scraping brown bits from bottom of pan. Turn chicken and add parsley. Serve over rice or pasta.

title: chocolate pie
directions: In saucepan, combine sugar and flour; gradually stir in milk and chocolate. Cook and stir over medium heat until bubbly.
Cook and stir 2 minutes. Remove from heat. Stir small amount hot mixture into yolks. Immediately return to hot mixture. Cook 2 minutes, stirring constantly. Remove from heat. Add butter and vanilla.
Pour into cooked baked pastry shell. Spread meringue atop pie and bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes; cool.

title: oyster stew
directions: Place all ingredients except oysters in the blender, cover. Press button 7 for 20 seconds.
Remove cover and add oysters and liquid in can and cover.
Press button 3 for 10 seconds or until the oysters are coarsely chopped.
Pour mixture in saucepan and heat, stirring until thick and smooth.

title: wild rice casserole
directions: Mix rice, pepper, chives, onion, mushrooms, chestnuts, salt and pepper.
Add melted margarine and marinate for 1 hour (overnight is okay).
Add broth and bake for 1 hour at 300° to 350°.
Add slivered almonds for the last 20 to 30 minutes.

title: apple cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs and beat well.
Add dry ingredients alternately with nuts and apples.
Bake at 350° in a 9 x 13-inch pan, about 1 hour.

title: asparagus bake
directions: Place the asparagus in a shallow greased baking dish. Combine the red pepper, mayonnaise, cheese and green onion.
Fold the beaten egg whites into the other ingredients and spread over the asparagus.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until heated through.

title: peaches and cream cheese pie
directions: Mix flour and vanilla pudding in a small bowl.
Add egg, milk and margarine.
Beat 2 minutes.
Pour into well greased 8 x 2-inch cake pan, Pyrex dish or deep dish pie plate.
(Do not use regular pie plate.)

title: tomato soup cake
directions: Mix sugar, shortening, egg and tomato soup together.
Add flour, baking powder, baking soda, cinnamon, cloves and nutmeg. Add nuts and raisins.
Bake at 350° for approximately 50 minutes in loaf size pan.

title: apple pancakes
directions: Beat all ingredients, except apple, with whisk or hand beater until smooth.
Stir in apple.
Pour scant 1/4 cup butter onto hot griddle for each pancake (grease griddle if necessary).
Cook until pancakes are dry around edges.
Turn.
Cook until brown. Makes about 14 pancakes.

title: moist baked potatoes
directions: Wash potatoes.
Slice potato in middle (like you are going to cut potato in half, but don't).
Wrap in aluminum foil.
Arrange in an iron skillet or baking dish.
Put about 1-inch of water in dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until potatoes are tender when pricked with a fork.

title: salad dressing
directions: Add crushed garlic to taste and a few drops fresh lemon juice. Combine all in jar and shake well.
Will keep in refrigerator for a few weeks.

title: fancy patties
directions: Mix ingredients.
Heat oil in deep pan or deep fryer.
Let iron heat in oil; dip in batter just up sides.
Dip in oil until brown.
Flip off onto paper towels to drain.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: artichoke frittata
directions: Saute onion and garlic in oil until limp.
Remove from heat. Drain and chop artichoke hearts; add to onion and garlic.
Beat eggs; add to mixture.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well. Pour into greased 7 x 11-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour. Let cool; cut into squares.
Good for parties or holidays as appetizers.

title: triffle
directions: In a triffle, or clear glass bowl, layer pound cake.
Top with pudding, prepared as per package directions.
Spread strawberry filling over pudding and top with Cool Whip.
Chill. For variation use lemon pudding mix or blueberry pie filling in place of strawberry pie filling.

title: cherry cheese cake
directions: Combine graham cracker crumbs, melted butter, brown sugar and press mixture in bottom of a 9 x 13 pan.
Prepare 2 envelopes of Dream Whip as per package instructions.
Blend together cream cheese and confectionary sugar.
Fold cream cheese mixture into Dream Whip.
Spread this mixture on top of base.
Top with cherry pie filling. Refrigerate overnight before serving.

title: lo-cal chicken cacciatore
directions: Combine all ingredients and simmer 45 minutes.
Remove bay leaf before serving.
Makes 4 servings.

title: never fail homemade bread
directions: In large bowl, mix 2 cups water, yeast, salt, sugar and melted butter.
Stir or let stand until ingredients are mixed well and yeast is dissolved.
Add 3 cups flour and mix well with electric mixer.
Gradually add 3 more cups flour, stirring well.
Place in greased bowl and cover with cloth.
Put in warm place and let rise unti l double in bulk.
Shape dough into loaves, rolls or cinnamon rolls.
Let rise again.
Bake at 375° until brown.

title: strawberry yogurt pie
directions: Thoroughly combine crushed fruit and yogort.
Fold in Cool Whip; blend well.
Spoon into crust and freeze for 4 hours. Remove from freezer and place in refrigerator 30 minutes before serving.
Store any left over in the freezer.

title: onion soup
directions: Saute onions in butter until golden brown.
Stir in flour to make a smooth paste.
Gradually stir in consomme.
Cover and simmer 30 minutes.

title: holiday sweet potato surprise
directions: Boil potatoes until tender. Peel and mash.
Add all other ingredients except marshmallows.
mix well.
Pour into a greased 12 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 20 minutes. Sprinkle with marshmallows.
Bake about 5 minutes or until brown.

title: monster cookies
directions: Mix in order and drop on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 6 to 7 minutes.
(Maybe longer if you want a crispier cookie.)

title: dutch meat loaf(my favorite meat loaf)
directions: Combine and pour over meat loaf and bake in moderate oven at 350° for 1 hour or until cooked through.

title: chocolate mound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream shortening and sugar.
Add egg yolks, one at a time.
Melt chocolate in boiling water; add to creamed mixture.
Dissolve soda in 1/4 cup milk.
Alternately add flour and milk to first mixture.
Add vanilla and salt.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Makes 6 layers.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Make two kinds of frosting.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli and drain.
Mix all ingredients except crackers. Put in square baking pan.
Sprinkle crushed crackers over the top.
Bake about 45 minutes until crackers brown in 350° oven. Serves 6.

title: peanut butter cup cookies
directions: Cream together sugar, brown sugar, oleo, peanut butter, egg and vanilla.
Mix flour, soda and salt and add to creamed mixture. Roll dough into 36 balls.
Place in small muffin tins.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes at 350°.
After baking, remove from oven and immediately place small peanut butter cup in center of each cookie (press it down).
Let cool completely before removing from pan. Be sure to remove foil from peanut butter cup before using!

title: frosted pumpkin bars
directions: Mix together sugar, eggs, pumpkin and oil.
Add flour, baking powder, soda, cinnamon and nuts or coconut.
Bake in well-greased and floured 10 x 15-inch pan at 325° for about 1/2 hour.
Frost with cream cheese icing when cool.

title: fruit compote
directions: Pears should be undrained.
Frozen strawberries, thawed and undrained.
Apples sliced a cubit.
Bananas, sliced.
Refrigerate about 5 to 6 hours.
If you use about 1/2 of vanilla pudding, it is better.
Try it both ways if you like.

title: diabetic cake
directions: Cook raisins in the water until all liquid boils out.
Cool. Add applesauce, sweetener, oil and eggs, mixing well.
Blend in the flour, soda, cinnamon and vanilla.
Pour into large tube pan. Bake at 350 degrees for 30 to 35 minutes or until center tests done with toothpick.

title: bread pudding
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into well sprayed baking pan (with Pam).
Make sure baking pan is deep enough so pudding will not bubble over.
Bake at 350° until lightly brown on top.

title: summer squash casserole
directions: Cook squash in covered pan in small amount of water along with the onion; squash makes its own liquids; needs only enough water to get it started.
Cook until tender but not falling apart.
Drain and combine with bread, egg, salt, pepper, basil and half the cheese.
Butter 2-quart casserole.
Place the mixture in it and dot with butter.
Top with remaining cheese.
Bake in preheated oven at 375° for 30 to 40 minutes or until firm.
Serves 6.

title: corned beef salad
directions: Mix Jell-O and water; let jell until slightly thickened.
Add mayonnaise and whip.
Add the beef, eggs, olives, pepper, celery and onion.
Refrigerate.
Cut into squares and decorate with sliced olives.

title: dirt cake
directions: Mix cream cheese, sugar and Cool Whip until smooth.
Mix the pudding mix and milk and add to cream cheese mixture.
Crumble cookies in food processor.
Serve in alternate layers in a large, clean pot for plants (plastic).
Be sure to end with cookie crumb layer on top to look like dirt.
Press and bouquet of silk flowers (stem wrapped in foil) into center and arrange.
Use as centerpiece and shock everyone by serving it for dessert!

title: hamburger steak
directions: Mix ingredients together and shape into steak size pieces and place in casserole dish.
Pour 1 can cream of mushroom soup over steaks and place in oven.
Cook at 350° for about 45 minutes or until done.

title: jello cake
directions: Bake cake and let cool.
Mix jello with 1/2 amount of water, and let cool, but not jelled.
Punch holes in cake and pour in jello.
Mix box of pudding and Dream Whip together, using milk, add vanilla and food coloring.
Spread on top of cake and keep refrigerated.

title: taco pie
directions: Prick
bottoms
and sides of crust.
Bake 10 minutes at 400°. Reduce oven temperature to 350°.
In skillet, cook meat and
onion until
browned.
Drain
fat and add taco seasoning according
to directions.
In small mixing bowl, combine beans and 1/3 cup taco sauce.
Layer 1/2 bean mix in pie shell.
Top with
seasoned meat, 1 cup cheese and taco chips.
Repeat layers, excluding chips.
Bake on preheated cookie sheet 20 to 25
minutes.
Remove from oven.
Top with lettuce, tomato and additional taco sauce to taste.

title: gulliver's creamed corn
directions: In a saucepan, combine all ingredients except butter and flour; bring to a boil.
Simmer for 5 minutes.
Blend butter with flour; add to corn mixture; mix well and remove from heat.
Serves 8.

title: sugarless christmas cookies
directions: Cream the butter. Sift the dry ingredients together; add to the butter. Add Sweet 'N Low and vanilla to mixture, then form into a roll 6 inches long. Wrap the roll in wax paper and chill in the refrigerator. When chilled, slice into 24 even-size cookies and bake in a moderate oven at 350° until brown.

title: strawberry pizza
directions: Mix well sugar and shortening, then add the eggs, then flour mixture.
Bake in a large cookie sheet at 375°.
Cool.

title: apple cake
directions: Fill pie plate 2/3 full of apples.
Sprinkle with cinnamon and 1 tablespoon sugar.
Combine in bowl 1 cup sugar, egg, nuts, flour and butter.
Pour over apples and bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix together and form into ball.
Sprinkle with chile powder. Wrap in wax paper or foil and refrigerate until ready to use.

title: salad dressing pickles
directions: Peel and slice or chunk cukes and onions.
Let stand overnight in brine of salt and water.
Pour brine off in the morning.
Make sauce of remaining ingredients.
Add cukes and onions.
Cook 10 to 15 minutes after they come to a boil.
Pack in jars and seal while hot.

title: homemade orange sherbet
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients together in ice cream freezer.
Fill to the fill line with Orange Crush.
Make in freezer until done.

title: hush puppies
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Set aside and let rise; do not re-stir.
Dip risings and drop into hot grease with ice tea spoon. If you let the spoon get hot in the grease, you can use over again without cleaning.
Hush puppies should turn themselves over in the grease.

title: mexican hot sauce
directions: Mix ingredients in heavy pot; simmer to desired thickness. Put in sterile jars.
Seal and water bath for 15 minutes.

title: marsha, marsha marshmallow squares
directions: In a large saucepan, melt marshmallows and margarine over medium heat, stirring constantly. When mixture is smooth, remove from heat and stir in vanilla. Add cereal in small batches, stirring well after each addition; stir in chocolate chips.

Spray a 9 x 13-inch baking pan with nonstick spray. Press cereal mixture evenly into pan; cover with plastic wrap and refrigerate until firm (about 1 hour). For crunchy squares, store in an airtight container in the refrigerator. For chewy squares, store at room temperature. Make 24 squares.

title: cherry salad
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Spoon into paper cupcake cups.
May be frozen.

title: chocolate chip walnut pie
directions: Beat eggs; add flour and sugar.
Mix well.
Add remaining ingredients.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
It's great served warm with vanilla ice cream.

title: sara's stuffed jalapeno peppers
directions: Cut each pepper in half lengthwise and remove vein and seed. In a small bowl, blend the cream cheese, eggs and mayonnaise. Stir in onion and garlic salt to taste. Stuff pepper halves with cheese mixture. Chill before serving. Yield: Approximately 30 appetizers.

title: taco casserole
directions: Place tortilla wedges on a baking sheet and bake at 350° for 10 minutes or until crisp; set aside.
Mix meat, tomato sauce, chilies, onion, oregano and garlic powder.
Pour into 10 x 6 x 2-inch baking dish and sprinkle with cheese.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 25 minutes or until heated through.
Serve on lettuce and tomato (if desired) with tortilla wedges.
Makes 6 servings.

title: best bread dough ornaments
directions: Bring water to a boil; add salt.
Remove from heat and let sit until cold.
Add flour and knead 10 minutes.
Shape as desired. Place on a foil-lined baking sheet and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Grease a 1 1/2 quart casserole.
Place 1 cup of the rice over bottom of casserole.
Cover with half of the broccoli.
Sprinkle 1/2 cup of the Cheddar cheese and 1/2 cup of the croutons over broccoli.
Repeat layers with remaining rice and broccoli.
In medium bowl, combine half and half, eggs, sour cream, salt, mustard, pepper, thyme and tarragon.
Stir in Muenster cheese. Cover and refrigerate.
Cover casserole and refrigerate until baking time.
About 1 hour before serving time preheat oven to 375 degrees.
Pour egg mixture evenly over casserole.
Top with remaining 1/4 cup Cheddar cheese and 1/4 cup croutons.
Bake 40 to 50 minutes.

title: orange pineapple jello salad
directions: Dissolve Jello in boiling water; stir in cold water. Add well-drained pineapple. Stir well and pour into 9 x 13 inch pan. Cool until set.

title: molasses crinkles
directions: Thoroughly cream shortening and brown sugar.
Add egg and molasses.
Beat well.
Add sifted ingredients.
Mix well.
Chill thoroughly or overnight.
Shape in balls the size of walnuts and dip one side in granulated sugar.
Place, sugared side up, on greased cookie sheet, 2 or 3 inches apart.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Makes 3 dozen cookies.

title: lois' pecan pralines
directions: Put first 4 ingredients in boiler and when mixture begins to boil, add the nuts.
Boil and stir occasionally until a little dropped in cold water makes a soft ball.
Remove from heat and set aside to cool a short time.
Then add vanilla and stir until mixture begins to stiffen.
Drop by tablespoonfuls on a sheet of waxed paper.
If it becomes too hard, return to very low heat and add 2 or 3 teaspoonfuls of boiling water.
Then drop again. Yield: about 30 pralines.

title: cranberry fluff
directions: The night before, wash cranberries and grind cranberries.
Add sugar and marshmallows to ground berries.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.

title: copper carrots
directions: Cook carrots in boiling water in large pan until tender-crisp (approximately 5 minutes).
Drain and cool.
Combine soup, sugar, oil, vinegar and salt until smooth.
Add carrots and stir gently to cover.
Refrigerate for at least 24 hours.

title: english pea salad
directions: Mix peas, celery, pepper, pimento, onion, green beans and water chestnuts.
Mix white vinegar, water, salt, oil and sugar; bring to a boil.
Cool.
Pour over vegetables.
Refrigerate overnight.
Drain before serving.
Keeps 2 weeks in refrigerator.

title: chestnut stuffing
directions: In a large saucepan, melt butter or margarine.
Add onions and saute until tender, but not brown.
Stir remaining ingredients, except broth, over mixture.
Toss lightly with a fork to moisten. Makes 14 servings, about 140 calories per 1/2 cup serving.

title: simple low-fat turkey meat loaf
directions: Mix thoroughly.
Place in loaf pan that was sprayed with nonfat cooking spray.
Pour the can of tomato sauce on top.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Serves 6.

title: fresh berry cobbler
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Prepare and wash berries.
Drain well and add sugar.
Set aside.
Blend together flour and water or juice.
Cook over medium heat until mixture comes to a boil, stirring constantly.
Add berry mixture and cook over low heat just until tender.
Pour hot mixture into a 1 1/2-quart casserole. Dot with butter.
Add spices, if desired.
Prepare Sweet Drop Biscuit Dough.
Drop from a spoon into berry mixture.
Do not stir.
Bake for 35 to 40 minutes.
Serve hot with cream if desired.
Makes 5 to 6 servings.

title: baked beans
directions: Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Place the ingredients in a large bowl and blend well.
Bake.

title: winter slush
directions: Mix pineapple juice, cream of coconut and rum together in a plastic container and store in freezer.

title: baked potato soup
directions: Melt butter.
Stir in flour until smooth.
Gradually add milk. Stir constantly.
Add potatoes and onions.
Bring to a boil; reduce heat and simmer 10 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients until cheese is melted.

title: popsicles delicious
directions: Mix dry ingredients together.
Mix 6 tablespoons of dry mix to 3/4 cup boiling water.
Add 3/4 cup cold water.
Put in popsicle mold.
Delicious.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook sliced squash and chopped onion in salted boiling water for 5 minutes.
Drain.
Combine soup and sour cream.
Stir in grated carrots.
Add squash and onion to the soup and sour cream mixture.
Combine the stuffing mix and butter.
Spread half of the stuffing mixture in bottom of an 11 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish. Spoon vegetable mixture over the top and top with remaining stuffing.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: no-bake cheesecake
directions: Cut up cream cheese and mix with Cool Whip on medium speed for 2 minutes.
Add vanilla and sugar.
Mix for 3 minutes or until smooth.
Empty into pie shell and chill.
Just before serving, spoon on cherry pie filling.

title: welsh rarebit
directions: *It is important always to buy Cheddar cut from the wheel. Don't ever use the packaged orange colored blocks sold in supermarkets under the name Cheddar.
Apart from the awful taste, these have been so highly processed that they don't even melt properly.

title: chocolate fudge pie
directions: Mix cocoa and sugar together.
Beat eggs and add to sugar mixture.
Add milk, melted margarine and vanilla.
Pour into unbaked 9-inch pie pan.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.
Serve plain or with whipped topping.

title: seven layer salad
directions: Layer
in
large container lettuce, onion, green pepper, green peas,
Parmesan cheese, mayonnaise and Bac*Os.
Marinate overnight.

title: punch
directions: Add 2 cups club soda to the ingredients in punch bowl.

title: sausage ball appetizer
directions: Form into small balls (mix first, of course!).
Bake on cookie sheet at 400° for 15 minutes.
(May be cooled and frozen, if desired.)

title: lynn's rice and pork chops
directions: Sear pork chops.
Cover with hot water in skillet.
Add dry onion soup mix.
Simmer 1 hour.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Cook ground beef and onion in butter. Stir in salt, garlic salt and mushrooms when beef is done. Simmer for 5 minutes.
Take off heat. Stir in soup. Simmer, uncovered, for 10 minutes.
Stir in sour cream.
Heat through. Pour over noodles.

title: dilly dip for vegetables
directions: Combine all ingredients and chill.

title: spinach salad
directions: Mix and chop 2 eggs; save remaining eggs for top. Slice mushrooms. Mix all together except mushrooms. Add these last. Decorate top with 2 remaining sliced eggs.

title: chicken papri-kosh
directions: Simmer 45 minutes in a small frying pan.
Serve over egg noodles.

title: lou's chicken marsala buffet style
directions: Clean, wash and cut cutlets into bite-size pieces.
Dip into flour mixed with salt and pepper.
Using 2 large frypans, place 1/2 pound butter in each and melt on low heat.
Place chicken into frypans equally and cover.
Turn chicken as it simmers. Meanwhile, on medium speed, mix together heavy cream or half and half together.
Add wine.
Mix until bubbly.
When chicken looks golden and cooked, add cream mixture and stir thoroughly.
Cover. As mixture thickens, add black pepper and granulated garlic to taste.
Remove to large serving pan.
Top with orange slices for garnish.
Serves 25.

title: irish cream liqueur
directions: In blender, put condensed milk, light cream, chocolate syrup and whiskey.
Blend 40 seconds, then add eggs (beaten well). Blend 20 more seconds.
Refrigerate.
Shake well before serving. Keeps in refrigerator 4 months.

title: chewy oatmeal cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Grease baking sheet.
Combine Crisco, sugar, egg, milk and vanilla.
Mix on medium speed until well blended.
Add flour, soda, salt, cinnamon, oats, raisins and nuts. Mix.
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls onto baking sheet.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes.

title: hot cheese dip
directions: Brown sausage and onion; drain.
Put in crock-pot.
Cube Velveeta cheese into 1-inch pieces.
Add cheese and remaining ingredients to crock-pot.
Heat through.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: turkey noodle casserole
directions: Combine noodles and remaining ingredients in large mixing bowl.
Mix well.
Spoon into greased shallow 2-quart oblong dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: bread pudding
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Scald milk; add butter.
Beat eggs slightly in bowl; stir in milk mixture, sugar, salt and cinnamon. Put bread cubes and raisins in 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Pour milk mixture over; stir gently.
Place in pan of hot water.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes or until knife inserted 1 inch from edge comes out clean.
Serve warm or cold with cream or whipped cream if desired.

title: prune cake(no sugar cake)
directions: Mix all dry ingredients.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Pour into Bundt pan and bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done.
Knife inserted in cake will come out clean.

title: butterscotch brownies
directions: *If nuts are not desired, add one of the following: chocolate chips, butterscotch chips, white chocolate chips or toffee pieces. Preheat oven to 350°. Melt margarine over low heat; watch so it does not burn. Remove from heat. In a large bowl, combine the margarine, sugar and eggs. Set aside.

title: fantasy fudge
directions: Combine sugar, margarine and milk in heavy saucepan; bring to a full rolling boil, stirring constantly.
Continue boiling 5 minutes, over medium heat, stirring constantly (mixture scorches easily).
Remove from heat.
Stir in chocolate until melted.
Add Marshmallow Creme, nuts and vanilla; beat until well blended. Pour into greased 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Cool at room temperature; cut into squares.
Makes 3 pounds.

title: broccoli with mustard butter
directions: Trim broccoli and cut into spears.
Cook broccoli in a large pot of boiling salted water until tender, about 5 minutes.
Drain. In the hot pot, melt butter over low heat.
Put mustard in a small bowl; gradually pour in butter, stirring constantly to combine. Pour over broccoli and serve; or toss first to coat.
Serves about 8.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Mix all together well and pour into a very large casserole. Topping:
Crumble Cheese-It crackers and pour into melted margarine.
(Add can of slivered almonds-optional)
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Great for a covered dish supper!

title: meat and potato casserole
directions: Brown ground beef, salt and pepper to taste.
Taco seasoning or chili seasoning can be added to beef.
Slice peeled potatoes into round slices and boil until tender; drain.
In a baking dish, put potatoes on bottom.
Layer evenly, then put hamburger meat evenly spread on top.
Put cheese on top, amount depends on own taste.
Bake at 350° long enough to melt cheese.

title: cinnamon swirl whole wheat raisin bread
directions: Mix 3 cups flour, 1/2 cup sugar, salt and yeast in a large bowl.
Heat water and oil to 120° to 130°; stir into flour mix. Beat in eggs until smooth.
Mix in whole wheat flour and enough of remaining flour to make dough easy to handle.
Turn dough onto floured surface.
Knead 8 to 10 minutes, until smooth and elastic. Place in greased bowl, turning to coat all sides.
(Can be refrigerated for up to 4 days.)
Cover; let rise until double, about 1 hour.
Grease two 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pans.
Punch down and divide in half.
Knead half of raisins into each ball of dough.
Roll each ball into a 9 x 18-inch rectangle; brush each with 1 tablespoon butter.

title: mom's rhubarb pie
directions: Cook rhubarb.
Stir in sugar and jello.
Let cool and then stir in Cool Whip.
Pour into graham cracker crust.
Let set in refrigerator until ready to serve.

title: quick punch
directions: Let sherbet soften.
Place in a punch bowl and add ginger ale. Stir slowly.
Serve immediately.

title: dilly bread
directions: Soften yeast in warm water.
Combine with next 7 ingredients. Add flour, a little at a time, beating after each addition.
Make a stiff dough.
Cover and let rise, in a warm place, until doubled.
Stir down and place in well-greased loaf pan.
Sprinkle liberally with garlic salt.
Let rise again and bake at 350° for 40 minutes, until golden brown.
Brush with soft butter and sprinkle with salt.

title: rice ramano
directions: Saute peppers and onions in broth until tender.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer about 30 minutes or until rice is tender and liquid is absorbed.

title: samantha's chow-chow
directions: Chop cabbage, peppers, tomatoes, cucumbers and onions; mix together.
Put pickle spices in a clean piece of cloth; tie.
Pour vinegar mixture over cabbage mixture.
Put spice bag in.
Cook until tender.
Put in pint jars.

title: norwegian rulle polserolled sausage
directions: Place thin strips of salt pork and half of the onion slices on the flank steak.
Sprinkle with salt, pepper and allspice.
Roll up like a jelly roll and wrap with cheese cloth.
Tie the ends securely to prevent the filling from falling out.
Place meat in a kettle with water to cover.
Add cut up celery, rest of onion slices, and bay leaf.
Simmer 2 hours.
Remove meat and cool slightly.
Press the meat by placing in a Rulle Polse Press or by putting in a loaf pan and weighting it down with another loaf pan filled with weights or a brick.
Keep refrigerated until ready to serve.
Serve cold, sliced thinly, on cocktail bread.

title: kahlua
