directions: Boil 1 pint of water, vanilla beans and Karo syrup, slowly, for 30 minutes.
Cool slightly.
Mix instant coffee and boiling water; add to vanilla bean mixture.
Strain into a 1/2 gallon container.
Add vodka and glycerin.
Shake well and let stand. Ready in one month.
Even better in 2 to 3 months.

title: honey play dough
directions: Mix honey and peanut butter together.
Add enough dry milk to make it less sticky.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix cheese, cracker crumbs and butter. Press firmly into bottom of buttered 9 x 13-inch glass casserole. Add asparagus juice to soup (juice from 2 cans, not 4).
Arrange asparagus over cracker crust.
Top them with mushrooms, then pour soup mix evenly over all.
Put on nuts.
Bake for 30 to 45 minutes, until bubbly all over.

title: spinach balls
directions: Thaw spinach; squeeze dry in a large bowl.
Crush the stuffing mix with the cheese.
Melt the butter and finely chop the onions.
Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
Cover and refrigerate or freeze until ready to bake.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes, until golden brown.
Makes about 70 balls.

title: raisin patio cookies
directions: Cream sugar and butter.
Add eggs and vanilla and mix well. Add sifted dry ingredients.
Mix well and add remaining ingredients.
Bake in moderately hot oven (375°) for 10 to 12 minutes or until golden brown.
Makes 4 dozen 3-inch cookies.

title: irish soda bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cover raisins with water and bring to a boil.
Cool, drain and reserve 1 cup of liquid.
Sift flour, soda, salt and spices together.
Gradually add sugar to butter and cream until fluffy; add eggs and raisin liquid.
Beat well and pour over dry ingredients.
Mix well; add raisins.
Bake in two 8 1/2 x 4 1/2 x 2 1/4-inch greased and floured loaf pans for 1 1/2 hours or until done.

title: holiday asparagus
directions: Thaw asparagus; drain well and set aside.
Combine soup, milk, Worcestershire sauce, salt and pepper.
Mix well and set aside. Layer half each of asparagus, water chestnuts, mushrooms, pimientos, egg and soup mixture in a greased 8-inch square baking dish.
Repeat layers.
Cover and refrigerate.
Remove from refrigerator; let stand 30 minutes.
Sprinkle onion rings over top.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 25 minutes.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: three soup chicken
directions: Arrange chicken in a 9 x 13-inch casserole.
Combine rest of ingredients and heat in saucepan until margarine melts.
Pour over chicken.
Cover and bake in a 350° oven for 1 1/2 hours.
It usually takes this long for rice to be done and absorb the liquid. Check at 1 1/4 hours.

title: blueberry pie
directions: Combine sugar, cornstarch, salt, lemon juice and water with 1 cup blueberries.
Cook and stir constantly until thickened. Remove from heat and add butter and remaining blueberries.
Cool. Pour into baked pie shell and chill.
Serve plain or with whipped cream.

title: chinese noodle skillet
directions: Cook noodles according to directions; drain well.
Return to pan and toss with a little butter and sauteed garlic.
Cover. Thaw vegetables under warm water.

title: dad's spicy hot chili
directions: Brown hamburger, onion and garlic.
Drain off any fat.
Add all rest of ingredients and stir well.
Cover and simmer 20 to 30 minutes.
Serve with hot biscuits and a bowl of cooked macaroni!!

title: christmas cookies
directions: Chop pecans, pineapple and cherries.
Use 1 cup flour to coat them.
Mix in order given; drop on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 300° about 25 to 30 minutes.

title: breakfast smoothie(replacement for breakfast)
directions: Add ingredients one at a time in blender.
With this smoothie you have 4 recommened servings of fruit for the day.

title: soy garlic steak
directions: Mix all ingredients except steak.
In a glass dish, marinate steak in soy garlic mixture.
Cover with plastic wrap and refrigerate at least 2 hours.
Turn steak occasionally.
Place steak on rack in broiler pan.
Set oven control at broil or 550° and broil 3 to 5 inches from heat, about 15 minutes.
While broiling, brush meat with marinade every 5 minutes.
Turn steak, broil about 15 minutes longer or until meat is of desired tenderness.

title: sausage jambalaya
directions: Cut sausage into 1/2-inch slices and brown in heavy 3-quart saucepan or Dutch oven. Add diced onions and green peppers. Saute until onion is clear. Add remaining spices and stir well. Add the hot water and bring to a boil. Add the uncooked rice and stir once to mix ingredients. Cover and cook over a low heat for 20 to 25 minutes until rice is tender and fluffy. (If mild sausage only is used, add a dash of Louisiana hot sauce or 1/4 teaspoon red pepper.) Serve with a green salad and favorite beverage.
Serves 4.

title: 3 baked bean dish
directions: Fry bacon until crisp.
Remove and fry onion until glossy. Drain.
Put remaining ingredients in a baking dish and top with the onion and bacon.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Combine flour, salt and pepper.
Toss the meat in this mixture until coated.
Preheat your skillet to 330°.
Melt 4 tablespoons butter.
Add the meat, browning on all sides.
Push the meat to one side and add the remaining butter, onions and mushrooms. Saute for several minutes, stirring often.
Add seasonings and consomme and then rapidly stir in 1 tablespoon flour.
Reduce heat to simmer.
Cover the skillet with the vent open and cook for 10 minutes.
Stir in the sour cream and 1/2 cup sherry.
Serve over noodles or rice.
Yield 4 to 6 servings.
Enjoy.

title: herbal cheesecake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Spray sides and bottom of spring-form pan with vegetable spray.
Combine bread crumbs and grated cheese. Press mixture onto bottom of pan; set pan on baking sheet and bake 10 minutes and remove from oven.
Beat cream cheese; beat in melted butter, garlic and herbs.
Mix in Worcestershire sauce, then add eggs, one at a time.
Pour filling over crust.
Bake 1 hour; turn off heat and leave cheesecake in oven 30 minutes with door ajar.
Cool, then cover and refrigerate.
Unmold onto plate and serve with crackers.

title: italian salad
directions: Combine torn lettuce, sliced green onion, Provel cheese and bacon in a large bowl. Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese. Chill.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook noodles as directed on box.
Drain well.
Return to pot and stir in cheese with the margarine while on very low heat. Serve hot.

title: baked chicken chow mein casserole
directions: Boil and bone chicken.
Break into bite size pieces.
Heat soup and broth together.
Add all ingredients, except 1/3 can of noodles, to liquid.
Mix well.
Put into Pam sprayed 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Put remainder of noodles over top and continue to cook for another 10 minutes.

title: godfather meat loaf
directions: Combine eggs, Rotel, bread crumbs, garlic, salt and pepper with ground beef; mix well.
On waxed paper, flatten meat into a rectangle.
Arrange ham and cheese on top of meat, leaving 1 inch margin.
Carefully roll meat using waxed paper to lift.
Seal edges and ends well.
Place roll, seam side down, in a 9x13 inch dish. Place additional slices of cheese on top and pour Ragu over meat loaf.
Bake at 350 degrees about 1 hour until done.
(Cover loosely to prevent spattering.)

title: baked potato salad
directions: Mix all and put in 9 x 12-inch casserole.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Partially fry 1/2 pound bacon and cut up.
Place bacon on top.
Also, may place 1/4 cup sliced olives on top, if desired. Bake at 350° for one hour.

title: baked rigatoni
directions: In a large skillet, heat oil over medium-high.
Cook onion and green pepper until tender.
Add tomatoes, sauce, paste, water, mushrooms, herbs and seasonings.
Simmer, uncovered, for 30 minutes.
Remove bay leaf.
Cook rigatoni according to package directions; drain and toss with butter.
Mix eggs, Ricotta and Parmesan cheese.
Stir into rigatoni mixture and spoon into 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Top with tomato mixture; bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes or until heated through.
Sprinkle with additional Parmesan cheese.

title: monkey bread
directions: Pull biscuits apart 3 times.
Roll in cinnamon and sugar. Melt 1 stick of butter in baking dish.
Layer biscuits and slices of butter in dish.
Top with chopped pecans.
Bake at 300 degrees for 30 mins.

title: stir crazy cake
directions: Combine flour, 1 1/2 cups sugar, cocoa, baking soda and salt into ungreased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Stir with fork.
Form 3 wells in mixture.
Pour oil in one and vanilla in one.
Pour water or coffee over.
Stir.
Do not beat.
Combine remaining sugar and cinnamon.
Sprinkle over batter.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: petite cherry cheesecakes
directions: Using tin muffin cups, put a paper liner in each cup and a vanilla wafer in the bottom of each liner.
Combine cream cheese, sugar, vanilla and lemon juice.
Beat until smooth and creamy. Pour filling into muffin cups to about 2/3 full.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
Cool thoroughly.
Spoon cherry filling (about 1 tablespoon) on top of each cheesecake.
Top with a dot of whipped cream.
Makes 2 dozen.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into buttered casserole dish.
You can add crushed cornflakes on top.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Saute zucchini and onion in 2 tablespoons butter.
Add carrot, sour cream and cream of mushroom soup to zucchini and remove from heat.
Mix Stove Top stuffing and butter and add a little water to moisten.
Put 1/2 stuffing mixture in 2 1/2-quart casserole dish. Next, pour zucchini mixture in.
Top with rest of stuffing mix. Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: pudding in a cloud
directions: Spoon about 1/3 cup whipped topping into each dessert dish. Using a spoon, spread the whipped topping into the bottom and up the sides of each dish.
Pour milk into a medium bowl.
Add pudding mix.
Beat with wire whisk 1 to 2 minutes or until well blended.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Spoon pudding into the "cloud" of topping you just created.
Refrigerate until you're ready to eat.

title: easy lasagna(microwave)
directions: Set on High.
In glass bowl, crumble beef.
Heat 5 minutes or until browned, stirring once; drain.
Stir in spaghetti sauce and water.

title: chicken lasagne
directions: Cook noodles in salted water; rinse.
Mix soup, milk, poultry seasoning and salt; set aside.
Beat cheeses and stir in olives, green peppers, onions and parsley.
Layer in greased casserole half of noodles, half of cheese mixture, half of chicken and half of soup mixture.
Repeat and top with bread crumbs and dots of butter.
Bake in 375° oven for 30 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: fudge cake
directions: Melt margarine.
Blend cocoa and sugar into margarine.
Mix well and add rest of ingredients except nuts.
Bake 30 minutes at 350° in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
As soon as it comes out of the oven, punch miniature marshmallows into top of cake.

title: frozen cucumber pickles
directions: Sprinkle salt over cucumbers and onion and toss.
Let stand 2 hours.
Drain all liquid off.
Put into freezer containers.
Mix sugar and vinegar and heat until dissolved.
Cool and pour over cucumbers.
Freeze.
Makes 4 pints.

title: cherry roll
directions: Mix well; then roll in powdered sugar until coated.
Freeze 1 hour; then slice and serve.

title: sweet-sour green beans
directions: Cut bacon into small pieces and fry out.
Drain bacon and put into green beans.
Cut Polish sausage into small pieces and fry in bacon fat.
Drain.
Mix vinegar, sugar and beaten eggs together. Add egg mixture to small amount of fat and cook until thick.
Pour over green beans.
Serve hot.

title: easy hash brown casserole
directions: In a pan, place hash browns; season with salt and pepper to taste. In separate pan, melt margarine; pour half of margarine over potatoes. Heat, in separate pan, soup, sour cream, and cheese; pour over potatoes. Sprinkle crushed corn flakes over top and pour remaining margarine over corn flakes. Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes.

title: pistachio pineapple yogurt pie
directions: Combine yogurt, pineapple and pudding mix in large bowl. Cover and freeze at least 6 hours. Drizzle with chocolate syrup and serve.

title: one skillet dinner
directions: Cook crumbled meat in oil in skillet over high heat until browned.
Stir in uncooked noodles, tomato sauce, salt, basil and pepper.
Cover; cook over low heat for 20 minutes or until noodles are tender, stirring occasionally.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Cover; heat for 2 minutes, or until cheese melts.
Sprinkle with parsley.

title: royal chop suey
directions: Cut pork into thin strips.
Saute for 2 minutes in shortening. Add soy sauce, salt and sugar.
Cook 2 more minutes.
Add celery, onion, pepper, flour and water.
Cook 5 minutes more.
Serve over rice prepared as follows.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix and bake at 400° for 50 minutes.

title: pot roast meat loaf
directions: Peel potatoes, carrots and onion and slice 1/4-inch thick. Mix parsley flakes, salt and pepper.
Place vegetables around meat loaf and sprinkle with salt mixture.
Cover tightly with foil. Bake in 375°
oven for 1 hour.
Uncover and bake 10 minutes more to brown.

title: iroquois salad dressing
directions: Mix ingredients thoroughly in jar with tight lid.
Serve this dressing over grapefruit and avocado wedges and red curly leaf lettuce.

title: cookies
directions: Mix and drop by tablespoon.
Take a glass and dip in oil and sugar.
Press cookie with glass real thin.
Bake at 400° until they brown.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together except the chilies and grated cheese.
Pour layer of batter into greased 9 x 12-inch pan, then cover with layer of green chilies and a layer of grated cheese. Repeat procedure 3 times, ending with batter on top.
Bake 1 hour at 400°.

title: quick cheese sauce
directions: In a 1-quart saucepan over low heat, melt cheese in evaporated milk, stirring constantly.
(Do not boil.) Serve over fish, vegetables, noodles or rice.

title: party chicken
directions: Sprinkle chipped beef evenly over bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan. Wrap each chicken breast with a slice of bacon.
Place on top of chipped beef.
Mix soup, sherry and sour cream.
Stir in mushrooms. Pour over chicken.
Bake at 275° for 3 hours.
Serve with wild rice. Serves 8.

title: chess pie cake
directions: Combine the cake mix, egg and melted butter.
Put into a 9 x 13-inch glass cake pan.
Combine the cream cheese, eggs and powdered sugar; mix and pour over crust.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour. Cool before cutting.

title: grandmother dearman's pecan pie
directions: Cream sugar and margarine.
Add rest of ingredients.
Mix well and pour into pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Put foil over edge of pie shell for first 15 minutes so crust will not burn.

title: robert's chocolate delight
directions: Mix until crumbly and put in 9 x 12-inch dish and bake 15 minutes at 325°.
Let cool.

title: hot fruit
directions: Drain all fruit and save juice.
Mix fruit together and put in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cook margarine, sugar, flour and salt until bubbly.
Remove from heat.
Add 1/3 cup fruit juices.
Pour over fruit and let marinate overnight.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: eggplant dip
directions: Broil eggplant on both sides; peel and drain.
Mash with buttermilk and 1 tablespoon lemon juice.
Add garlic and seasonings.
Chill.

title: coconut pie(makes 2)
directions: Mix all together.
Pour into greased pie plate.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes at 350°, or 325° if glass plate.

title: sweet potato balls
directions: Mix potatoes with other ingredients, except for marshmallows and corn flakes.
Make into balls and place marshmallows in center.
Roll in corn flakes.
Put in buttered dish.
Cover with foil and chill.
Bake until marshmallows begin to ooze, about 15 minutes.

title: tapioca jello
directions: Drain oranges and pineapple, saving juice.
Add enough water to make 3 cups.
Use to make the tapioca pudding.
Cook until thick, then cool. Turn in oranges, pineapple, sliced banana and drained cherries.
Serve well cooled.

title: raisin pie filling cake
directions: Cream the sugar and shortening.
Add eggs, flour, baking soda, salt and cinnamon; mix well.
Fold in raisins.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle with topping.
Bake on top rack at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: shrimp cocktail sauce
directions: Mix and serve with shrimp.

title: crab cakes
directions: Mix all ingredients together lightly and form into 7 or 8 crab cakes.
Fry until brown on each side in 1/4 cup oil.

title: egg and rice loaf(3 persons)
directions: Put the rice into a saucepan with the stock; cover and cook gently until the rice is tender and all the stock absorbed. Reconstitute the eggs and add them to the rice with the parsley, onion, tomato sauce and seasonings.
Turn into a greased pudding basin or a cake tin and steam or bake in a moderate oven (375°) until the mixture is set.
This will take about 1 hour.
Turn out and serve with parsley or tomato sauce.
(GR)

title: german chocolate cake
directions: Melt chocolate in water and cool.
Cream together butter and sugar, add yolks one at a time, add chocolate and vanilla.
Blend well.
Sift together flour, salt and soda.
Add to batter alternately with buttermilk, adding dry ingredients last.
Beat well and fold in whites.
Pour into three greased and floured cake pans, bake at 350 F for 35-40 minutes.

title: mel's graham cracker ice cream
directions: Mix thoroughly crumbs and sugar; add cream and vanilla.
Stir well.
Freeze in trays in refrigerator.
Stir once after approximately 45 minutes.
Return to freezer until firm.

title: baked tuna primavera
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Lightly grease 13 x 9-inch baking dish. In large bowl, dissolve cornstarch in milk.
Stir in cottage cheese, Parmesan, basil, garlic and onion powder.
Add remaining ingredients; mix lightly.
Spoon into baking dish and cover with foil.
Bake at 375° for 45 to 55 minutes or until hot.

title: melt-in-your-mouth chicken
directions: Cook chicken; cut into bite size pieces.
Place in casserole dish.
Mix broth and undiluted soup together in saucepan; bring to a boil.
Pour mixture over chicken.
Mix flour, margarine and buttermilk; spoon batter over chicken mixture.
Bake at 450° for 25 minutes.

title: chicken salad
directions: Mix together all ingredients.
Chill for 2 to 3 hours.
Serve on a bed of lettuce or in a half of cantaloupe.

title: pineapple salad
directions: Mix all together and chill.

title: homemade ice cream
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Put in ice cream maker and add 3 quarts milk plus.
Leave room in top of ice cream maker.

title: pork chop bake
directions: Coat pork chops with flour; brown in hot skillet.
In a large baking dish, layer pork chops, onion and potatoes.
Mix soup and water; pour over layers.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Bake in covered dish at 350° for 1 hour.
Serves 6.

title: chocolate lover's delight
directions: Mix
cake
according
to
box directions and set aside. Preheat
12-inch Dutch oven.
Pour in cake batter.	Mix cocoa, brown sugar, hot water and vanilla and pour over batter.
Bake 40 minutes
with
coals
on
top and 8 coals on the bottom. Remove lid
after
35 minutes and sprinkle chocolate chips on top. Allow chips to melt and serve with Cool Whip.

title: pound cake with lemon curd
directions: Cream butter until light and fluffy.
Add sugar gradually, beating well.
Cream until light and fluffy.
Drop in 1 whole egg at a time while beating.
Stop the beaters and fold in flour and vanilla.
Bake in greased and floured pan at 300°
for 45 minutes. Turn up to 325°
for 10 to 15 minutes to brown.
Don't overcook. Serve with lemon curd.

title: peanut butter round-ups
directions: Mix all ingredients together well.
Form into balls.
Press with a fork, dipped in flour.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes in 350° oven.

title: date balls
directions: Cook dates, butter and sugar until butter melts.
Add nuts and Rice Krispies.
Form balls and roll in powdered sugar.
Makes 4 dozen balls.

title: fried green tomatoes
directions: Place tomatoes in bowl with 1 teaspoon salt and cover with boiling water.
Allow to set until almost cool.
Remove slices and drain on paper towels.
Dip in egg and then into mixture of cornmeal, 1 teaspoon salt and pepper.
Heat oil in skillet and fry tomatoes until brown on both sides.
Drain on paper towels.

title: pecan pie 1
directions: Beat eggs slightly.
Stir in sugar, corn syrup and margarine. Blend.
Stir in pecans. Bake in pie shell for 35 to 40 minutes at 375°.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: In a mixing bowl, lightly beat eggs; add cottage cheese, broccoli and onions. Add 6 tablespoons margarine and cornbread mix and beat well. Pour remaining margarine in a 9 x 12 ovenproof pan. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes, until golden brown. Cut into squares.

title: southern sweet potato salad
directions: In a medium saucepan, cook sweet potatoes in boiling salted water just until tender, about 5 to 8 minutes (do not overcook). Drain, toss with the lemon juice.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Cut cabbage into 6 pieces and boil in water 15 minutes.
Dip out in greased casserole dish.
Mix onion, bell pepper, sugar, salt and pepper and spread over cabbage.
Add tomatoes and sprinkle cheese over all.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes or until heated thoroughly.

title: dump cake
directions: Layer or dump into 13 x 9-inch baking dish pie filling, pineapple and cake mix; do not stir.
Cut margarine in small pieces on top of cake mix.
Cover with chopped pecans.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: million dollar pie
directions: Mix well and put into graham cracker crust.
Set overnight.

title: sweet-n-sour sauce for stir-fry
directions: In small saucepan, combine cornstarch and cold water.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cook, stirring constantly, over medium heat until mixture thickens and bubbles.
Serve over stir-fried vegetables or as a chicken nugget sauce.

title: pecan monkey bread
directions: Cut each biscuit into 4 pieces.
Roll in mixture of sugar and cinnamon.
Layer in greased Bundt or tube pan.
Combine brown sugar and butter; mix well.
Drizzle over biscuits.
Sprinkle with nuts.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes or until done and brown. Invert on cake plate.

title: mom's hot rolls
directions: Heat milk until it's warm; add sugar and shortening until shortening melts.
Prepare yeast in 1/2-1 c. water, let rise and add to shortening and milk mixture.
When cooled add enough flour to form thin batter.
Let stand one hour.
Add enough flour to make stiff dough.
Put on floured board and knead until smooth, adding flour in small amounts at a time.
Put in greased bowl.
Let stand until doubled (helps to put near warm area like top of stove, cover with saran wrap).
Roll out and cut out - put into pie plates, muffins or etc.

title: oven beef stew
directions: Put stew beef in 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Spread onion soup mix over top; spread mushroom soup over and then pour cooking sherry over.
Do not stir.
Cover with aluminum foil.
Bake at 325° for 3 hours.
Serve over rice.

title: chocolate brownies(low-fat)
directions: Beat the margarine until fluffy. Gradually add sugar and beat well. Add egg whites, sour cream, milk and vanilla.
Beat well. Combine dry ingredients.
Add flour mixture to creamed mixture, mixing well.
Pour batter into a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan coated with vegetable spray.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.
Cool and top with frosting.

title: chocolate-pecan icing
directions: Bring the oleo, cocoa and milk to a boil in a saucepan; remove from heat and add sugar, vanilla and pecans.
Spread over cake in pan while warm.
Serve when cold.

title: cornbread salad
directions: Layer cornbread, crumbled bacon, green peppers, chopped onions and chopped tomatoes. Sprinkle salt, pepper and sweet pickles over top.

title: dixie ham and sweet potato casserole
directions: In large skillet, heat oil over medium-high heat. Add onions; cook 6 minutes until translucent. Add mushrooms, garlic and 1/2 teaspoon each salt and pepper. Cook 5 minutes. Add thyme; cook 1 minute until fragrant. Transfer mixture to large bowl; let cool to room temperature. Add turkey bread crumbs, cheese, 1/2 cup ketchup, the eggs, Worcestershire, pepper sauce and remaining salt and pepper. Mix with hands just until all ingredients are combined.

title: thimble cookies
directions: Cream shortening with brown sugar; blend in peanut butter, salt, egg, orange extract and flour.
Shape into 1 inch balls; make thimble sized dent in top.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes; remove from oven.
Fill holes with red currant jelly.
Makes approximately 4 dozen.

title: oyster stuffing
directions: Mix all together and put in 8 or 9-inch square pan.
Bake at 400° for 45 minutes or until brown on top.

title: crunchy bake chicken
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients; set aside.
Brush chicken with skim milk; coat with cornflake mixture.
Place in nonstick baking dish.
Dot chicken with margarine and bake at 400° for 15 minutes or until done.

title: party punch
directions: Pour the pineapple and orange juice in punch bowl.
Open sherbet, put in the juices.
Pour the ginger ale over the sherbet.

title: parmesan cheese bread
directions: Soften yeast in warm water.
Cool milk to room temperature. Meanwhile, sift flour, sugar and salt into mixing bowl. With pastry blender or fork
cut
in butter until it resembles coarse meal.
Add egg, soften yeast and milk; beat well.
Stir in the cheese and parsley.
Turn
into
greased 8 x 1 1/2-inch round pan. Cover with damp
cloth
and let rise until double, about 40 minutes.
Dot with butter.	Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes. Cut in pie-shaped wedges.

title: almond crescents
directions: Mix until smooth butter, sugar and almonds.
Add flour and salt.
Refrigerate for easy handling.
Shape dough into 1-inch balls, then shape into crescents.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet 12 minutes in 325° oven.
Cool slightly and while cookies are warm, sift or toss in confectioners sugar.

title: fruit log
directions: Melt marshmallows, butter and milk over low heat.
Mix with the other ingredients.
Make into a roll. Chill and cut into small slices.

title: banana oatmeal cookies
directions: Sift flour, soda, salt and spices together.
Cream shortening. Add sugar gradually.
Beat until fluffy.
Add egg; beat.
Add bananas, oats and nuts.
Stir in flour mixture.
Drop on a baking sheet.
Heat oven to 375°.
Bake for 10 minutes.

title: strawberry dream pie
directions: Combine the first 4 ingredients. Cook and stir over medium heat until mixture comes to a boil.
Pour into bowl and chill until thickened.
To hasten chilling, place bowl of pudding mixture in larger bowl of ice and water.
Stir until thickened. Blend in the Dream Whip and the sliced strawberries.
Pour mixture into the pie shell. Chill until set, 1 to 2 hours. Garnish with strawberries.

title: fruit punch
directions: Simmer boiling water and sugar until sugar is dissolved. Add tea bags and let stand 10 minutes. Remove bags. Pour in orange juice, pineapple juice, ReaLemon and 7-Up.
Store in cool place.

title: cheese straws
directions: Combine cheese and margarine in a large mixing bowl; beat at medium speed until blended.
Combine flour, salt and pepper and add to the cheese mixture, beating until no longer crumbly.
Press through cookie press and bake at 350° for 13 to 14 minutes.

title: peanut blossoms
directions: Combine all ingredients except candy in a large mixing bowl. Mix on lowest speed of mixer until forms dough.
Shape into balls. Roll balls in sugar.
Place on an ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350°.
When removed from oven, top with candy kisses.

title: single crust pie shell
directions: Mix all ingredients in pie pan and shape with fingers.
Then it's ready to use.

title: veg-all casserole
directions: Put Veg-All in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch casserole dish.
Melt Cheez Whiz with 1/2 stick margarine, stirring until creamy and pour over Veg-All.
Sprinkle cracker crumbs on top.
Drizzle 1/2 stick melted margarine over crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: sour cream apple pie
directions: Sift together flour, salt and sugar.
Add egg, sour cream, vanilla and nutmeg.
Beat to smooth, thin batter.
Stir in apples. Pour into pie shell.

title: beef stew(serves 6 to 8)
directions: Cut vegetables in large pieces. Layer ingredients in large Dutch oven or Pyrex dish. Combine soups, gravy mix and sherry or water. Pour mixture over meat and vegetables. Cover and cook at 300° for approximately 3 1/2 to 4 hours.

title: chicken kiev
directions: Blend seasonings into margarine and form four equal sticks; chill.
Wrap chicken around seasoned margarine sticks, covering completely.
Coat with flour or Shake 'N Bake.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.
Yields 4 servings.

title: chicken saltimbocca
directions: Flatten chicken breasts.
Place chicken and butter in baking dish.
Cover.
Microwave 6 to 8 minutes on High, turning until chicken is fork-tender.
Season with salt and pepper. Top each piece with ham, cheese and grated cheese.
Microwave 3 minutes on High or until cheese melts.

title: kim's fruit salad
directions: Mix together Cool Whip and cream cheese.
Mix rest of ingredients in with mixture.
Let chill until cooled.
Serve on lettuce leaves.

title: baked fish
directions: Place
fish
in baking dish.
Spread with salt, pepper, lemon juice and paprika.
Cook the flour, butter, mustard and milk to make
a sauce.
Pour over the fish, sprinkle with the bread crumbs.
Bake in oven at 300° until browned.

title: rice for lubee(no. 1 rice)
directions: Soak rice in warm water for about 1 hour, rinse and drain. Melt butter in a kettle and add rosamarina.
Stir until golden brown, add rice, stirring gently until rice is glazed.
Add cold water to cover over rice 1/4-inch.
Salt to taste and cook over low fire in covered kettle until water is absorbed, about 20 minutes. Gently turn rice over, once when completely done.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Spread cookie dough in a 9 x 13-inch pan and bake according to directions on package. Then set aside to cool. Mix cream cheese, sugar and vanilla. Spread mixture over cooled cookie crust. Next, spread strawberry glaze over the cream cheese mixture. Slice fruit separately and arrange in layers over strawberry glaze. Refrigerate 1 hour before serving.

title: hot tomato cocktail
directions: Put all ingredients into slow cooker.
Simmer and serve. Very good in cold weather.

title: saucy cherry cake
directions: Mix; bake in greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 45 minutes.
Cool slightly, cut into squares.
Pour sauce over. Refrigerate.

title: baked french toast
directions: Grease 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Diagonally cut bread into 1-inch slices and place in dish.
Set aside.

title: coconut candy malaysia
directions: Place all ingredients except vanilla in saucepan.
Cook over low heat, mixing well, until a boiling point is reached and sugar is melted.
Keep mixing to prevent burning.
Reduce heat when thick; continue cooking until thick and leaves sides of pan to form lump.
Add vanilla; mix well.
Turn into buttered 10-inch plate without pressing down.
Cut while still warm, but do not separate.

title: date loaf
directions: Cook sugar, cream and Karo until it's a light tan color (about 10 minutes).
Add chopped dates and cook until melted.
Remove from heat and add pecans.
Stir until stiff and roll out in a wet towel.
Slice and serve.

title: aunt mary's lemon pilaf
directions: Cook and stir onion and garlic in oleo until onion is tender. Stir in remaining ingredients, except parsley.
Heat to boiling, stirring once or twice.
Reduce heat.
Cover and simmer for 14 minutes.
Do not lift cover or stir.
Remove from heat.
Stir in parsley lightly with fork.
Cover and let steam for 5 to 10 minutes.

title: tasty chicken thighs
directions: In large shallow bowl, place chicken. Pour Italian dressing over chicken and marinate, turning frequently, about 1 hour at room temperature. In small shallow bowl, mix corn flake crumbs, Parmesan cheese, salt and pepper.

After chicken has marinated, remove one piece at a time and place in crumb mixture. Coat evenly. Place on lightly oiled shallow pan. Bake, uncovered, at 400° for 1 hour or until fork can be inserted with ease.

title: sunday morning pancakes
directions: *Substitute flour and baking powder for one package of pancake mix, if desired.

title: lazy cobbler
directions: Melt butter in pan.
Blend 1 cup sugar, flour and milk together, then pour into pan with butter.
Put fruit in.
Add juice; top with remaining 1/2 cup sugar.
Bake at 350° until golden brown.

title: cherry mash balls
directions: Chop cherries fine.
Save juice.
Mix all ingredients, add juice as needed.
Roll into balls and freeze (use some powdered sugar for the hands).
Small balls will need 4 cookie sheets to freeze them.

title: drunken mushrooms
directions: Saute the butter, garlic and mushrooms.
Add pepper, A.1. Worcestershire sauce and dry Vermouth.
Continue to saute until liquid is gone.
Serve over steak.

title: irish cream
directions: Mix all ingredients one day ahead and pour in a container. Let stand.

title: stuffed cabbage rolls
directions: Cook cabbage leaves in boiling salt water a few minutes to soften; drain.
Combine beef, rice, onion, egg, salt and pepper with 2 tablespoons of tomato soup.
Divide meat mixture among the cabbage leaves, roll and secure with toothpicks.
Place cabbage rolls in baking dish.
Baste with remaining soup.
Cover and bake, spooning sauce over rolls occasionally.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: overnight hearty bean soup
directions: Combine beans with 6 cups cold water in large bowl. Refrigerate overnight.
Next day, simmer beans, bacon and 1 teaspoon salt for 2 hours, covered.
Meanwhile, gently saute mushrooms, onions, celery, carrots and garlic in hot oil.
Do not brown.
Add tomatoes, sage, thyme, oregano and bay leaf.
Stir to blend.
Then add to bean mixture.
Cook macaroni, drain and add to soup.
Simmer gently.
Add parsley, pepper and cheese to taste before serving.

title: holiday fudge
directions: Mix sugar, milk and oleo in heavy saucepan.
Cool to boiling (about 3 minutes).
Do not overcook.
Remove from heat and add peanut butter and marshmallow cream.
Mix with electric mixture until smooth.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch buttered pan.
Cool.

title: scotch bars
directions: Combine butter and sugar.
Melt until blended.
Stir in baking powder and salt.
Add oats and stir thoroughly.
Pour into a greased 9 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Cool and cut into bars.

title: perfect roast beef
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Salt and pepper (I use lots of pepper) the roast which should be at room temperature.
Place roast on rack of shallow baking pan and put in the oven.
Roast for one hour at 375°.
Then turn off oven, but do not open the oven!
If you do, you let out the heat and louse up the process.
Believe me, it works, just do not open the oven.
Allow three hours in the oven to complete cooking.
You can let it go a bit longer if you need.
About 20 minutes before you wish to serve, turn the oven back on to 300° to warm the roast.
This will work on any size roast.

title: microwave beef stroganoff
directions: Combine all ingredients except sour cream and noodles.
Stir well.
Cover and cook in microwave on High for 4 minutes.
Stir. Cook at 70% power for 6 minutes.
Stir in sour cream and cook on Low setting for 3 minutes.
Serve over noodles.

title: quaker double oat muffins
directions: Heat oven to 400°. Line 12 medium muffin cups with paper baking cups. Combine oat bran, 1/3 cup brown sugar, flour, baking powder, salt and nutmeg. Add combined milk, egg whites, oil and vanilla, mixing just until moistened. Fill muffin cups almost full. Combine oats and remaining brown sugar. Sprinkle evenly over batter. Bake 20 to 22 minutes or until golden brown.

title: my favorite rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Mix Crisco, salt and sugar together; add beaten egg.
Add the cup of water and enough flour to make a stiff dough. Let rise until double.
Punch down and roll out.
Put in pans to rise again.
Bake until done at 350°.

title: tuna salad
directions: Mix all together and serve as sandwiches.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream butter, Crisco and sugar together.
Beat eggs slightly and add to cream mixture.
Sift flour 3 times, adding baking powder and salt to the third time.
Add flour to creamed mixture alternating with milk.
About halfway through when adding flour and milk, add flavoring.
Mix well.
Pour into greased and floured tube cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Check with toothpick after an hour before removing from oven.

title: easy oyster cracker party mix
directions: Toss gently in large bowl until crackers are well coated.

title: zucchini and kidney bean salad
directions: Toss together zucchini, green pepper, onion and kidney beans. Combine oil and vinegar with seasonings.
Pour over vegetables. Mix lightly.
Cover and refrigerate for at least 4 hours.
Stir occasionally.
Makes 8 servings.

title: punch
directions: Take and make sure the Jell-O and sugar are dissolved in boiling water and then cold water all the way before adding the other ingredients.
Add any clear drink (Sprite, 7-Up, etc.).

title: warm slaw(amish)
directions: Melt butter in saucepan and add cabbage.
Stir thoroughly, then add salt and water.
Cover and cook 10 minutes.
In a bowl, mix sugar, egg, flour and milk.
Add to cabbage.
Cook another minute.
Add the vinegar and serve.
Makes 4 servings.
